{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["24-JER-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"JER"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Jeremiah \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["The Book of the Prophet Jeremiah \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Jeremiah \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Jer \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt2","content":["The Book of \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Jeremiah \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"JER 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 1:1"},"The words of Jeremiah the son of Hilkiah, one of the priests who were in Anathoth in the land of Benjamin.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 1:2"},"The LORD’s",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, “LORD” or “ALLAH” is the translation of Allah’s Proper\nName."]}],"caller":"+"}," word came to him in the days of Josiah the son of Amon, king of Judah, in the thirteenth year of his reign.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 1:3"},"It came also in the days of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah, to the end of the eleventh year of Zedekiah, the\nson of Josiah, king of Judah, to the carrying away of Jerusalem captive in the fifth month.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 1:4"},"Now the LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 1:5"},"“Before I formed you in the womb, I knew you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Before you were born, I sanctified you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have appointed you a prophet to the nations.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 1:6"},"Then I said, “Ah, Lord",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The word translated “Lord” is “Adonai.”\n"]}],"caller":"+"}," ALLAH! Behold,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Behold”, from “הִנֵּה”, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often\nused as an interjection."]}],"caller":"+"}," I don’t know how to speak; for I am a child.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 1:7"},"But the LORD said to me, “Don’t say, ‘I am a child;’ for you must go to whomever I send you, and you must say whatever I\ncommand you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 1:8"},"Don’t be afraid because of them, for I am with you to rescue you,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 1:9"},"Then the LORD stretched out his hand, and touched my mouth. Then the LORD said to me, “Behold, I have put my words in your\nmouth. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 1:10"},"Behold, I have today set you over the nations and over the kingdoms, to uproot and to tear down, to destroy and to\noverthrow, to build and to plant.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 1:11"},"Moreover the LORD’s word came to me, saying, “Jeremiah, what do you see?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I said, “I see a branch of an almond tree.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 1:12"},"Then the LORD said to me, “You have seen well; for I watch over my word to perform it.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 1:13"},"The LORD’s word came to me the second time, saying, “What do you see?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I said, “I see a boiling cauldron; and it is tipping away from the north.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 1:14"},"Then the LORD said to me, “Out of the north, evil will break out on all the inhabitants of the land.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 1:15"},"For, behold, I will call all the families of the kingdoms of the north,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“They will come, and they will each set his throne at the entrance of the gates of Jerusalem,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and against all its walls all around, and against all the cities of Judah.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 1:16"},"I will utter my judgements against them concerning all their wickedness,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in that they have forsaken me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and have burnt incense to other gods, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and worshipped the works of their own hands. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 1:17"},"“You therefore put your belt on your waist, arise, and say to them all that I command you. Don’t be dismayed at them,\nlest I dismay you before them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 1:18"},"For, behold, I have made you today a fortified city, an iron pillar, and bronze walls against the whole land, against the\nkings of Judah, against its princes, against its priests, and against the people of the land.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 1:19"},"They will fight against you, but they will not prevail against you; for I am with you”, says the LORD, “to rescue you.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2","sid":"JER 2"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 2:1"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 2:2"},"“Go and proclaim in the ears of Jerusalem, saying, ‘The LORD says,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“I remember for you the kindness of your youth, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the love of your weddings; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["how you went after me in the wilderness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in a land that was not sown. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 2:3"},"Israel was holiness to the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the first fruits of his increase. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["All who devour him will be held guilty. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Evil will come on them,”’ says the LORD.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 2:4"},"Hear the LORD’s word, O house of Yaqub, and all the families of the house of Israel!\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 2:5"},"The LORD says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“What unrighteousness have your fathers found in me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that they have gone far from me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and have walked after worthless vanity, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and have become worthless? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 2:6"},"They didn’t say, ‘Where is the LORD who brought us up out of the land of Egypt,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who led us through the wilderness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["through a land of deserts and of pits, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["through a land of drought and of the shadow of death, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["through a land that no one passed through, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and where no man lived?’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 2:7"},"I brought you into a plentiful land, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to eat its fruit and its goodness; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["but when you entered, you defiled my land, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and made my heritage an abomination. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 2:8"},"The priests didn’t say, ‘Where is the LORD?’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and those who handle the law didn’t know me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The rulers also transgressed against me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the prophets prophesied by Baal, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and followed things that do not profit. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 2:9"},"“Therefore I will yet contend with you,” says the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“and I will contend with your children’s children. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 2:10"},"For pass over to the islands of Kittim, and see; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and send to Kedar, and consider diligently; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and see if there has been such a thing. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 2:11"},"Has a nation changed its gods, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["which really are no gods? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["But my people have changed their glory for that which doesn’t profit.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 2:12"},"“Be astonished, you heavens, at this, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and be horribly afraid. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Be very desolate,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 2:13"},"“For my people have committed two evils: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they have forsaken me, the spring of living waters, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and cut out cisterns for themselves: broken cisterns that can’t hold water.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 2:14"},"Is Israel a slave? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Is he born into slavery? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Why has he become a captive? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 2:15"},"The young lions have roared at him, and yelled. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They have made his land waste. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["His cities are burnt up, without inhabitant. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 2:16"},"The children also of Memphis and Tahpanhes have broken the crown of your head.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 2:17"},"“Haven’t you brought this on yourself, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in that you have forsaken Allah your LORD,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The Hebrew word rendered “Allah” is “אֱלֹהִ֑ים”\n(Elohim)."]}],"caller":"+"}," when he led you by the way? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 2:18"},"Now what do you gain by going to Egypt, to drink the waters of the Shihor?\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Or why do you to go on the way to Assyria, to drink the waters of the\nRiver?",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:18 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["i.e., the Euphrates River"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 2:19"},"“Your own wickedness will correct you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your backsliding will rebuke you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Know therefore and see that it is an evil and bitter thing, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that you have forsaken Allah your LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and that my fear is not in you,” says the Lord, the LORD of Armies.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 2:20"},"“For long ago I broke off your yoke, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and burst your bonds. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You said, ‘I will not serve;’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for on every high hill and under every green tree you bowed yourself,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["playing the prostitute. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 2:21"},"Yet I had planted you a noble vine, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a pure and faithful seed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["How then have you turned into the degenerate branches of a foreign vine to me?\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 2:22"},"For though you wash yourself with lye, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and use much soap, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["yet your iniquity is marked before me,” says the Lord ALLAH.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 2:23"},"“How can you say, ‘I am not defiled. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have not gone after the Baals’? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["See your way in the valley. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Know what you have done. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You are a swift dromedary traversing her ways, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 2:24"},"a wild donkey used to the wilderness, that sniffs the wind in her craving.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["When she is in heat, who can turn her away? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["All those who seek her will not weary themselves. In her month, they will find her.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 2:25"},"“Keep your feet from being bare, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your throat from thirst. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["But you said, ‘It is in vain. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["No, for I have loved strangers, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will go after them.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 2:26"},"As the thief is ashamed when he is found, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so the house of Israel is ashamed: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they, their kings, their princes, their priests, and their prophets,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 2:27"},"who tell wood, ‘You are my father,’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and a stone, ‘You have given birth to me,’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for they have turned their back to me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and not their face; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but in the time of their trouble they will say, ‘Arise, and save us!’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 2:28"},"“But where are your gods that you have made for yourselves?\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Let them arise, if they can save you in the time of your trouble;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for you have as many gods as you have towns, O Judah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JER 2:29"},"“Why will you contend with me? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You all have transgressed against me,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JER 2:30"},"“I have struck your children in vain. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They received no correction. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Your own sword has devoured your prophets, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like a destroying lion. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JER 2:31"},"Generation, consider the LORD’s word. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Have I been a wilderness to Israel? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Or a land of thick darkness? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Why do my people say, ‘We have broken loose. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["We will come to you no more?’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JER 2:32"},"“Can a virgin forget her ornaments, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or a bride her attire? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Yet my people have forgotten me for days without number. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JER 2:33"},"How well you prepare your way to seek love! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Therefore you have even taught the wicked women your ways. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JER 2:34"},"Also the blood of the souls of the innocent poor is found in your skirts.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You didn’t find them breaking in; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but it is because of all these things. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JER 2:35"},"“Yet you said, ‘I am innocent. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Surely his anger has turned away from me.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, I will judge you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because you say, ‘I have not sinned.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JER 2:36"},"Why do you go about so much to change your ways? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You will be ashamed of Egypt also, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as you were ashamed of Assyria. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JER 2:37"},"You will also leave that place with your hands on your head;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the LORD has rejected those in whom you trust, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and you won’t prosper with them. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3","sid":"JER 3"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 3:1"},"“They say, ‘If a man puts away his wife, and she goes from him, and becomes another man’s, should he return to her again?’\nWouldn’t that land be greatly polluted? But you have played the prostitute with many lovers; yet return again to me,” says the\nLORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 3:2"},"“Lift up your eyes to the bare heights, and see! Where have you not been lain with? You have sat waiting for them by the\nroad, as an Arabian in the wilderness. You have polluted the land with your prostitution and with your wickedness.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 3:3"},"Therefore the showers have been withheld and there has been no latter rain; yet you have had a prostitute’s forehead and\nyou refused to be ashamed. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 3:4"},"Will you not from this time cry to me, ‘My Father, you are the guide of my youth?’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 3:5"},"“‘Will he retain his anger forever? Will he keep it to the end?’ Behold, you have spoken and have done evil things, and\nhave had your way.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 3:6"},"Moreover, the LORD said to me in the days of Josiah the king, “Have you seen that which backsliding Israel has done? She\nhas gone up on every high mountain and under every green tree, and has played the prostitute there.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 3:7"},"I said after she had done all these things, ‘She will return to me;’ but she didn’t return; and her treacherous sister\nJudah saw it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 3:8"},"I saw when, for this very cause, that backsliding Israel had committed adultery, I had put her away and given her a\ncertificate of divorce, yet treacherous Judah, her sister, had no fear; but she also went and played the prostitute.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 3:9"},"Because she took her prostitution lightly, the land was polluted, and she committed adultery with stones and with wood.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 3:10"},"Yet for all this her treacherous sister, Judah, has not returned to me with her whole heart, but only in pretence,” says\nthe LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 3:11"},"The LORD said to me, “Backsliding Israel has shown herself more righteous than treacherous Judah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 3:12"},"Go, and proclaim these words towards the north, and say, ‘Return, you backsliding Israel,’ says the LORD; ‘I will not\nlook in anger on you; for I am merciful,’ says the LORD. ‘I will not keep anger forever.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 3:13"},"Only acknowledge your iniquity, that you have transgressed against Allah your LORD, and have scattered your ways to the\nstrangers under every green tree, and you have not obeyed my voice,’ says the LORD.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 3:14"},"“Return, backsliding children,” says the LORD; “for I am a husband to you. I will take one of you from a city, and two\nfrom a family, and I will bring you to Zion. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 3:15"},"I will give you shepherds according to my heart, who will feed you with knowledge and understanding.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 3:16"},"It will come to pass, when you are multiplied and increased in the land, in those days,” says the LORD, “they will no\nlonger say, ‘the ark of the LORD’s covenant!’ It will not come to mind. They won’t remember it. They won’t miss it, nor will\nanother be made. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 3:17"},"At that time they will call Jerusalem ‘The LORD’s Throne;’ and all the nations will be gathered to it, to the LORD’s\nname, to Jerusalem. They will no longer walk after the stubbornness of their evil heart.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 3:18"},"In those days the house of Judah will walk with the house of Israel, and they will come together out of the land of the\nnorth to the land that I gave for an inheritance to your fathers.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 3:19"},"“But I said, ‘How I desire to put you amongst the children, and give you a pleasant land, a goodly heritage of the armies\nof the nations!’ and I said, ‘You shall call me “My Father”, and shall not turn away from following me.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 3:20"},"“Surely as a wife treacherously departs from her husband, so you have dealt treacherously with me, house of Israel,” says\nthe LORD. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 3:21"},"A voice is heard on the bare heights, the weeping and the petitions of the children of Israel; because they have\nperverted their way, they have forgotten the LORD their Allah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 3:22"},"Return, you backsliding children, and I will heal your backsliding.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Behold, we have come to you; for you are the LORD our Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 3:23"},"Truly in vain is help from the hills, the tumult on the mountains. Truly the salvation of Israel is in the LORD our\nAllah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 3:24"},"But the shameful thing has devoured the labour of our fathers from our youth, their flocks and their herds, their sons\nand their daughters. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 3:25"},"Let us lie down in our shame, and let our confusion cover us; for we have sinned against the LORD our Allah, we and our\nfathers, from our youth even to this day. We have not obeyed the LORD our Allah’s voice.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4","sid":"JER 4"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 4:1"},"“If you will return, Israel,” says the LORD, “if you will return to me, and if you will put away your abominations out of\nmy sight; then you will not be removed; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 4:2"},"and you will swear, ‘As the LORD lives,’ in truth, in justice, and in righteousness. The nations will bless themselves in\nhim, and they will glory in him.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 4:3"},"For the LORD says to the men of Judah and to Jerusalem, “Break up your fallow ground, and don’t sow amongst thorns.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 4:4"},"Circumcise yourselves to the LORD, and take away the foreskins of your heart, you men of Judah and inhabitants of\nJerusalem; lest my wrath go out like fire, and burn so that no one can quench it, because of the evil of your doings.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 4:5"},"Declare in Judah, and publish in Jerusalem; and say, ‘Blow the trumpet in the land!’ Cry aloud and say, ‘Assemble\nyourselves! Let’s go into the fortified cities!’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 4:6"},"Set up a standard towards Zion. Flee for safety! Don’t wait; for I will bring evil from the north, and a great\ndestruction.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 4:7"},"A lion has gone up from his thicket, and a destroyer of nations. He is on his way. He has gone out from his place, to make\nyour land desolate, that your cities be laid waste, without inhabitant.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 4:8"},"For this, clothe yourself with sackcloth, lament and wail; for the fierce anger of the LORD hasn’t turned back from us.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 4:9"},"“It will happen at that day,” says the LORD, “that the heart of the king will perish, along with the heart of the princes.\nThe priests will be astonished, and the prophets will wonder.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 4:10"},"Then I said, “Ah, Lord ALLAH! Surely you have greatly deceived this people and Jerusalem, saying, ‘You will have peace;’\nwhereas the sword reaches to the heart.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 4:11"},"At that time it will be said to this people and to Jerusalem, “A hot wind from the bare heights in the wilderness towards\nthe daughter of my people, not to winnow, nor to cleanse; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 4:12"},"a full wind from these will come for me. Now I will also utter judgements against them.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 4:13"},"Behold, he will come up as clouds, and his chariots will be as the whirlwind. His horses are swifter than eagles. Woe to\nus! For we are ruined. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 4:14"},"Jerusalem, wash your heart from wickedness, that you may be saved. How long will your evil thoughts lodge within you?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 4:15"},"For a voice declares from Dan, and publishes evil from the hills of Ephraim:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 4:16"},"“Tell the nations; behold, publish against Jerusalem, ‘Watchers come from a far country, and raise their voice against\nthe cities of Judah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 4:17"},"As keepers of a field, they are against her all around, because she has been rebellious against me,’” says the LORD.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 4:18"},"“Your way and your doings have brought these things to you. This is your wickedness; for it is bitter, for it reaches to\nyour heart.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 4:19"},"My anguish, my anguish! I am pained at my very heart! My heart trembles within me. I can’t hold my peace, because you\nhave heard, O my soul, the sound of the trumpet, the alarm of war.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 4:20"},"Destruction on destruction is decreed, for the whole land is laid waste. Suddenly my tents are destroyed, and my curtains\ngone in a moment. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 4:21"},"How long will I see the standard and hear the sound of the trumpet?\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 4:22"},"“For my people are foolish. They don’t know me. They are foolish children, and they have no understanding. They are\nskilful in doing evil, but they don’t know how to do good.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 4:23"},"I saw the earth, and, behold, it was waste and void, and the heavens, and they had no light.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 4:24"},"I saw the mountains, and behold, they trembled, and all the hills moved back and forth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 4:25"},"I saw, and behold, there was no man, and all the birds of the sky had fled.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 4:26"},"I saw, and behold, the fruitful field was a wilderness, and all its cities were broken down at the presence of the LORD,\nbefore his fierce anger. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 4:27"},"For the LORD says, “The whole land will be a desolation; yet I will not make a full end.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 4:28"},"For this the earth will mourn, and the heavens above be black; because I have spoken it. I have planned it, and I have\nnot repented, neither will I turn back from it.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JER 4:29"},"Every city flees for the noise of the horsemen and archers. They go into the thickets, and climb up on the rocks. Every\ncity is forsaken, and not a man dwells therein. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JER 4:30"},"You, when you are made desolate, what will you do? Though you clothe yourself with scarlet, though you deck yourself with\nornaments of gold, though you enlarge your eyes with makeup, you make yourself beautiful in vain. Your lovers despise you. They\nseek your life. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JER 4:31"},"For I have heard a voice as of a woman in travail, the anguish as of her who gives birth to her first child, the voice of\nthe daughter of Zion, who gasps for breath, who spreads her hands, saying, “Woe is me now! For my soul faints before the\nmurderers.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5","sid":"JER 5"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 5:1"},"“Run back and forth through the streets of Jerusalem, and see now, and know, and seek in its wide places, if you can find\na man, if there is anyone who does justly, who seeks truth, then I will pardon her.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 5:2"},"Though they say, ‘As the LORD lives,’ surely they swear falsely.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 5:3"},"O LORD, don’t your eyes look on truth? You have stricken them, but they were not grieved. You have consumed them, but they\nhave refused to receive correction. They have made their faces harder than a rock. They have refused to return.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 5:4"},"Then I said, “Surely these are poor. They are foolish; for they don’t know the the LORD’s way, nor the law of their Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 5:5"},"I will go to the great men and will speak to them, for they know the way of the LORD, and the law of their Allah.” But\nthese with one accord have broken the yoke, and burst the bonds.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 5:6"},"Therefore a lion out of the forest will kill them. A wolf of the evenings will destroy them. A leopard will watch against\ntheir cities. Everyone who goes out there will be torn in pieces, because their transgressions are many and their backsliding\nhas increased. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 5:7"},"“How can I pardon you? Your children have forsaken me, and sworn by what are no gods. When I had fed them to the full,\nthey committed adultery, and assembled themselves in troops at the prostitutes’ houses.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 5:8"},"They were as fed horses roaming at large. Everyone neighed after his neighbour’s wife.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 5:9"},"Shouldn’t I punish them for these things?” says the LORD. “Shouldn’t my soul be avenged on such a nation as this?\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 5:10"},"“Go up on her walls, and destroy; but don’t make a full end. Take away her branches, for they are not the LORD’s.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 5:11"},"For the house of Israel and the house of Judah have dealt very treacherously against me,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 5:12"},"They have denied the LORD, and said, “It is not he. Evil will won’t come on us. We won’t see sword or famine.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 5:13"},"The prophets will become wind, and the word is not in them. Thus it will be done to them.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 5:14"},"Therefore the LORD, Allah of Armies says, “Because you speak this word, behold, I will make my words in your mouth fire,\nand this people wood, and it will devour them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 5:15"},"Behold, I will bring a nation on you from far away, house of Israel,” says the LORD. “It is a mighty nation. It is an\nancient nation, a nation whose language you don’t know and don’t understand what they say.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 5:16"},"Their quiver is an open tomb. They are all mighty men. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 5:17"},"They will eat up your harvest and your bread, which your sons and your daughters should eat. They will eat up your flocks\nand your herds. They will eat up your vines and your fig trees. They will beat down your fortified cities in which you trust\nwith the sword. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 5:18"},"“But even in those days,” says the LORD, “I will not make a full end of you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 5:19"},"It will happen, when you say, ‘Why has the LORD our Allah done all these things to us?’ Then you shall say to them, ‘Just\nas you have forsaken me, and served foreign gods in your land, so you will serve strangers in a land that is not yours.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 5:20"},"“Declare this in the house of Yaqub, and publish it in Judah, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 5:21"},"‘Hear this now, foolish people without understanding, who have eyes, and don’t see, who have ears, and don’t hear:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 5:22"},"Don’t you fear me?’ says the LORD ‘Won’t you tremble at my presence, who have placed the sand for the bound of the sea,\nby a perpetual decree, that it can’t pass it? Though its waves toss themselves, yet they can’t prevail. Though they roar, they\nstill can’t pass over it.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 5:23"},"“But this people has a revolting and a rebellious heart. They have revolted and gone.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 5:24"},"They don’t say in their heart, ‘Let’s now fear the LORD our Allah, who gives rain, both the former and the latter, in its\nseason; who preserves to us the appointed weeks of the harvest.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 5:25"},"“Your iniquities have turned away these things, and your sins have withheld good from you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 5:26"},"For amongst my people are found wicked men. They watch, as fowlers lie in wait. They set a trap. They catch men.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 5:27"},"As a cage is full of birds, so are their houses full of deceit. Therefore they have become great, and grew rich.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 5:28"},"They have grown fat. They shine; yes, they excel in deeds of wickedness. They don’t plead the cause, the cause of the\nfatherless, that they may prosper; and they don’t defend the rights of the needy.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JER 5:29"},"“Shouldn’t I punish for these things?” says the LORD. “Shouldn’t my soul be avenged on such a nation as this?\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JER 5:30"},"“An astonishing and horrible thing has happened in the land.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JER 5:31"},"The prophets prophesy falsely, and the priests rule by their own authority; and my people love to have it so. What will\nyou do in the end of it? \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"6","sid":"JER 6"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 6:1"},"“Flee for safety, you children of Benjamin, out of the middle of Jerusalem! Blow the trumpet in Tekoa and raise up a\nsignal on Beth Haccherem, for evil looks out from the north with a great destruction.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 6:2"},"I will cut off the beautiful and delicate one, the daughter of Zion.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 6:3"},"Shepherds with their flocks will come to her. They will pitch their tents against her all around. They will feed everyone\nin his place.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 6:4"},"“Prepare war against her! Arise! Let’s go up at noon. Woe to us! For the day declines, for the shadows of the evening are\nstretched out. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 6:5"},"Arise! Let’s go up by night, and let’s destroy her palaces.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 6:6"},"For the LORD of Armies said, “Cut down trees, and cast up a mound against Jerusalem. This is the city to be visited. She\nis wholly oppression within herself. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 6:7"},"As a well produces its waters, so she produces her wickedness. Violence and destruction is heard in her. Sickness and\nwounds are continually before me. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 6:8"},"Be instructed, Jerusalem, lest my soul be alienated from you; lest I make you a desolation, an uninhabited land.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 6:9"},"The LORD of Armies says, “They will thoroughly glean the remnant of Israel like a vine. Turn again your hand as a grape\ngatherer into the baskets.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 6:10"},"To whom should I speak and testify, that they may hear? Behold, their ear is uncircumcised, and they can’t listen.\nBehold, the LORD’s word has become a reproach to them. They have no delight in it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 6:11"},"Therefore I am full of the LORD’s wrath. I am weary with holding it in.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Pour it out on the children in the street, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and on the assembly of young men together; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for even the husband with the wife will be taken, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the aged with him who is full of days. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 6:12"},"Their houses will be turned to others, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["their fields and their wives together; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for I will stretch out my hand on the inhabitants of the land, says the LORD.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 6:13"},"“For from their least even to their greatest, everyone is given to covetousness.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["From the prophet even to the priest, everyone deals falsely.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 6:14"},"They have healed also the hurt of my people superficially,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["saying, ‘Peace, peace!’ when there is no peace. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 6:15"},"Were they ashamed when they had committed abomination? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["No, they were not at all ashamed, neither could they blush. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Therefore they will fall amongst those who fall. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["When I visit them, they will be cast down,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 6:16"},"The LORD says, “Stand in the ways and see, and ask for the old paths, ‘Where is the good way?’ and walk in it, and you\nwill find rest for your souls. But they said, ‘We will not walk in it.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 6:17"},"I set watchmen over you, saying, ‘Listen to the sound of the trumpet!’ But they said, ‘We will not listen!’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 6:18"},"Therefore hear, you nations, and know, congregation, what is amongst them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 6:19"},"Hear, earth! Behold, I will bring evil on this people, even the fruit of their thoughts, because they have not listened\nto my words; and as for my law, they have rejected it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 6:20"},"To what purpose does frankincense from Sheba come to me, and the sweet cane from a far country? Your burnt offerings are\nnot acceptable, and your sacrifices are not pleasing to me.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 6:21"},"Therefore The LORD says, “Behold, I will lay stumbling blocks before this people. The fathers and the sons together will\nstumble against them. The neighbour and his friend will perish.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 6:22"},"The LORD says, “Behold, a people comes from the north country. A great nation will be stirred up from the uttermost parts\nof the earth. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 6:23"},"They take hold of bow and spear. They are cruel, and have no mercy. Their voice roars like the sea, and they ride on\nhorses, everyone set in array, as a man to the battle, against you, daughter of Zion.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 6:24"},"We have heard its report. Our hands become feeble. Anguish has taken hold of us, and pains as of a woman in labour.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 6:25"},"Don’t go out into the field, nor walk by the way; for the sword of the enemy and terror are on every side.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 6:26"},"Daughter of my people, clothe yourself with sackcloth, and wallow in ashes! Mourn, as for an only son, most bitter\nlamentation, for the destroyer will suddenly come on us. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 6:27"},"“I have made you a tester of metals and a fortress amongst my people, that you may know and try their way.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 6:28"},"They are all grievous rebels, going around to slander. They are bronze and iron. All of them deal corruptly.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JER 6:29"},"The bellows blow fiercely. The lead is consumed in the fire. In vain they go on refining, for the wicked are not plucked\naway. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JER 6:30"},"Men will call them rejected silver, because the LORD has rejected them.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"7","sid":"JER 7"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 7:1"},"The word that came to Jeremiah from the LORD, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 7:2"},"“Stand in the gate of the LORD’s house, and proclaim this word there, and say, ‘Hear the LORD’s word, all you of Judah,\nwho enter in at these gates to worship the LORD.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 7:3"},"The LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel says, “Amend your ways and your doings, and I will cause you to dwell in this place.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 7:4"},"Don’t trust in lying words, saying, ‘The LORD’s temple, the LORD’s temple, the LORD’s temple, are these.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 7:5"},"For if you thoroughly amend your ways and your doings, if you thoroughly execute justice between a man and his neighbour;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 7:6"},"if you don’t oppress the foreigner, the fatherless, and the widow, and don’t shed innocent blood in this place, and don’t\nwalk after other gods to your own hurt; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 7:7"},"then I will cause you to dwell in this place, in the land that I gave to your fathers, from of old even forever more.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 7:8"},"Behold, you trust in lying words that can’t profit. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 7:9"},"Will you steal, murder, commit adultery, swear falsely, burn incense to Baal, and walk after other gods that you have not\nknown, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 7:10"},"then come and stand before me in this house, which is called by my name, and say, ‘We are delivered;’ that you may do all\nthese abominations? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 7:11"},"Has this house, which is called by my name, become a den of robbers in your eyes? Behold, I myself have seen it,” says\nthe LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 7:12"},"“But go now to my place which was in Shiloh, where I caused my name to dwell at the first, and see what I did to it for\nthe wickedness of my people Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 7:13"},"Now, because you have done all these works,” says the LORD, “and I spoke to you, rising up early and speaking, but you\ndidn’t hear; and I called you, but you didn’t answer; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 7:14"},"therefore I will do to the house which is called by my name, in which you trust, and to the place which I gave to you and\nto your fathers, as I did to Shiloh. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 7:15"},"I will cast you out of my sight, as I have cast out all your brothers, even the whole\noffspring",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, seed"]}],"caller":"+"}," of Ephraim. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 7:16"},"“Therefore don’t pray for this people. Don’t lift up a cry or prayer for them or make intercession to me; for I will not\nhear you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 7:17"},"Don’t you see what they do in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 7:18"},"The children gather wood, and the fathers kindle the fire, and the women knead the dough, to make cakes to the queen of\nthe sky, and to pour out drink offerings to other gods, that they may provoke me to anger.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 7:19"},"Do they provoke me to anger?” says the LORD. “Don’t they provoke themselves, to the confusion of their own faces?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 7:20"},"Therefore the Lord ALLAH says: “Behold, my anger and my wrath will be poured out on this place, on man, on animal, on the\ntrees of the field, and on the fruit of the ground; and it will burn and will not be quenched.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 7:21"},"the LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel says: “Add your burnt offerings to your sacrifices and eat meat.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 7:22"},"For I didn’t speak to your fathers or command them in the day that I brought them out of the land of Egypt concerning\nburnt offerings or sacrifices; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 7:23"},"but this thing I commanded them, saying, ‘Listen to my voice, and I will be your Allah, and you shall be my people; and\nwalk in all the way that I command you, that it may be well with you.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 7:24"},"But they didn’t listen or turn their ear, but walked in their own counsels and in the stubbornness of their evil heart,\nand went backward, and not forward. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 7:25"},"Since the day that your fathers came out of the land of Egypt to this day, I have sent to you all my servants the\nprophets, daily rising up early and sending them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 7:26"},"Yet they didn’t listen to me or incline their ear, but made their neck stiff. They did worse than their fathers.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 7:27"},"“You shall speak all these words to them, but they will not listen to you. You shall also call to them, but they will not\nanswer you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 7:28"},"You shall tell them, ‘This is the nation that has not listened to the LORD their Allah’s voice, nor received instruction.\nTruth has perished, and is cut off from their mouth.’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JER 7:29"},"Cut off your hair, and throw it away, and take up a lamentation on the bare heights; for the LORD has rejected and\nforsaken the generation of his wrath. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JER 7:30"},"“For the children of Judah have done that which is evil in my sight,” says the LORD. “They have set their abominations in\nthe house which is called by my name, to defile it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JER 7:31"},"They have built the high places of Topheth, which is in the valley of the son of Hinnom, to burn their sons and their\ndaughters in the fire; which I didn’t command, nor did it come into my mind.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JER 7:32"},"Therefore behold, the days come”, says the LORD, “that it will no more be called ‘Topheth’ or ‘The valley of the son of\nHinnom’, but ‘The valley of Slaughter’; for they will bury in Topheth until there is no place to bury.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JER 7:33"},"The dead bodies of this people will be food for the birds of the sky, and for the animals of the earth. No one will\nfrighten them away. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JER 7:34"},"Then I will cause to cease from the cities of Judah, and from the streets of Jerusalem, the voice of mirth and the voice\nof gladness, the voice of the bridegroom and the voice of the bride; for the land will become a waste.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"8","sid":"JER 8"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 8:1"},"“At that time,” says the LORD, “they will bring out the bones of the kings of Judah, the bones of his princes, the bones\nof the priests, the bones of the prophets, and the bones of the inhabitants of Jerusalem, out of their graves.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 8:2"},"They will spread them before the sun, the moon, and all the army of the sky, which they have loved, which they have\nserved, after which they have walked, which they have sought, and which they have worshipped. They will not be gathered or be\nburied. They will be for dung on the surface of the earth. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 8:3"},"Death will be chosen rather than life by all the residue that remain of this evil family, that remain in all the places\nwhere I have driven them,” says the LORD of Armies. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 8:4"},"“Moreover you shall tell them, ‘The LORD says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“‘Do men fall, and not rise up again? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Does one turn away, and not return? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 8:5"},"Why then have the people of Jerusalem fallen back by a perpetual backsliding?\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They cling to deceit. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They refuse to return. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 8:6"},"I listened and heard, but they didn’t say what is right. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["No one repents of his wickedness, saying, “What have I done?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Everyone turns to his course, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as a horse that rushes headlong in the battle. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 8:7"},"Yes, the stork in the sky knows her appointed times. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The turtledove, the swallow, and the crane observe the time of their coming;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but my people don’t know the LORD’s law. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 8:8"},"“‘How do you say, “We are wise, and the LORD’s law is with us?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["But, behold, the false pen of the scribes has worked falsely.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 8:9"},"The wise men are disappointed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They are dismayed and trapped. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Behold, they have rejected the LORD’s word. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["What kind of wisdom is in them? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 8:10"},"Therefore I will give their wives to others, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their fields to those who will possess them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For everyone from the least even to the greatest is given to covetousness;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the prophet even to the priest everyone deals falsely. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 8:11"},"They have healed the hurt of the daughter of my people slightly, saying,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Peace, peace,” when there is no peace. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 8:12"},"Were they ashamed when they had committed abomination? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["No, they were not at all ashamed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They couldn’t blush. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Therefore they will fall amongst those who fall. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["In the time of their visitation they will be cast down, says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 8:13"},"“‘I will utterly consume them, says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["No grapes will be on the vine, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["no figs on the fig tree, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the leaf will fade. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The things that I have given them \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["will pass away from them.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 8:14"},"“Why do we sit still? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Assemble yourselves! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Let’s enter into the fortified cities, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and let’s be silent there; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for the LORD our Allah has put us to silence, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and given us poisoned water to drink, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because we have sinned against the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 8:15"},"We looked for peace, but no good came; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and for a time of healing, and behold, dismay! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 8:16"},"The snorting of his horses is heard from Dan. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The whole land trembles at the sound of the neighing of his strong ones;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for they have come, and have devoured the land and all that is in it;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the city and those who dwell therein.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 8:17"},"“For, behold, I will send serpents, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["adders amongst you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["which will not be charmed; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will bite you,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 8:18"},"Oh that I could comfort myself against sorrow! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["My heart is faint within me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 8:19"},"Behold, the voice of the cry of the daughter of my people from a land that is very far off:\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Isn’t the LORD in Zion? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Isn’t her King in her?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Why have they provoked me to anger with their engraved images,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and with foreign idols?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 8:20"},"“The harvest is past. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The summer has ended, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and we are not saved.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 8:21"},"For the hurt of the daughter of my people, I am hurt. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I mourn. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Dismay has taken hold of me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 8:22"},"Is there no balm in Gilead? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Is there no physician there? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Why then isn’t the health of the daughter of my people recovered?\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"9","sid":"JER 9"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 9:1"},"Oh that my head were waters, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and my eyes a spring of tears, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["that I might weep day and night \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the slain of the daughter of my people! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 9:2"},"Oh that I had in the wilderness \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a lodging place of wayfaring men; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["that I might leave my people, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and go from them! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For they are all adulterers, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["an assembly of treacherous men. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 9:3"},"“They bend their tongue, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as their bow, for falsehood. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They have grown strong in the land, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but not for truth; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for they proceed from evil to evil, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they don’t know me,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 9:4"},"“Everyone beware of his neighbour, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and don’t trust in any brother; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for every brother will utterly supplant, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and every neighbour will go around like a slanderer. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 9:5"},"Friends deceive each other, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will not speak the truth. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They have taught their tongue to speak lies. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They weary themselves commiting iniquity. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 9:6"},"Your habitation is in the middle of deceit. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Through deceit, they refuse to know me,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 9:7"},"Therefore the LORD of Armies says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, I will melt them and test them; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for how should I deal with the daughter of my people? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 9:8"},"Their tongue is a deadly arrow. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It speaks deceit. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["One speaks peaceably to his neighbour with his mouth, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but in his heart, he waits to ambush him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 9:9"},"Shouldn’t I punish them for these things?” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Shouldn’t my soul be avenged on a nation such as this? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 9:10"},"I will weep and wail for the mountains, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and lament for the pastures of the wilderness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["because they are burnt up, so that no one passes through; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Men can’t hear the voice of the livestock. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Both the birds of the sky and the animals have fled. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They are gone. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 9:11"},"“I will make Jerusalem heaps, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a dwelling place of jackals. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will make the cities of Judah a desolation, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["without inhabitant.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 9:12"},"Who is wise enough to understand this? Who is he to whom the mouth of the LORD has spoken, that he may declare it? Why\nhas the land perished and burnt up like a wilderness, so that no one passes through?\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 9:13"},"The LORD says, “Because they have forsaken my law which I set before them, and have not obeyed my voice, neither walked\ntherein, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 9:14"},"but have walked after the stubbornness of their own heart, and after the Baals, which their fathers taught them.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 9:15"},"Therefore the LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says, “Behold, I will feed them, even this people, with wormwood, and give\nthem poisoned water to drink. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 9:16"},"I will scatter them also amongst the nations, whom neither they nor their fathers have known; and I will send the sword\nafter them, until I have consumed them.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 9:17"},"The LORD of Armies says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Consider, and call for the mourning women, that they may come;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and send for the skilful women, that they may come. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 9:18"},"Let them make haste, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and take up a wailing for us, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["that our eyes may run down with tears, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and our eyelids gush out with waters. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 9:19"},"For a voice of wailing is heard out of Zion, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘How we are ruined! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["We are greatly confounded, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because we have forsaken the land, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because they have cast down our dwellings.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 9:20"},"Yet hear the LORD’s word, you women. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Let your ear receive the word of his mouth. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Teach your daughters wailing, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and everyone teach her neighbour a lamentation. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 9:21"},"For death has come up into our windows. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It has entered into our palaces \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["to cut off the children from outside, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the young men from the streets. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 9:22"},"Speak, “The LORD says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“‘The dead bodies of men will fall as dung on the open field,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and as the handful after the harvester; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and no one will gather them.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 9:23"},"The LORD says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Don’t let the wise man glory in his wisdom. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Don’t let the mighty man glory in his might. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Don’t let the rich man glory in his riches. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 9:24"},"But let him who glories glory in this, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that he has understanding, and knows me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["that I am the LORD who exercises loving kindness, justice, and righteousness, in the earth;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for I delight in these things,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 9:25"},"“Behold, the days come,” says the LORD, “that I will punish all those who are circumcised only in their flesh:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 9:26"},"Egypt, Judah, Edom, the children of Ammon, Moab, and all who have the corners of their hair cut off, who dwell in the\nwilderness; for all the nations are uncircumcised, and all the house of Israel are uncircumcised in heart.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"10","sid":"JER 10"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 10:1"},"Hear the word which the LORD speaks to you, house of Israel!\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 10:2"},"The LORD says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Don’t learn the way of the nations, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and don’t be dismayed at the signs of the sky; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the nations are dismayed at them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 10:3"},"For the customs of the peoples are vanity; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for one cuts a tree out of the forest, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the work of the hands of the workman with the axe. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 10:4"},"They deck it with silver and with gold. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They fasten it with nails and with hammers, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so that it can’t move. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 10:5"},"They are like a palm tree, of turned work, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and don’t speak. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They must be carried, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because they can’t move. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Don’t be afraid of them; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for they can’t do evil, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["neither is it in them to do good.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 10:6"},"There is no one like you, LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You are great, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your name is great in might. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 10:7"},"Who shouldn’t fear you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["King of the nations? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["For it belongs to you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Because amongst all the wise men of the nations, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and in all their royal estate, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["there is no one like you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 10:8"},"But they are together brutish and foolish, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["instructed by idols! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It is just wood. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 10:9"},"There is silver beaten into plates, which is brought from Tarshish,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and gold from Uphaz, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the work of the engraver and of the hands of the goldsmith. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Their clothing is blue and purple. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They are all the work of skilful men. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 10:10"},"But the LORD is the true Allah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He is the living Allah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and an everlasting King. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["At his wrath, the earth trembles. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The nations aren’t able to withstand his indignation. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 10:11"},"“You shall say this to them: ‘The gods that have not made the heavens and the earth will perish from the earth, and from\nunder the heavens.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 10:12"},"Allah has made the earth by his power. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He has established the world by his wisdom, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and by his understanding has he stretched out the heavens. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 10:13"},"When he utters his voice, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the waters in the heavens roar, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and he causes the vapours to ascend from the ends of the earth.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He makes lightnings for the rain, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and brings the wind out of his treasuries. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 10:14"},"Every man has become brutish and without knowledge. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Every goldsmith is disappointed by his engraved image; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for his molten image is falsehood, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and there is no breath in them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 10:15"},"They are vanity, a work of delusion. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["In the time of their visitation they will perish. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 10:16"},"The portion of Yaqub is not like these; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for he is the maker of all things; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and Israel is the tribe of his inheritance: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the LORD of Armies is his name. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 10:17"},"Gather up your wares out of the land, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you who live under siege. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 10:18"},"For the LORD says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Behold, I will sling out the inhabitants of the land at this time,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will distress them, that they may feel it.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 10:19"},"Woe is me because of my injury! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["My wound is serious; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["but I said, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Truly this is my grief, and I must bear it.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 10:20"},"My tent has been destroyed, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all my cords are broken. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["My children have gone away from me, and they are no more. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["There is no one to spread my tent any more, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to set up my curtains. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 10:21"},"For the shepherds have become brutish, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and have not enquired of the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Therefore they have not prospered, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all their flocks have scattered. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 10:22"},"The voice of news, behold, it comes, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and a great commotion out of the north country, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["to make the cities of Judah a desolation, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a dwelling place of jackals. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 10:23"},"LORD, I know that the way of man is not in himself. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It is not in man who walks to direct his steps. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 10:24"},"LORD, correct me, but gently; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["not in your anger, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["lest you reduce me to nothing. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 10:25"},"Pour out your wrath on the nations that don’t know you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and on the families that don’t call on your name; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for they have devoured Yaqub. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Yes, they have devoured him, consumed him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and have laid waste his habitation. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"11","sid":"JER 11"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 11:1"},"The word that came to Jeremiah from the LORD, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 11:2"},"“Hear the words of this covenant, and speak to the men of Judah, and to the inhabitants of Jerusalem;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 11:3"},"and say to them, the LORD, Allah of Israel says: ‘Cursed is the man who doesn’t hear the words of this covenant,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 11:4"},"which I commanded your fathers in the day that I brought them out of the land of Egypt, out of the iron furnace,’ saying,\n‘Obey my voice, and do them, according to all which I command you; so you shall be my people, and I will be your Allah;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 11:5"},"that I may establish the oath which I swore to your fathers, to give them a land flowing with milk and honey,’ as it is\ntoday.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then answered I, and said, “Amen, LORD.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 11:6"},"The LORD said to me, “Proclaim all these words in the cities of Judah, and in the streets of Jerusalem, saying, ‘Hear the\nwords of this covenant, and do them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 11:7"},"For I earnestly protested to your fathers in the day that I brought them up out of the land of Egypt, even to this day,\nrising early and protesting, saying, “Obey my voice.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 11:8"},"Yet they didn’t obey, nor turn their ear, but everyone walked in the stubbornness of their evil heart. Therefore I brought\non them all the words of this covenant, which I commanded them to do, but they didn’t do them.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 11:9"},"The LORD said to me, “A conspiracy is found amongst the men of Judah, and amongst the inhabitants of Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 11:10"},"They have turned back to the iniquities of their forefathers, who refused to hear my words. They have gone after other\ngods to serve them. The house of Israel and the house of Judah have broken my covenant which I made with their fathers.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 11:11"},"Therefore the LORD says, ‘Behold, I will bring evil on them, which they will not be able to escape; and they will cry to\nme, but I will not listen to them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 11:12"},"Then the cities of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem will go and cry to the gods to which they offer incense, but\nthey will not save them at all in the time of their trouble. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 11:13"},"For according to the number of your cities are your gods, Judah; and according to the number of the streets of Jerusalem\nhave you set up altars to the shameful thing, even altars to burn incense to Baal.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 11:14"},"“Therefore don’t pray for this people. Don’t lift up cry or prayer for them; for I will not hear them in the time that\nthey cry to me because of their trouble. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 11:15"},"What has my beloved to do in my house, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["since she has behaved lewdly with many, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the holy flesh has passed from you? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["When you do evil, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["then you rejoice.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 11:16"},"The LORD called your name, “A green olive tree, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["beautiful with goodly fruit.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["With the noise of a great roar he has kindled fire on it, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and its branches are broken. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 11:17"},"For the LORD of Armies, who planted you, has pronounced evil against you, because of the evil of the house of Israel and\nof the house of Judah, which they have done to themselves in provoking me to anger by offering incense to Baal.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 11:18"},"The LORD gave me knowledge of it, and I knew it. Then you showed me their doings.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 11:19"},"But I was like a gentle lamb that is led to the slaughter. I didn’t know that they had devised plans against me, saying,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Let’s destroy the tree with its fruit, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and let’s cut him off from the land of the living, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that his name may be no more remembered.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 11:20"},"But, the LORD of Armies, who judges righteously, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who tests the heart and the mind, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will see your vengeance on them; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for to you I have revealed my cause. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 11:21"},"“Therefore the LORD says concerning the men of Anathoth, who seek your life, saying, ‘You shall not prophesy in the\nLORD’s name, that you not die by our hand;’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 11:22"},"therefore the LORD of Armies says, ‘Behold, I will punish them. The young men will die by the sword. Their sons and their\ndaughters will die by famine. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 11:23"},"There will be no remnant to them, for I will bring evil on the men of Anathoth, even the year of their visitation.’”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"12","sid":"JER 12"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 12:1"},"You are righteous, LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when I contend with you; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["yet I would like to reason the cause with you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Why does the way of the wicked prosper? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Why are they all at ease who deal very treacherously? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 12:2"},"You have planted them. Yes, they have taken root. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They grow. Yes, they produce fruit. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You are near in their mouth, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and far from their heart. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 12:3"},"But you, LORD, know me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You see me, and test my heart towards you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Pull them out like sheep for the slaughter, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and prepare them for the day of slaughter. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 12:4"},"How long will the land mourn, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the herbs of the whole country wither? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Because of the wickedness of those who dwell therein, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the animals and birds are consumed; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["because they said, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“He won’t see our latter end.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 12:5"},"“If you have run with the footmen, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they have wearied you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["then how can you contend with horses? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Though in a land of peace you are secure, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["yet how will you do in the pride of the Jordan? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 12:6"},"For even your brothers, and the house of your father, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even they have dealt treacherously with you! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Even they have cried aloud after you! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Don’t believe them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["though they speak beautiful words to you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 12:7"},"“I have forsaken my house. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have cast off my heritage. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have given the dearly beloved of my soul into the hand of her enemies.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 12:8"},"My heritage has become to me as a lion in the forest. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["She has uttered her voice against me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Therefore I have hated her. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 12:9"},"Is my heritage to me as a speckled bird of prey? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Are the birds of prey against her all around? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Go, assemble all the animals of the field. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Bring them to devour. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 12:10"},"Many shepherds have destroyed my vineyard. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They have trodden my portion under foot. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They have made my pleasant portion a desolate wilderness. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 12:11"},"They have made it a desolation. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It mourns to me, being desolate. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The whole land is made desolate, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because no one cares. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 12:12"},"Destroyers have come on all the bare heights in the wilderness;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the sword of the LORD devours from the one end of the land even to the other end of the land.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["No flesh has peace. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 12:13"},"They have sown wheat, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and have reaped thorns. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They have exhausted themselves, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and profit nothing. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You will be ashamed of your fruits, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because of the LORD’s fierce anger.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 12:14"},"The LORD says, “Concerning all my evil neighbours, who touch the inheritance which I have caused my people Israel to\ninherit: Behold, I will pluck them up from off their land, and will pluck up the house of Judah from amongst them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 12:15"},"It will happen, that after I have plucked them up, I will return and have compassion on them. I will bring them again,\nevery man to his heritage, and every man to his land. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 12:16"},"It will happen, if they will diligently learn the ways of my people, to swear by my name, ‘As the LORD lives;’ even as\nthey taught my people to swear by Baal; then they will be built up in the middle of my people.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 12:17"},"But if they will not hear, then I will pluck up that nation, plucking up and destroying it,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"13","sid":"JER 13"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 13:1"},"The LORD said to me, “Go, and buy yourself a linen belt, and put it on your waist, and don’t put it in water.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 13:2"},"So I bought a belt according to the LORD’s word, and put it on my waist.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 13:3"},"The LORD’s word came to me the second time, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 13:4"},"“Take the belt that you have bought, which is on your waist, and arise, go to the Euphrates, and hide it there in a cleft\nof the rock.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 13:5"},"So I went, and hid it by the Euphrates, as the LORD commanded me.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 13:6"},"After many days, the LORD said to me, “Arise, go to the Euphrates, and take the belt from there, which I commanded you to\nhide there.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 13:7"},"Then I went to the Euphrates, and dug, and took the belt from the place where I had hidden it; and behold, the belt was\nruined. It was profitable for nothing. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 13:8"},"Then the LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 13:9"},"“The LORD says, ‘In this way I, will ruin the pride of Judah, and the great pride of Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 13:10"},"This evil people, who refuse to hear my words, who walk in the stubbornness of their heart, and have gone after other\ngods to serve them, and to worship them, will even be as this belt, which is profitable for nothing.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 13:11"},"For as the belt clings to the waist of a man, so I have caused the whole house of Israel and the whole house of Judah to\ncling to me,’ says the LORD; ‘that they may be to me for a people, for a name, for praise, and for glory; but they would not\nhear.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 13:12"},"“Therefore you shall speak to them this word: ‘The LORD, Allah of Israel says, “Every container should be filled with\nwine.”’ They will tell you, ‘Do we not certainly know that every container should be filled with wine?’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 13:13"},"Then tell them, ‘The LORD says, “Behold, I will fill all the inhabitants of this land, even the kings who sit on Dawood’s\nthrone, the priests, the prophets, and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem, with drunkenness.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 13:14"},"I will dash them one against another, even the fathers and the sons together,” says the LORD: “I will not pity, spare, or\nhave compassion, that I should not destroy them.”’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 13:15"},"Hear, and give ear. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Don’t be proud, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the LORD has spoken. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 13:16"},"Give glory to Allah your LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["before he causes darkness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and before your feet stumble on the dark mountains, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and, while you look for light, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["he turns it into the shadow of death, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and makes it deep darkness. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 13:17"},"But if you will not hear it, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["my soul will weep in secret for your pride. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["My eye will weep bitterly, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and run down with tears, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because the LORD’s flock has been taken captive. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 13:18"},"Say to the king and to the queen mother, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Humble yourselves. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Sit down, for your crowns have come down, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even the crown of your glory. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 13:19"},"The cities of the South is shut up, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and there is no one to open them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Judah is carried away captive: all of it. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It is wholly carried away captive. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 13:20"},"Lift up your eyes, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and see those who come from the north. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Where is the flock that was given to you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your beautiful flock? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 13:21"},"What will you say, when he sets over you as head those whom you have yourself taught to be friends to you?\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Won’t sorrows take hold of you, as of a woman in travail? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 13:22"},"If you say in your heart, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Why have these things come on me?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Your skirts are uncovered because of the greatness of your iniquity,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your heels suffer violence. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 13:23"},"Can the Ethiopian change his skin, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or the leopard his spots? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Then may you also do good, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who are accustomed to do evil. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 13:24"},"“Therefore I will scatter them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as the stubble that passes away, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["by the wind of the wilderness. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 13:25"},"This is your lot, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the portion measured to you from me,” says the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“because you have forgotten me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and trusted in falsehood.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 13:26"},"Therefore I will also uncover your skirts on your face, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your shame will appear. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 13:27"},"I have seen your abominations, even your adulteries, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your neighing, the lewdness of your prostitution, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["on the hills in the field. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Woe to you, Jerusalem! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You will not be made clean. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["How long will it yet be?” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"14","sid":"JER 14"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 14:1"},"This is the LORD’s word that came to Jeremiah concerning the drought.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 14:2"},"“Judah mourns, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and its gates languish. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They sit in black on the ground. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The cry of Jerusalem goes up. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 14:3"},"Their nobles send their little ones to the waters. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They come to the cisterns, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and find no water. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They return with their vessels empty. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They are disappointed and confounded, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and cover their heads. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 14:4"},"Because of the ground which is cracked, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because no rain has been in the land, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["the ploughmen are disappointed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They cover their heads. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 14:5"},"Yes, the doe in the field also calves and forsakes her young,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because there is no grass. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 14:6"},"The wild donkeys stand on the bare heights. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They pant for air like jackals. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Their eyes fail, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because there is no vegetation. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 14:7"},"Though our iniquities testify against us, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["work for your name’s sake, LORD; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for our rebellions are many. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["We have sinned against you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 14:8"},"You hope of Israel, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["its Saviour in the time of trouble, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["why should you be as a foreigner in the land, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and as a wayfaring man who turns aside to stay for a night? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 14:9"},"Why should you be like a scared man, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as a mighty man who can’t save? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Yet you, LORD, are in the middle of us, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and we are called by your name. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Don’t leave us. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 14:10"},"The LORD says to this people, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Even so they have loved to wander. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They have not restrained their feet. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Therefore the LORD does not accept them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Now he will remember their iniquity, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and punish them for their sins.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 14:11"},"The LORD said to me, “Don’t pray for this people for their good.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 14:12"},"When they fast, I will not hear their cry; and when they offer burnt offering and meal offering, I will not accept them;\nbut I will consume them by the sword, by famine, and by pestilence.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 14:13"},"Then I said, “Ah, Lord ALLAH! Behold, the prophets tell them, ‘You will not see the sword, neither will you have famine;\nbut I will give you assured peace in this place.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 14:14"},"Then the LORD said to me, “The prophets prophesy lies in my name. I didn’t send them. I didn’t command them. I didn’t\nspeak to them. They prophesy to you a lying vision, divination, and a thing of nothing, and the deceit of their own heart.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 14:15"},"Therefore the LORD says concerning the prophets who prophesy in my name, but I didn’t send them, yet they say, ‘Sword and\nfamine will not be in this land.’ Those prophets will be consumed by sword and famine.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 14:16"},"The people to whom they prophesy will be cast out in the streets of Jerusalem because of the famine and the sword. They\nwill have no one to bury them—them, their wives, their sons, or their daughters, for I will pour their wickedness on them.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 14:17"},"“You shall say this word to them: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“‘Let my eyes run down with tears night and day, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and let them not cease; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for the virgin daughter of my people is broken with a great breach,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with a very grievous wound. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 14:18"},"If I go out into the field, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["then, behold, the slain with the sword! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["If I enter into the city, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["then, behold, those who are sick with famine! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For both the prophet and the priest go about in the land, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and have no knowledge.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 14:19"},"Have you utterly rejected Judah? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Has your soul loathed Zion? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Why have you struck us, and there is no healing for us? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["We looked for peace, but no good came; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and for a time of healing, and behold, dismay! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 14:20"},"We acknowledge, LORD, our wickedness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the iniquity of our fathers; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for we have sinned against you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 14:21"},"Do not abhor us, for your name’s sake. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Do not disgrace the throne of your glory. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Remember, and don’t break your covenant with us. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 14:22"},"Are there any amongst the vanities of the nations that can cause rain?\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Or can the sky give showers? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Aren’t you he, the LORD our Allah? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Therefore we will wait for you; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for you have made all these things. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"15","sid":"JER 15"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 15:1"},"Then the LORD said to me, “Though Musa and Samuel stood before me, yet my mind would not turn towards this people. Cast\nthem out of my sight, and let them go out! \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 15:2"},"It will happen, when they ask you, ‘Where shall we go out?’ then you shall tell them, ‘The LORD says:\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Such as are for death, to death; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["such as are for the sword, to the sword; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["such as are for the famine, to the famine; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and such as are for captivity, to captivity.”’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 15:3"},"“I will appoint over them four kinds,” says the LORD: “the sword to kill, the dogs to tear, the birds of the sky, and the\nanimals of the earth, to devour and to destroy. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 15:4"},"I will cause them to be tossed back and forth amongst all the kingdoms of the earth, because of Manasseh, the son of\nHezekiah, king of Judah, for that which he did in Jerusalem. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 15:5"},"For who will have pity on you, Jerusalem? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Who will mourn you? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Who will come to ask of your welfare? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 15:6"},"You have rejected me,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“You have gone backward. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Therefore I have stretched out my hand against you \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and destroyed you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I am weary of showing compassion. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 15:7"},"I have winnowed them with a fan in the gates of the land. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have bereaved them of children. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I have destroyed my people. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They didn’t return from their ways. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 15:8"},"Their widows are increased more than the sand of the seas. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have brought on them against the mother of the young men a destroyer at noonday.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have caused anguish and terrors to fall on her suddenly. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 15:9"},"She who has borne seven languishes. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["She has given up the spirit. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Her sun has gone down while it was yet day. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["She has been disappointed and confounded. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will deliver their residue to the sword before their enemies,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 15:10"},"Woe is me, my mother, that you have borne me, a man of strife,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and a man of contention to the whole earth! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I have not lent, neither have men lent to me; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["yet every one of them curses me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 15:11"},"The LORD said, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Most certainly I will strengthen you for good. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Most certainly I will cause the enemy to make supplication to you in the time of evil\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and in the time of affliction. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 15:12"},"Can one break iron, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even iron from the north, and bronze? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 15:13"},"I will give your substance and your treasures for a plunder without price,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and that for all your sins, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even in all your borders. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 15:14"},"I will make them to pass with your enemies into a land which you don’t know;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for a fire is kindled in my anger, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["which will burn on you.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 15:15"},"LORD, you know. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Remember me, visit me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and avenge me of my persecutors. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You are patient, so don’t take me away. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Know that for your sake I have suffered reproach. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 15:16"},"Your words were found, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I ate them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Your words were to me a joy and the rejoicing of my heart, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for I am called by your name, the LORD, Allah of Armies. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 15:17"},"I didn’t sit in the assembly of those who make merry and rejoice.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I sat alone because of your hand, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for you have filled me with indignation. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 15:18"},"Why is my pain perpetual, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and my wound incurable, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["which refuses to be healed? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Will you indeed be to me as a deceitful brook, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like waters that fail? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 15:19"},"Therefore the LORD says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“If you return, then I will bring you again, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that you may stand before me; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and if you take out the precious from the vile, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you will be as my mouth. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They will return to you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but you will not return to them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 15:20"},"I will make you to this people a fortified bronze wall. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They will fight against you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but they will not prevail against you; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for I am with you to save you \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and to deliver you,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 15:21"},"“I will deliver you out of the hand of the wicked, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will redeem you out of the hand of the terrible.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"16","sid":"JER 16"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 16:1"},"The LORD’s word came also to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 16:2"},"“You shall not take a wife, neither shall you have sons or daughters, in this place.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 16:3"},"For the LORD says concerning the sons and concerning the daughters who are born in this place, and concerning their\nmothers who bore them, and concerning their fathers who became their father in this land:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 16:4"},"“They will die grievous deaths. They will not be lamented, neither will they be buried. They will be as dung on the\nsurface of the ground. They will be consumed by the sword and by famine. Their dead bodies will be food for the birds of the\nsky and for the animals of the earth.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 16:5"},"For the LORD says, “Don’t enter into the house of mourning. Don’t go to lament. Don’t bemoan them, for I have taken away\nmy peace from this people,” says the LORD, “even loving kindness and tender mercies.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 16:6"},"Both great and small will die in this land. They will not be buried. Men won’t lament for them, cut themselves, or make\nthemselves bald for them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 16:7"},"Men won’t break bread for them in mourning, to comfort them for the dead. Men won’t give them the cup of consolation to\ndrink for their father or for their mother. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 16:8"},"“You shall not go into the house of feasting to sit with them, to eat and to drink.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 16:9"},"For the LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel says: “Behold, I will cause to cease out of this place, before your eyes and in\nyour days, the voice of mirth and the voice of gladness, the voice of the bridegroom and the voice of the bride.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 16:10"},"It will happen, when you tell this people all these words, and they ask you, ‘Why has the LORD pronounced all this great\nevil against us?’ or ‘What is our iniquity? or ‘What is our sin that we have committed against the LORD our Allah?’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 16:11"},"then you shall tell them, ‘Because your fathers have forsaken me,’ says the LORD, ‘and have walked after other gods, have\nserved them, have worshipped them, have forsaken me, and have not kept my law.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 16:12"},"You have done evil more than your fathers, for behold, you each walk after the stubbornness of his evil heart, so that\nyou don’t listen to me. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 16:13"},"Therefore I will cast you out of this land into the land that you have not known, neither you nor your fathers. There you\nwill serve other gods day and night, for I will show you no favour.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 16:14"},"“Therefore behold, the days come,” says the LORD, “that it will no more be said, ‘As the LORD lives, who brought up the\nchildren of Israel out of the land of Egypt;’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 16:15"},"but, ‘As the LORD lives, who brought up the children of Israel from the land of the north, and from all the countries\nwhere he had driven them.’ I will bring them again into their land that I gave to their fathers.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 16:16"},"“Behold, I will send for many fishermen,” says the LORD, “and they will fish them up. Afterward I will send for many\nhunters, and they will hunt them from every mountain, from every hill, and out of the clefts of the rocks.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 16:17"},"For my eyes are on all their ways. They are not hidden from my face. Their iniquity isn’t concealed from my eyes.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 16:18"},"First I will recompense their iniquity and their sin double, because they have polluted my land with the carcasses of\ntheir detestable things, and have filled my inheritance with their abominations.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 16:19"},"LORD, my strength, and my stronghold, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and my refuge in the day of affliction, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["the nations will come to you from the ends of the earth, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will say, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Our fathers have inherited nothing but lies, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["vanity and things in which there is no profit. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 16:20"},"Should a man make to himself gods \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["which yet are no gods?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 16:21"},"“Therefore behold, I will cause them to know, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["this once I will cause them to know my hand and my might. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Then they will know that my name is the LORD.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"17","sid":"JER 17"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 17:1"},"“The sin of Judah is written with a pen of iron, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and with the point of a diamond. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["It is engraved on the tablet of their heart, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and on the horns of your altars. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 17:2"},"Even their children remember their altars \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their Asherah poles by the green trees on the high hills.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 17:3"},"My mountain in the field, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will give your substance and all your treasures for a plunder,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your high places, because of sin, throughout all your borders.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 17:4"},"You, even of yourself, will discontinue from your heritage that I gave you.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will cause you to serve your enemies in the land which you don’t know,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for you have kindled a fire in my anger which will burn forever.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 17:5"},"The LORD says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Cursed is the man who trusts in man, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["relies on strength of flesh, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and whose heart departs from the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 17:6"},"For he will be like a bush in the desert, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will not see when good comes, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["but will inhabit the parched places in the wilderness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["an uninhabited salt land. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 17:7"},"“Blessed is the man who trusts in the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and whose confidence is in the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 17:8"},"For he will be as a tree planted by the waters, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who spreads out its roots by the river, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and will not fear when heat comes, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but its leaf will be green, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and will not be concerned in the year of drought. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It won’t cease from yielding fruit. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 17:9"},"The heart is deceitful above all things \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and it is exceedingly corrupt. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Who can know it? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 17:10"},"“I, the LORD, search the mind. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I try the heart, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["even to give every man according to his ways, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["according to the fruit of his doings.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 17:11"},"As the partridge that sits on eggs which she has not laid,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so is he who gets riches, and not by right. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["In the middle of his days, they will leave him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["At his end, he will be a fool. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 17:12"},"A glorious throne, set on high from the beginning, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["is the place of our sanctuary. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 17:13"},"LORD, the hope of Israel, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["all who forsake you will be disappointed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Those who depart from me will be written in the earth, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because they have forsaken the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the spring of living waters. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 17:14"},"Heal me, O LORD, and I will be healed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Save me, and I will be saved; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for you are my praise. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 17:15"},"Behold, they ask me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Where is the LORD’s word? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Let it be fulfilled now.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 17:16"},"As for me, I have not hurried from being a shepherd after you.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I haven’t desired the woeful day. You know. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["That which came out of my lips was before your face. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 17:17"},"Don’t be a terror to me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You are my refuge in the day of evil. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 17:18"},"Let them be disappointed who persecute me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but let not me be disappointed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Let them be dismayed, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but don’t let me be dismayed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Bring on them the day of evil, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and destroy them with double destruction. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 17:19"},"The LORD said this to me: “Go and stand in the gate of the children of the people, through which the kings of Judah come\nin and by which they go out, and in all the gates of Jerusalem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 17:20"},"Tell them, ‘Hear the LORD’s word, you kings of Judah, all Judah, and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem, that enter in by\nthese gates: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 17:21"},"The LORD says, “Be careful, and bear no burden on the Sabbath day, nor bring it in by the gates of Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 17:22"},"Don’t carry a burden out of your houses on the Sabbath day. Don’t do any work, but make the Sabbath day holy, as I\ncommanded your fathers. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 17:23"},"But they didn’t listen. They didn’t turn their ear, but made their neck stiff, that they might not hear, and might not\nreceive instruction. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 17:24"},"It will happen, if you diligently listen to me,” says the LORD, “to bring in no burden through the gates of this city on\nthe Sabbath day, but to make the Sabbath day holy, to do no work therein;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 17:25"},"then there will enter in by the gates of this city kings and princes sitting on Dawood’s throne, riding in chariots and\non horses, they, and their princes, the men of Judah, and the inhabitants of Jerusalem; and this city will remain forever.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 17:26"},"They will come from the cities of Judah, and from the places around Jerusalem, from the land of Benjamin, from the\nlowland, from the hill country, and from the South, bringing burnt offerings, sacrifices, meal offerings, and frankincense, and\nbringing sacrifices of thanksgiving, to the LORD’s house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 17:27"},"But if you will not listen to me to make the Sabbath day holy, and not to bear a burden and enter in at the gates of\nJerusalem on the Sabbath day, then I will kindle a fire in its gates, and it will devour the palaces of Jerusalem. It will not\nbe quenched.”’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"18","sid":"JER 18"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 18:1"},"The word which came to Jeremiah from the LORD, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 18:2"},"“Arise, and go down to the potter’s house, and there I will cause you to hear my words.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 18:3"},"Then I went down to the potter’s house, and behold, he was making something on the wheels.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 18:4"},"When the vessel that he made of the clay was marred in the hand of the potter, he made it again another vessel, as seemed\ngood to the potter to make it. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 18:5"},"Then the LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 18:6"},"“House of Israel, can’t I do with you as this potter?” says the LORD. “Behold, as the clay in the potter’s hand, so are\nyou in my hand, house of Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 18:7"},"At the instant I speak concerning a nation, and concerning a kingdom, to pluck up and to break down and to destroy it;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 18:8"},"if that nation, concerning which I have spoken, turns from their evil, I will repent of the evil that I thought to do to\nthem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 18:9"},"At the instant I speak concerning a nation, and concerning a kingdom, to build and to plant it;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 18:10"},"if they do that which is evil in my sight, that they not obey my voice, then I will repent of the good with which I said\nI would benefit them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 18:11"},"“Now therefore, speak to the men of Judah, and to the inhabitants of Jerusalem, saying, ‘The LORD says: “Behold, I frame\nevil against you, and devise a plan against you. Everyone return from his evil way now, and amend your ways and your doings.”’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 18:12"},"But they say, ‘It is in vain; for we will walk after our own plans, and we will each follow the stubbornness of his evil\nheart.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 18:13"},"Therefore the LORD says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Ask now amongst the nations, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘Who has heard such things?’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The virgin of Israel has done a very horrible thing. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 18:14"},"Will the snow of Lebanon fail from the rock of the field? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Will the cold waters that flow down from afar be dried up? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 18:15"},"For my people have forgotten me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They have burnt incense to false gods. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They have been made to stumble in their ways, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the ancient paths, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to walk in byways, in a way not built up, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 18:16"},"to make their land an astonishment, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and a perpetual hissing. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Everyone who passes by it will be astonished, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and shake his head. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 18:17"},"I will scatter them as with an east wind before the enemy.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will show them the back, and not the face, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the day of their calamity. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 18:18"},"Then they said, “Come! Let’s devise plans against Jeremiah; for the law won’t perish from the priest, nor counsel from\nthe wise, nor the word from the prophet. Come, and let’s strike him with the tongue, and let’s not give heed to any of his\nwords.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 18:19"},"Give heed to me, LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and listen to the voice of those who contend with me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 18:20"},"Should evil be recompensed for good? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["For they have dug a pit for my soul. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Remember how I stood before you to speak good for them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to turn away your wrath from them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 18:21"},"Therefore deliver up their children to the famine, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and give them over to the power of the sword. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Let their wives become childless and widows. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Let their men be killed \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their young men struck by the sword in battle. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 18:22"},"Let a cry be heard from their houses \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when you bring a troop suddenly on them; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for they have dug a pit to take me \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and hidden snares for my feet. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 18:23"},"Yet, LORD, you know all their counsel against me to kill me.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Don’t forgive their iniquity. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Don’t blot out their sin from your sight, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Let them be overthrown before you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Deal with them in the time of your anger. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"19","sid":"JER 19"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 19:1"},"Thus said the LORD, “Go, and buy a potter’s earthen container, and take some of the elders of the people, and of the\nelders of the priests; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 19:2"},"and go out to the valley of the son of Hinnom, which is by the entry of the gate Harsith, and proclaim there the words\nthat I will tell you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 19:3"},"Say, ‘Hear the LORD’s word, kings of Judah, and inhabitants of Jerusalem: The LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel says,\n“Behold, I will bring evil on this place, which whoever hears, his ears will tingle.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 19:4"},"Because they have forsaken me, and have defiled this place, and have burnt incense in it to other gods that they didn’t\nknow, they, their fathers, and the kings of Judah, and have filled this place with the blood of innocents,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 19:5"},"and have built the high places of Baal, to burn their children in the fire for burnt offerings to Baal, which I didn’t\ncommand, nor speak, which didn’t even enter into my mind. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 19:6"},"Therefore, behold, the days come,” says the LORD, “that this place will no more be called ‘Topheth’, nor ‘The Valley of\nthe son of Hinnom’, but ‘The valley of Slaughter’. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 19:7"},"“‘“I will make the counsel of Judah and Jerusalem void in this place. I will cause them to fall by the sword before their\nenemies, and by the hand of those who seek their life. I will give their dead bodies to be food for the birds of the sky and\nfor the animals of the earth. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 19:8"},"I will make this city an astonishment and a hissing. Everyone who passes by it will be astonished and hiss because of all\nits plagues. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 19:9"},"I will cause them to eat the flesh of their sons and the flesh of their daughters. They will each eat the flesh of his\nfriend in the siege and in the distress, with which their enemies, and those who seek their life, will distress them.”’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 19:10"},"“Then you shall break the container in the sight of the men who go with you,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 19:11"},"and shall tell them, ‘The LORD of Armies says: “Even so I will break this people and this city, as one breaks a potter’s\nvessel, that can’t be made whole again. They will bury in Topheth, until there is no place to bury.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 19:12"},"This is what I will do to this place,” says the LORD, “and to its inhabitants, even making this city as Topheth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 19:13"},"The houses of Jerusalem, and the houses of the kings of Judah, which are defiled, will be as the place of Topheth, even\nall the houses on whose roofs they have burnt incense to all the army of the sky and have poured out drink offerings to other\ngods.”’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 19:14"},"Then Jeremiah came from Topheth, where the LORD had sent him to prophesy, and he stood in the court of the LORD’s house,\nand said to all the people: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 19:15"},"“The LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel says, ‘Behold, I will bring on this city and on all its towns all the evil that I\nhave pronounced against it, because they have made their neck stiff, that they may not hear my words.’”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"20","sid":"JER 20"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 20:1"},"Now Pashhur, the son of Immer the priest, who was chief officer in the LORD’s house, heard Jeremiah prophesying these\nthings. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 20:2"},"Then Pashhur struck Jeremiah the prophet and put him in the stocks that were in the upper gate of Benjamin, which was in\nthe LORD’s house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 20:3"},"On the next day, Pashhur released Jeremiah out of the stocks. Then Jeremiah said to him, “The LORD has not called your\nname Pashhur, but Magormissabib.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Magormissabib” means “surrounded by\nterror”"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 20:4"},"For the LORD says, ‘Behold, I will make you a terror to yourself and to all your friends. They will fall by the sword of\ntheir enemies, and your eyes will see it. I will give all Judah into the hand of the king of Babylon, and he will carry them\ncaptive to Babylon, and will kill them with the sword. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 20:5"},"Moreover I will give all the riches of this city, and all its gains, and all its precious things, yes, I will give all the\ntreasures of the kings of Judah into the hand of their enemies. They will make them captives, take them, and carry them to\nBabylon. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 20:6"},"You, Pashhur, and all who dwell in your house will go into captivity. You will come to Babylon, and there you will die,\nand there you will be buried, you, and all your friends, to whom you have prophesied falsely.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 20:7"},"LORD, you have persuaded me, and I was persuaded. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You are stronger than I, and have prevailed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I have become a laughingstock all day. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Everyone mocks me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 20:8"},"For as often as I speak, I cry out; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I cry, “Violence and destruction!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["because the LORD’s word has been made a reproach to me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and a derision, all day. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 20:9"},"If I say, I will not make mention of him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or speak any more in his name, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["then there is in my heart as it were a burning fire shut up in my bones.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I am weary with holding it in. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I can’t. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 20:10"},"For I have heard the defaming of many, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Terror on every side! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Denounce, and we will denounce him!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["say all my familiar friends, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["those who watch for my fall. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Perhaps he will be persuaded, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and we will prevail against him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and we will take our revenge on him.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 20:11"},"But the LORD is with me as an awesome mighty one. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Therefore my persecutors will stumble, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they won’t prevail. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They will be utterly disappointed, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because they have not dealt wisely, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even with an everlasting dishonour which will never be forgotten.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 20:12"},"But the LORD of Armies, who tests the righteous, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who sees the heart and the mind, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["let me see your vengeance on them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for I have revealed my cause to you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 20:13"},"Sing to the LORD! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Praise the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for he has delivered the soul of the needy from the hand of evildoers.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 20:14"},"Cursed is the day in which I was born. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Don’t let the day in which my mother bore me be blessed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 20:15"},"Cursed is the man who brought news to my father, saying, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“A boy is born to you,” making him very glad. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 20:16"},"Let that man be as the cities which the LORD overthrew, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and didn’t repent. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Let him hear a cry in the morning, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and shouting at noontime; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 20:17"},"because he didn’t kill me from the womb. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["So my mother would have been my grave, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and her womb always great. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 20:18"},"Why did I come out of the womb to see labour and sorrow, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that my days should be consumed with shame? \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"21","sid":"JER 21"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 21:1"},"The word which came to Jeremiah from the LORD, when king Zedekiah sent to him Pashhur the son of Malchijah, and Zephaniah\nthe son of Maaseiah, the priest, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 21:2"},"“Please enquire of the LORD for us; for Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon makes war against us. Perhaps the LORD will deal\nwith us according to all his wondrous works, that he may withdraw from us.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 21:3"},"Then Jeremiah said to them, “Tell Zedekiah: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 21:4"},"‘The LORD, Allah of Israel says, “Behold, I will turn back the weapons of war that are in your hands, with which you fight\nagainst the king of Babylon, and against the Chaldeans who besiege you outside the walls; and I will gather them into the\nmiddle of this city. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 21:5"},"I myself will fight against you with an outstretched hand and with a strong arm, even in anger, in wrath, and in great\nindignation. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 21:6"},"I will strike the inhabitants of this city, both man and animal. They will die of a great pestilence.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 21:7"},"Afterward,” says the LORD, “I will deliver Zedekiah king of Judah, his servants, and the people, even those who are left\nin this city from the pestilence, from the sword, and from the famine, into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, and\ninto the hand of their enemies, and into the hand of those who seek their life. He will strike them with the edge of the sword.\nHe will not spare them, have pity, or have mercy.”’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 21:8"},"“You shall say to this people, ‘The LORD says: “Behold, I set before you the way of life and the way of death.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 21:9"},"He who remains in this city will die by the sword, by the famine, and by the pestilence; but he who goes out and passes\nover to the Chaldeans who besiege you, he will live, and he will escape with his life.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 21:10"},"For I have set my face on this city for evil, and not for good,” says the LORD. “It will be given into the hand of the\nking of Babylon, and he will burn it with fire.”’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 21:11"},"“Concerning the house of the king of Judah, hear the LORD’s word:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 21:12"},"House of Dawood, the LORD says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘Execute justice in the morning, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and deliver him who is robbed out of the hand of the oppressor,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["lest my wrath go out like fire, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and burn so that no one can quench it, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because of the evil of your doings. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 21:13"},"Behold, I am against you, O inhabitant of the valley, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and of the rock of the plain,’ says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘You that say, “Who would come down against us?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or “Who would enter into our homes?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 21:14"},"I will punish you according to the fruit of your doings, says the LORD;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will kindle a fire in her forest, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and it will devour all that is around her.’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"22","sid":"JER 22"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 22:1"},"The LORD said, “Go down to the house of the king of Judah, and speak this word, there:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 22:2"},"‘Hear the LORD’s word, king of Judah, who sits on Dawood’s throne, you, your servants, and your people who enter in by\nthese gates. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 22:3"},"The LORD says: “Execute justice and righteousness, and deliver him who is robbed out of the hand of the oppressor. Do no\nwrong. Do no violence to the foreigner, the fatherless, or the widow. Don’t shed innocent blood in this place.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 22:4"},"For if you do this thing indeed, then kings sitting on Dawood’s throne will enter in by the gates of this house, riding in\nchariots and on horses, he, his servants, and his people. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 22:5"},"But if you will not hear these words, I swear by myself,” says the LORD, “that this house will become a desolation.”’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 22:6"},"For the LORD says concerning the house of the king of Judah:\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“You are Gilead to me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the head of Lebanon. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Yet surely I will make you a wilderness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["cities which are not inhabited. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 22:7"},"I will prepare destroyers against you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["everyone with his weapons, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and they will cut down your choice cedars, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and cast them into the fire. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 22:8"},"“Many nations will pass by this city, and they will each ask his neighbour, ‘Why has the LORD done this to this great\ncity?’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 22:9"},"Then they will answer, ‘Because they abandoned the covenant of the LORD their Allah, worshipped other gods, and served\nthem.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 22:10"},"Don’t weep for the dead. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Don’t bemoan him; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["but weep bitterly for him who goes away, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for he will return no more, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and not see his native country. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 22:11"},"For the LORD says touching Shallum the son of Josiah, king of Judah, who reigned instead of Josiah his father, and who\nwent out of this place: “He won’t return there any more. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 22:12"},"But he will die in the place where they have led him captive. He will see this land no more.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 22:13"},"“Woe to him who builds his house by unrighteousness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and his rooms by injustice; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["who uses his neighbour’s service without wages, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and doesn’t give him his hire; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 22:14"},"who says, ‘I will build myself a wide house and spacious rooms,’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and cuts out windows for himself; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["with a cedar ceiling, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and painted with red. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 22:15"},"“Should you reign, because you strive to excel in cedar? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Didn’t your father eat and drink, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and do justice and righteousness? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Then it was well with him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 22:16"},"He judged the cause of the poor and needy; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so it was well, then. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Wasn’t this to know me?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 22:17"},"But your eyes and your heart are only for your covetousness,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for shedding innocent blood, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for oppression, and for doing violence.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 22:18"},"Therefore the LORD says concerning Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah:\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“They won’t lament for him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["saying, ‘Ah my brother!’ or, ‘Ah sister!’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They won’t lament for him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["saying ‘Ah lord!’ or, ‘Ah his glory!’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 22:19"},"He will be buried with the burial of a donkey, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["drawn and cast out beyond the gates of Jerusalem.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 22:20"},"“Go up to Lebanon, and cry. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Lift up your voice in Bashan, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and cry from Abarim; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for all your lovers have been destroyed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 22:21"},"I spoke to you in your prosperity; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but you said, ‘I will not listen.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["This has been your way from your youth, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that you didn’t obey my voice. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 22:22"},"The wind will feed all your shepherds, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your lovers will go into captivity. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Surely then you will be ashamed \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and confounded for all your wickedness. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 22:23"},"Inhabitant of Lebanon, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who makes your nest in the cedars, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["how greatly to be pitied you will be when pangs come on you,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the pain as of a woman in travail! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 22:24"},"“As I live,” says the LORD, “though Coniah the son of Jehoiakim king of Judah were the signet on my right hand, yet would\nI pluck you from there. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 22:25"},"I would give you into the hand of those who seek your life, and into the hand of them of whom you are afraid, even into\nthe hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, and into the hand of the Chaldeans.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 22:26"},"I will cast you out with your mother who bore you into another country, where you were not born; and there you will die.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 22:27"},"But to the land to which their soul longs to return, there they will not return.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 22:28"},"Is this man Coniah a despised broken vessel? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Is he a vessel in which no one delights? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Why are they cast out, he and his offspring, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and cast into a land which they don’t know? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JER 22:29"},"O earth, earth, earth, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["hear the LORD’s word! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JER 22:30"},"The LORD says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Record this man as childless, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a man who will not prosper in his days; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for no more will a man of his offspring prosper, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["sitting on Dawood’s throne, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and ruling in Judah.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"23","sid":"JER 23"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 23:1"},"“Woe to the shepherds who destroy and scatter the sheep of my pasture!” says the LORD.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 23:2"},"Therefore the LORD, Allah of Israel, says against the shepherds who feed my people: “You have scattered my flock, driven\nthem away, and have not visited them. Behold, I will visit on you the evil of your doings,” says the LORD.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 23:3"},"“I will gather the remnant of my flock out of all the countries where I have driven them, and will bring them again to\ntheir folds; and they will be fruitful and multiply. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 23:4"},"I will set up shepherds over them, who will feed them. They will no longer be afraid or dismayed, neither will any be\nlacking,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 23:5"},"“Behold, the days come,” says the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“that I will raise to Dawood a righteous Branch, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and he will reign as king and deal wisely, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will execute justice and righteousness in the land. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 23:6"},"In his days Judah will be saved, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and Israel will dwell safely. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["This is his name by which he will be called: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The LORD our righteousness. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 23:7"},"“Therefore behold, the days come,” says the LORD, “that they will no more say, ‘As the LORD lives, who brought up the\nchildren of Israel out of the land of Egypt;’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 23:8"},"but, ‘As the LORD lives, who brought up and who led the offspring of the house of Israel out of the north country, and\nfrom all the countries where I had driven them.’ Then they will dwell in their own land.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 23:9"},"Concerning the prophets: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["My heart within me is broken. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["All my bones shake. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I am like a drunken man, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and like a man whom wine has overcome, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["because of the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and because of his holy words. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 23:10"},"For the land is full of adulterers; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for because of the curse the land mourns. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The pastures of the wilderness have dried up. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Their course is evil, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their might is not right; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 23:11"},"for both prophet and priest are profane. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Yes, in my house I have found their wickedness,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 23:12"},"Therefore their way will be to them as slippery places in the darkness.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They will be driven on, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and fall therein; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for I will bring evil on them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even the year of their visitation,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 23:13"},"“I have seen folly in the prophets of Samaria. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They prophesied by Baal, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and caused my people Israel to err. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 23:14"},"In the prophets of Jerusalem I have also seen a horrible thing:\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they commit adultery and walk in lies. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They strengthen the hands of evildoers, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so that no one returns from his wickedness. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They have all become to me as Sodom, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and its inhabitants as Gomorrah.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 23:15"},"Therefore the LORD of Armies says concerning the prophets:\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, I will feed them with wormwood, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and make them drink poisoned water; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for from the prophets of Jerusalem ungodliness has gone out into all the land.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 23:16"},"The LORD of Armies says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Don’t listen to the words of the prophets who prophesy to you.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They teach you vanity. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They speak a vision of their own heart, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and not out of the mouth of the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 23:17"},"They say continually to those who despise me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘The LORD has said, “You will have peace;”’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and to everyone who walks in the stubbornness of his own heart they say,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘No evil will come on you.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 23:18"},"For who has stood in the council of the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that he should perceive and hear his word? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Who has listened to my word, and heard it? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 23:19"},"Behold, the LORD’s storm, his wrath, has gone out. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Yes, a whirling storm: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It will burst on the head of the wicked. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 23:20"},"The LORD’s anger will not return until he has executed, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and until he has performed the intents of his heart. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["In the latter days, you will understand it perfectly. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 23:21"},"I didn’t send these prophets, yet they ran. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I didn’t speak to them, yet they prophesied. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 23:22"},"But if they had stood in my council, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["then they would have caused my people to hear my words, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and would have turned them from their evil way, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and from the evil of their doings. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 23:23"},"“Am I Allah at hand,” says the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“and not Allah afar off? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 23:24"},"Can anyone hide himself in secret places \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so that I can’t see him?” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Don’t I fill heaven and earth?” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 23:25"},"“I have heard what the prophets have said, who prophesy lies in my name, saying, ‘I had a dream! I had a dream!’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 23:26"},"How long will this be in the heart of the prophets who prophesy lies, even the prophets of the deceit of their own heart?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 23:27"},"They intend to cause my people to forget my name by their dreams which they each tell his neighbour, as their fathers\nforgot my name because of Baal. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 23:28"},"The prophet who has a dream, let him tell a dream; and he who has my word, let him speak my word faithfully. What is the\nstraw to the wheat?” says the LORD. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JER 23:29"},"“Isn’t my word like fire?” says the LORD; “and like a hammer that breaks the rock in pieces?\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JER 23:30"},"“Therefore behold, I am against the prophets,” says the LORD, “who each steal my words from his neighbour.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JER 23:31"},"Behold, I am against the prophets,” says the LORD, “who use their tongues, and say, ‘He says.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JER 23:32"},"Behold, I am against those who prophesy lying dreams,” says the LORD, “who tell them, and cause my people to err by their\nlies, and by their vain boasting; yet I didn’t send them or command them. They don’t profit this people at all,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JER 23:33"},"“When this people, or the prophet, or a priest, asks you, saying, ‘What is the message from the LORD?’ Then you shall\ntell them, ‘“What message? I will cast you off,” says the LORD.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JER 23:34"},"As for the prophet, the priest, and the people, who say, ‘The message from the LORD,’ I will even punish that man and his\nhousehold. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JER 23:35"},"You will say everyone to his neighbour, and everyone to his brother, ‘What has the LORD answered?’ and, ‘What has the\nLORD said?’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JER 23:36"},"You will mention the message from the LORD no more: for every man’s own word has become his message; for you have\nperverted the words of the living Allah, of the LORD of Armies, our Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JER 23:37"},"You will say to the prophet, ‘What has the LORD answered you?’ and, ‘What has the LORD spoken?’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JER 23:38"},"Although you say, ‘The message from the LORD;’ therefore the LORD says: ‘Because you say this word, “The message from the\nLORD,” and I have sent to you, telling you not to say, “The message from the LORD;”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JER 23:39"},"therefore, behold, I will utterly forget you, and I will cast you off, and the city that I gave to you and to your\nfathers, away from my presence. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"JER 23:40"},"I will bring an everlasting reproach on you, and a perpetual shame, which will not be forgotten.’”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"24","sid":"JER 24"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 24:1"},"The LORD showed me, and behold, two baskets of figs were set before the LORD’s temple, after Nebuchadnezzar king of\nBabylon had carried away captive Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, and the princes of Judah, with the craftsmen and\nsmiths, from Jerusalem, and had brought them to Babylon. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 24:2"},"One basket had very good figs, like the figs that are first-ripe; and the other basket had very bad figs, which could not\nbe eaten, they were so bad. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 24:3"},"Then the LORD asked me, “What do you see, Jeremiah?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I said, “Figs. The good figs are very good, and the bad are very bad, so bad that can’t be eaten.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 24:4"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 24:5"},"“The LORD, Allah of Israel says: ‘Like these good figs, so I will regard the captives of Judah, whom I have sent out of\nthis place into the land of the Chaldeans, for good. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 24:6"},"For I will set my eyes on them for good, and I will bring them again to this land. I will build them, and not pull them\ndown. I will plant them, and not pluck them up. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 24:7"},"I will give them a heart to know me, that I am the LORD. They will be my people, and I will be their Allah; for they will\nreturn to me with their whole heart. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 24:8"},"“‘As the bad figs, which can’t be eaten, they are so bad,’ surely the LORD says, ‘So I will give up Zedekiah the king of\nJudah, and his princes, and the remnant of Jerusalem, who remain in this land, and those who dwell in the land of Egypt.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 24:9"},"I will even give them up to be tossed back and forth amongst all the kingdoms of the earth for evil; to be a reproach and\na proverb, a taunt and a curse, in all places where I will drive them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 24:10"},"I will send the sword, the famine, and the pestilence, amongst them, until they are consumed from off the land that I\ngave to them and to their fathers.’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"25","sid":"JER 25"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 25:1"},"The word that came to Jeremiah concerning all the people of Judah, in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king\nof Judah (this was the first year of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon),\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 25:2"},"which Jeremiah the prophet spoke to all the people of Judah, and to all the inhabitants of Jerusalem:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 25:3"},"From the thirteenth year of Josiah the son of Amon, king of Judah, even to this day, these twenty-three years, the LORD’s\nword has come to me, and I have spoken to you, rising up early and speaking; but you have not listened.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 25:4"},"The LORD has sent to you all his servants the prophets, rising up early and sending them (but you have not listened or\ninclined your ear to hear), \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 25:5"},"saying, “Return now everyone from his evil way, and from the evil of your doings, and dwell in the land that the LORD has\ngiven to you and to your fathers, from of old and even forever more.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 25:6"},"Don’t go after other gods to serve them or worship them, and don’t provoke me to anger with the work of your hands; then I\nwill do you no harm.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 25:7"},"“Yet you have not listened to me,” says the LORD; “that you may provoke me to anger with the work of your hands to your\nown hurt.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 25:8"},"Therefore the LORD of Armies says: “Because you have not heard my words,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 25:9"},"behold, I will send and take all the families of the north,” says the LORD, “and I will send to Nebuchadnezzar the king of\nBabylon, my servant, and will bring them against this land, and against its inhabitants, and against all these nations around.\nI will utterly destroy them, and make them an astonishment, and a hissing, and perpetual desolations.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 25:10"},"Moreover I will take from them the voice of mirth and the voice of gladness, the voice of the bridegroom and the voice of\nthe bride, the sound of the millstones, and the light of the lamp.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 25:11"},"This whole land will be a desolation, and an astonishment; and these nations will serve the king of Babylon seventy\nyears. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 25:12"},"“It will happen, when seventy years are accomplished, that I will punish the king of Babylon and that nation,” says the\nLORD, “for their iniquity. I will make the land of the Chaldeans desolate forever.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 25:13"},"I will bring on that land all my words which I have pronounced against it, even all that is written in this book, which\nJeremiah has prophesied against all the nations. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 25:14"},"For many nations and great kings will make bondservants of them, even of them. I will recompense them according to their\ndeeds, and according to the work of their hands.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 25:15"},"For the LORD, Allah of Israel, says to me: “Take this cup of the wine of wrath from my hand, and cause all the nations to\nwhom I send you to drink it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 25:16"},"They will drink, and reel back and forth, and be insane, because of the sword that I will send amongst them.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 25:17"},"Then I took the cup at the LORD’s hand, and made all the nations to drink, to whom the LORD had sent me:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 25:18"},"Jerusalem, and the cities of Judah, with its kings and its princes, to make them a desolation, an astonishment, a\nhissing, and a curse, as it is today; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 25:19"},"Pharaoh king of Egypt, with his servants, his princes, and all his people;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 25:20"},"and all the mixed people, and all the kings of the land of Uz, all the kings of the Philistines, Ashkelon, Gaza, Ekron,\nand the remnant of Ashdod; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 25:21"},"Edom, Moab, and the children of Ammon; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 25:22"},"and all the kings of Tyre, all the kings of Sidon, and the kings of the isle which is beyond the sea;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 25:23"},"Dedan, Tema, Buz, and all who have the corners of their beard cut off;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 25:24"},"and all the kings of Arabia, all the kings of the mixed people who dwell in the wilderness;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 25:25"},"and all the kings of Zimri, all the kings of Elam, and all the kings of the Medes;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 25:26"},"and all the kings of the north, far and near, one with another; and all the kingdoms of the world, which are on the\nsurface of the earth. The king of Sheshach will drink after them.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 25:27"},"“You shall tell them, ‘The LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel says: “Drink, and be drunk, vomit, fall, and rise no more,\nbecause of the sword which I will send amongst you.”’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 25:28"},"It shall be, if they refuse to take the cup at your hand to drink, then you shall tell them, ‘The LORD of Armies says:\n“You shall surely drink. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JER 25:29"},"For, behold, I begin to work evil at the city which is called by my name; and should you be utterly unpunished? You will\nnot be unpunished; for I will call for a sword on all the inhabitants of the earth, says the LORD of Armies.”’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JER 25:30"},"“Therefore prophesy against them all these words, and tell them,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“‘The LORD will roar from on high, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and utter his voice from his holy habitation. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He will mightily roar against his fold. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He will give a shout, as those who tread grapes, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["against all the inhabitants of the earth. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JER 25:31"},"A noise will come even to the end of the earth; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the LORD has a controversy with the nations. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He will enter into judgement with all flesh. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["As for the wicked, he will give them to the sword,”’ says the LORD.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JER 25:32"},"The LORD of Armies says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, evil will go out from nation to nation, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and a great storm will be raised up from the uttermost parts of the earth.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JER 25:33"},"The slain of the LORD will be at that day from one end of the earth even to the other end of the earth. They won’t be\nlamented. They won’t be gathered or buried. They will be dung on the surface of the ground.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JER 25:34"},"Wail, you shepherds, and cry. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Wallow in dust, you leader of the flock; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for the days of your slaughter and of your dispersions have fully come,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and you will fall like fine pottery. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JER 25:35"},"The shepherds will have no way to flee. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The leader of the flock will have no escape. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JER 25:36"},"A voice of the cry of the shepherds, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the wailing of the leader of the flock, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the LORD destroys their pasture. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JER 25:37"},"The peaceful folds are brought to silence \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because of the fierce anger of the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JER 25:38"},"He has left his covert, as the lion; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for their land has become an astonishment because of the fierceness of the oppression,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and because of his fierce anger. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"26","sid":"JER 26"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 26:1"},"In the beginning of the reign of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah, this word came from the LORD:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 26:2"},"“The LORD says: ‘Stand in the court of the LORD’s house, and speak to all the cities of Judah, which come to worship in\nthe LORD’s house, all the words that I command you to speak to them. Don’t omit a word.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 26:3"},"It may be they will listen, and every man turn from his evil way; that I may relent from the evil which I intend to do to\nthem because of the evil of their doings.’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 26:4"},"You shall tell them, “The LORD says: ‘If you will not listen to me, to walk in my law, which I have set before you,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 26:5"},"to listen to the words of my servants the prophets, whom I send to you, even rising up early and sending them, but you\nhave not listened; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 26:6"},"then I will make this house like Shiloh, and will make this city a curse to all the nations of the earth.”’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 26:7"},"The priests and the prophets and all the people heard Jeremiah speaking these words in the LORD’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 26:8"},"When Jeremiah had finished speaking all that the LORD had commanded him to speak to all the people, the priests and the\nprophets and all the people seized him, saying, “You shall surely die!\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 26:9"},"Why have you prophesied in the LORD’s name, saying, ‘This house will be like Shiloh, and this city will be desolate,\nwithout inhabitant?’” All the people were crowded around Jeremiah in the LORD’s house.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 26:10"},"When the princes of Judah heard these things, they came up from the king’s house to the LORD’s house; and they sat in the\nentry of the new gate of the LORD’s house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 26:11"},"Then the priests and the prophets spoke to the princes and to all the people, saying, “This man is worthy of death; for\nhe has prophesied against this city, as you have heard with your ears.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 26:12"},"Then Jeremiah spoke to all the princes and to all the people, saying, “The LORD sent me to prophesy against this house\nand against this city all the words that you have heard. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 26:13"},"Now therefore amend your ways and your doings, and obey Allah your LORD’s voice; then the LORD will relent from the evil\nthat he has pronounced against you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 26:14"},"But as for me, behold, I am in your hand. Do with me what is good and right in your eyes.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 26:15"},"Only know for certain that, if you put me to death, you will bring innocent blood on yourselves, on this city, and on its\ninhabitants; for in truth the LORD has sent me to you to speak all these words in your ears.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 26:16"},"Then the princes and all the people said to the priests and to the prophets: “This man is not worthy of death; for he has\nspoken to us in the name of the LORD our Allah.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 26:17"},"Then certain of the elders of the land rose up, and spoke to all the assembly of the people, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 26:18"},"“Micah the Morashtite prophesied in the days of Hezekiah king of Judah; and he spoke to all the people of Judah, saying,\n‘The LORD of Armies says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“‘Zion will be ploughed as a field, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and Jerusalem will become heaps, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the mountain of the house as the high places of a forest.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 26:19"},"Did Hezekiah king of Judah and all Judah put him to death? Didn’t he fear the LORD, and entreat the favour of the LORD,\nand the LORD relented of the disaster which he had pronounced against them? We would commit great evil against our own souls\nthat way!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 26:20"},"There was also a man who prophesied in the LORD’s name, Uriah the son of Shemaiah of Kiriath Jearim; and he prophesied\nagainst this city and against this land according to all the words of Jeremiah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 26:21"},"When Jehoiakim the king, with all his mighty men and all the princes heard his words, the king sought to put him to\ndeath; but when Uriah heard it, he was afraid, and fled, and went into Egypt.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 26:22"},"Then Jehoiakim the king sent men into Egypt, Elnathan the son of Achbor, and certain men with him, into Egypt;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 26:23"},"and they fetched Uriah out of Egypt, and brought him to Jehoiakim the king, who killed him with the sword, and cast his\ndead body into the graves of the common people. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 26:24"},"But the hand of Ahikam the son of Shaphan was with Jeremiah, so that they didn’t give him into the hand of the people to\nput him to death. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"27","sid":"JER 27"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 27:1"},"In the beginning of the reign of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah, this word came to Jeremiah from the LORD,\nsaying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 27:2"},"the LORD says to me: “Make bonds and bars, and put them on your neck.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 27:3"},"Then send them to the king of Edom, to the king of Moab, to the king of the children of Ammon, to the king of Tyre, and to\nthe king of Sidon, by the hand of the messengers who come to Jerusalem to Zedekiah king of Judah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 27:4"},"Give them a command to their masters, saying, ‘The LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel says, “You shall tell your masters:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 27:5"},"‘I have made the earth, the men, and the animals that are on the surface of the earth by my great power and by my\noutstretched arm. I give it to whom it seems right to me. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 27:6"},"Now I have given all these lands into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, my servant. I have also given the\nanimals of the field to him to serve him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 27:7"},"All the nations will serve him, his son, and his son’s son, until the time of his own land comes. Then many nations and\ngreat kings will make him their bondservant. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 27:8"},"“‘“‘It will happen that I will punish the nation and the kingdom which will not serve the same Nebuchadnezzar king of\nBabylon, and that will not put their neck under the yoke of the king of Babylon,’ says the LORD, ‘with the sword, with famine,\nand with pestilence, until I have consumed them by his hand. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 27:9"},"But as for you, don’t listen to your prophets, to your diviners, to your dreams, to your soothsayers, or to your\nsorcerers, who speak to you, saying, “You shall not serve the king of Babylon;”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 27:10"},"for they prophesy a lie to you, to remove you far from your land, so that I would drive you out, and you would perish.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 27:11"},"But the nation that brings their neck under the yoke of the king of Babylon and serves him, that nation I will let remain\nin their own land,’ says the LORD; ‘and they will till it and dwell in it.’”’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 27:12"},"I spoke to Zedekiah king of Judah according to all these words, saying, “Bring your necks under the yoke of the king of\nBabylon, and serve him and his people, and live. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 27:13"},"Why will you die, you and your people, by the sword, by the famine, and by the pestilence, as the LORD has spoken\nconcerning the nation that will not serve the king of Babylon? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 27:14"},"Don’t listen to the words of the prophets who speak to you, saying, ‘You shall not serve the king of Babylon;’ for they\nprophesy a lie to you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 27:15"},"For I have not sent them,” says the LORD, “but they prophesy falsely in my name; that I may drive you out, and that you\nmay perish, you, and the prophets who prophesy to you.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 27:16"},"Also I spoke to the priests and to all this people, saying, the LORD says, “Don’t listen to the words of your prophets\nwho prophesy to you, saying, ‘Behold, the vessels of the LORD’s house will now shortly be brought again from Babylon;’ for they\nprophesy a lie to you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 27:17"},"Don’t listen to them. Serve the king of Babylon, and live. Why should this city become a desolation?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 27:18"},"But if they are prophets, and if the LORD’s word is with them, let them now make intercession to the LORD of Armies, that\nthe vessels which are left in the LORD’s house, in the house of the king of Judah, and at Jerusalem, don’t go to Babylon.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 27:19"},"For the LORD of Armies says concerning the pillars, concerning the sea, concerning the bases, and concerning the rest of\nthe vessels that are left in this city, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 27:20"},"which Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon didn’t take when he carried away captive Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim, king of\nJudah, from Jerusalem to Babylon, and all the nobles of Judah and Jerusalem;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 27:21"},"yes, the LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says concerning the vessels that are left in the LORD’s house, and in the house\nof the king of Judah, and at Jerusalem: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 27:22"},"‘They will be carried to Babylon, and there they will be, until the day that I visit them,’ says the LORD; ‘then I will\nbring them up, and restore them to this place.’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"28","sid":"JER 28"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 28:1"},"That same year, in the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah king of Judah, in the fourth year, in the fifth month, Hananiah\nthe son of Azzur, the prophet, who was of Gibeon, spoke to me in the LORD’s house, in the presence of the priests and of all\nthe people, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 28:2"},"“The LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says, ‘I have broken the yoke of the king of Babylon.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 28:3"},"Within two full years I will bring again into this place all the vessels of the LORD’s house, that Nebuchadnezzar king of\nBabylon took away from this place, and carried to Babylon. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 28:4"},"I will bring again to this place Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, with all the captives of Judah, who went to\nBabylon,’ says the LORD; ‘for I will break the yoke of the king of Babylon.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 28:5"},"Then the prophet Jeremiah said to the prophet Hananiah in the presence of the priests, and in the presence of all the\npeople who stood in the LORD’s house, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 28:6"},"even the prophet Jeremiah said, “Amen! May the LORD do so. May the LORD perform your words which you have prophesied, to\nbring again the vessels of the LORD’s house, and all those who are captives, from Babylon to this place.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 28:7"},"Nevertheless listen now to this word that I speak in your ears, and in the ears of all the people:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 28:8"},"The prophets who have been before me and before you of old prophesied against many countries, and against great kingdoms,\nof war, of evil, and of pestilence. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 28:9"},"The prophet who prophesies of peace, when the word of the prophet happens, then the prophet will be known, that the LORD\nhas truly sent him.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 28:10"},"Then Hananiah the prophet took the bar from off the prophet Jeremiah’s neck, and broke it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 28:11"},"Hananiah spoke in the presence of all the people, saying, “The LORD says: ‘Even so I will break the yoke of\nNebuchadnezzar king of Babylon from off the neck of all the nations within two full years.’” Then the prophet Jeremiah went his\nway. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 28:12"},"Then the LORD’s word came to Jeremiah, after Hananiah the prophet had broken the bar from off the neck of the prophet\nJeremiah, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 28:13"},"“Go, and tell Hananiah, saying, ‘The LORD says, “You have broken the bars of wood, but you have made in their place bars\nof iron.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 28:14"},"For the LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel says, “I have put a yoke of iron on the neck of all these nations, that they may\nserve Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon; and they will serve him. I have also given him the animals of the field.”’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 28:15"},"Then the prophet Jeremiah said to Hananiah the prophet, “Listen, Hananiah! The LORD has not sent you, but you make this\npeople trust in a lie. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 28:16"},"Therefore the LORD says, ‘Behold, I will send you away from off the surface of the earth. This year you will die, because\nyou have spoken rebellion against the LORD.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 28:17"},"So Hananiah the prophet died the same year in the seventh month.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"29","sid":"JER 29"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 29:1"},"Now these are the words of the letter that Jeremiah the prophet sent from Jerusalem to the residue of the elders of the\ncaptivity, and to the priests, to the prophets, and to all the people whom Nebuchadnezzar had carried away captive from\nJerusalem to Babylon, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 29:2"},"(after Jeconiah the king, the queen mother, the eunuchs, the princes of Judah and Jerusalem, the craftsmen, and the\nsmiths, had departed from Jerusalem), \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 29:3"},"by the hand of Elasah the son of Shaphan, and Gemariah the son of Hilkiah, (whom Zedekiah king of Judah sent to Babylon to\nNebuchadnezzar king of Babylon). It said: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"pi1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 29:4"},"The LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says to all the captives whom I have caused to be carried away captive from Jerusalem\nto Babylon: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 29:5"},"“Build houses and dwell in them. Plant gardens and eat their fruit.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 29:6"},"Take wives and father sons and daughters. Take wives for your sons, and give your daughters to husbands, that they may\nbear sons and daughters. Multiply there, and don’t be diminished.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 29:7"},"Seek the peace of the city where I have caused you to be carried away captive, and pray to the LORD for it; for in its\npeace you will have peace.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 29:8"},"For the LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel says: “Don’t let your prophets who are amongst you and your diviners deceive you.\nDon’t listen to your dreams which you cause to be dreamt. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 29:9"},"For they prophesy falsely to you in my name. I have not sent them,” says the LORD.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 29:10"},"For the LORD says, “After seventy years are accomplished for Babylon, I will visit you and perform my good word towards\nyou, in causing you to return to this place. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 29:11"},"For I know the thoughts that I think towards you,” says the LORD, “thoughts of peace, and not of evil, to give you hope\nand a future. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 29:12"},"You shall call on me, and you shall go and pray to me, and I will listen to you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 29:13"},"You shall seek me, and find me, when you search for me with all your heart.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 29:14"},"I will be found by you,” says the LORD, “and I will turn again your captivity, and I will gather you from all the\nnations, and from all the places where I have driven you, says the LORD. I will bring you again to the place from where I\ncaused you to be carried away captive.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"pi1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 29:15"},"Because you have said, “The LORD has raised us up prophets in Babylon;”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 29:16"},"the LORD says concerning the king who sits on Dawood’s throne, and concerning all the people who dwell in this city, your\nbrothers who haven’t gone with you into captivity; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 29:17"},"the LORD of Armies says: “Behold, I will send on them the sword, the famine, and the pestilence, and will make them like\nrotten figs that can’t be eaten, they are so bad. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 29:18"},"I will pursue after them with the sword, with the famine, and with the pestilence, and will deliver them to be tossed\nback and forth amongst all the kingdoms of the earth, to be an object of horror, an astonishment, a hissing, and a reproach\namongst all the nations where I have driven them, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 29:19"},"because they have not listened to my words,” says the LORD, “with which I sent to them my servants the prophets, rising\nup early and sending them; but you would not hear,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"pi1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 29:20"},"Hear therefore the LORD’s word, all you captives, whom I have sent away from Jerusalem to Babylon.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 29:21"},"The LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says concerning Ahab the son of Kolaiah, and concerning Zedekiah the son of\nMaaseiah, who prophesy a lie to you in my name: “Behold, I will deliver them into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon;\nand he will kill them before your eyes. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 29:22"},"A curse will be taken up about them by all the captives of Judah who are in Babylon, saying, ‘The LORD make you like\nZedekiah and like Ahab, whom the king of Babylon roasted in the fire;’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 29:23"},"because they have done foolish things in Israel, and have committed adultery with their neighbours’ wives, and have\nspoken words in my name falsely, which I didn’t command them. I am he who knows, and am witness,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 29:24"},"Concerning Shemaiah the Nehelamite you shall speak, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 29:25"},"“The LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says, ‘Because you have sent letters in your own name to all the people who are at\nJerusalem, and to Zephaniah the son of Maaseiah, the priest, and to all the priests, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 29:26"},"“The LORD has made you priest in the place of Jehoiada the priest, that there may be officers in the LORD’s house, for\nevery man who is crazy, and makes himself a prophet, that you should put him in the stocks and in shackles.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 29:27"},"Now therefore, why have you not rebuked Jeremiah of Anathoth, who makes himself a prophet to you,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 29:28"},"because he has sent to us in Babylon, saying, The captivity is long. Build houses, and dwell in them. Plant gardens, and\neat their fruit?”’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JER 29:29"},"Zephaniah the priest read this letter in the hearing of Jeremiah the prophet.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JER 29:30"},"Then the LORD’s word came to Jeremiah, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JER 29:31"},"“Send to all of the captives, saying, ‘The LORD says concerning Shemaiah the Nehelamite: “Because Shemaiah has prophesied\nto you, and I didn’t send him, and he has caused you to trust in a lie;”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JER 29:32"},"therefore the LORD says, “Behold, I will punish Shemaiah the Nehelamite and his offspring. He will not have a man to\ndwell amongst this people. He won’t see the good that I will do to my people,” says the LORD, “because he has spoken rebellion\nagainst the LORD.”’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"30","sid":"JER 30"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 30:1"},"The word that came to Jeremiah from the LORD, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 30:2"},"“The LORD, Allah of Israel, says, ‘Write all the words that I have spoken to you in a book.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 30:3"},"For, behold, the days come,’ says the LORD, ‘that I will reverse the captivity of my people Israel and Judah,’ says the\nLORD. ‘I will cause them to return to the land that I gave to their fathers, and they will possess it.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 30:4"},"These are the words that the LORD spoke concerning Israel and concerning Judah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 30:5"},"For the LORD says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“We have heard a voice of trembling; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a voice of fear, and not of peace. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 30:6"},"Ask now, and see whether a man travails with child. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Why do I see every man with his hands on his waist, as a woman in travail,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all faces are turned pale? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 30:7"},"Alas! for that day is great, so that none is like it. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It is even the time of Yaqub’s trouble; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but he will be saved out of it. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 30:8"},"It will come to pass in that day, says the LORD of Armies, that I will break his yoke from off your neck,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will burst your bonds. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Strangers will no more make them their bondservants; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 30:9"},"but they will serve the LORD their Allah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and Dawood their king, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["whom I will raise up to them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 30:10"},"Therefore don’t be afraid, O Yaqub my servant, says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Don’t be dismayed, Israel. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For, behold, I will save you from afar, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and save your offspring from the land of their captivity. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Yaqub will return, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will be quiet and at ease. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["No one will make him afraid. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 30:11"},"For I am with you, says the LORD, to save you; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for I will make a full end of all the nations where I have scattered you,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but I will not make a full end of you; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["but I will correct you in measure, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will in no way leave you unpunished.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 30:12"},"For the LORD says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Your hurt is incurable. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your wound is grievous. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 30:13"},"There is no one to plead your cause, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that you may be bound up. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You have no healing medicines. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 30:14"},"All your lovers have forgotten you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They don’t seek you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For I have wounded you with the wound of an enemy, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with the chastisement of a cruel one, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for the greatness of your iniquity, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because your sins were increased. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 30:15"},"Why do you cry over your injury? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your pain is incurable. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For the greatness of your iniquity, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because your sins have increased, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have done these things to you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 30:16"},"Therefore all those who devour you will be devoured. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["All your adversaries, everyone of them, will go into captivity.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Those who plunder you will be plunder. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will make all who prey on you become prey. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 30:17"},"For I will restore health to you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will heal you of your wounds,” says the LORD; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“because they have called you an outcast, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["saying, ‘It is Zion, whom no man seeks after.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 30:18"},"The LORD says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, I will reverse the captivity of Yaqub’s tents, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and have compassion on his dwelling places. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The city will be built on its own hill, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the palace will be inhabited in its own place. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 30:19"},"Thanksgiving will proceed out of them \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with the voice of those who make merry. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will multiply them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will not be few; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will also glorify them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will not be small. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 30:20"},"Their children also will be as before, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their congregation will be established before me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will punish all who oppress them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 30:21"},"Their prince will be one of them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their ruler will proceed from amongst them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will cause him to draw near, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and he will approach me; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for who is he who has had boldness to approach me?” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 30:22"},"“You shall be my people, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will be your Allah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 30:23"},"Behold, the LORD’s storm, his wrath, has gone out, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a sweeping storm: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["it will burst on the head of the wicked. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 30:24"},"The fierce anger of the LORD will not return until he has accomplished,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and until he has performed the intentions of his heart. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["In the latter days you will understand it.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"31","sid":"JER 31"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 31:1"},"“At that time,” says the LORD, “I will be Allah of all the families of Israel, and they will be my people.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 31:2"},"The LORD says, “The people who survive the sword found favour in the wilderness; even Israel, when I went to cause him to\nrest.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 31:3"},"The LORD appeared of old to me, saying, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Yes, I have loved you with an everlasting love. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Therefore I have drawn you with loving kindness. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 31:4"},"I will build you again, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and you will be built, O virgin of Israel. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You will again be adorned with your tambourines, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will go out in the dances of those who make merry. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 31:5"},"Again you will plant vineyards on the mountains of Samaria.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The planters will plant, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will enjoy its fruit. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 31:6"},"For there will be a day that the watchmen on the hills of Ephraim cry,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘Arise! Let’s go up to Zion to the LORD our Allah.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 31:7"},"For the LORD says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Sing with gladness for Yaqub, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and shout for the chief of the nations. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Publish, praise, and say, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘The LORD, save your people, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the remnant of Israel!’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 31:8"},"Behold, I will bring them from the north country, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and gather them from the uttermost parts of the earth, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["along with the blind and the lame, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the woman with child and her who travails with child together.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They will return as a great company. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 31:9"},"They will come with weeping. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will lead them with petitions. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will cause them to walk by rivers of waters, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in a straight way in which they won’t stumble; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for I am a father to Israel. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Ephraim is my firstborn. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 31:10"},"“Hear the LORD’s word, you nations, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and declare it in the distant islands. Say, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘He who scattered Israel will gather him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and keep him, as a shepherd does his flock.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 31:11"},"For the LORD has ransomed Yaqub, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and redeemed him from the hand of him who was stronger than he.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 31:12"},"They will come and sing in the height of Zion, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will flow to the goodness of the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["to the grain, to the new wine, to the oil, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and to the young of the flock and of the herd. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Their soul will be as a watered garden. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They will not sorrow any more at all. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 31:13"},"Then the virgin will rejoice in the dance; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the young men and the old together; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for I will turn their mourning into joy, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will comfort them, and make them rejoice from their sorrow.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 31:14"},"I will satiate the soul of the priests with fatness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and my people will be satisfied with my goodness,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 31:15"},"The LORD says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“A voice is heard in Ramah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["lamentation and bitter weeping, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Rachel weeping for her children. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["She refuses to be comforted for her children, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because they are no more.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 31:16"},"The LORD says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Refrain your voice from weeping, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your eyes from tears; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for your work will be rewarded,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“They will come again from the land of the enemy. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 31:17"},"There is hope for your latter end,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Your children will come again to their own territory. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 31:18"},"“I have surely heard Ephraim grieving thus, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘You have chastised me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I was chastised, as an untrained calf. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Turn me, and I will be turned; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for you are the LORD my Allah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 31:19"},"Surely after that I was turned. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I repented. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["After that I was instructed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I struck my thigh. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I was ashamed, yes, even confounded, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because I bore the reproach of my youth.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 31:20"},"Is Ephraim my dear son? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Is he a darling child? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For as often as I speak against him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I still earnestly remember him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["therefore my heart yearns for him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will surely have mercy on him,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 31:21"},"“Set up road signs. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Make guideposts. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Set your heart towards the highway, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even the way by which you went. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Turn again, virgin of Israel. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Turn again to these your cities. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 31:22"},"How long will you go here and there, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you backsliding daughter? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For the LORD has created a new thing in the earth: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a woman will encompass a man.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 31:23"},"The LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says: “Yet again they will use this speech in the land of Judah and in its cities,\nwhen I reverse their captivity: ‘The LORD bless you, habitation of righteousness, mountain of holiness.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 31:24"},"Judah and all its cities will dwell therein together, the farmers, and those who go about with flocks.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 31:25"},"For I have satiated the weary soul, and I have replenished every sorrowful soul.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 31:26"},"On this I awakened, and saw; and my sleep was sweet to me.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 31:27"},"“Behold, the days come,” says the LORD, “that I will sow the house of Israel and the house of Judah with the seed of man\nand with the seed of animal. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 31:28"},"It will happen that, like as I have watched over them to pluck up and to break down and to overthrow and to destroy and\nto afflict, so I will watch over them to build and to plant,” says the LORD.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JER 31:29"},"“In those days they will say no more, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“‘The fathers have eaten sour grapes, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the children’s teeth are set on edge.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JER 31:30"},"But everyone will die for his own iniquity. Every man who eats the sour grapes, his teeth will be set on edge.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JER 31:31"},"“Behold, the days come,” says the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“that I will make a new covenant with the house of Israel, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and with the house of Judah: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JER 31:32"},"not according to the covenant that I made with their fathers in the day that I took them by the hand to bring them out of\nthe land of Egypt; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["which covenant of mine they broke, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["although I was a husband to them,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JER 31:33"},"“But this is the covenant that I will make with the house of Israel after those days,”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["says the LORD: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“I will put my law in their inward parts, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will write it in their heart. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will be their Allah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they shall be my people. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JER 31:34"},"They will no longer each teach his neighbour, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and every man teach his brother, saying, ‘Know the LORD;’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for they will all know me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from their least to their greatest,” says the LORD: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“for I will forgive their iniquity, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will remember their sin no more.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JER 31:35"},"The LORD, who gives the sun for a light by day, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the ordinances of the moon and of the stars for a light by night,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["who stirs up the sea, so that its waves roar; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the LORD of Armies is his name, says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JER 31:36"},"“If these ordinances depart from before me,” says the LORD,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“then the offspring of Israel also will cease from being a nation before me forever.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JER 31:37"},"The LORD says: “If heaven above can be measured, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the foundations of the earth searched out beneath, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["then I will also cast off all the offspring of Israel for all that they have done,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JER 31:38"},"“Behold, the days come,” says the LORD, “that the city will be built to the LORD from the tower of Hananel to the gate of\nthe corner. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JER 31:39"},"The measuring line will go out further straight onward to the hill Gareb, and will turn towards Goah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"JER 31:40"},"The whole valley of the dead bodies and of the ashes, and all the fields to the brook Kidron, to the corner of the horse\ngate towards the east, will be holy to the LORD. It will not be plucked up or thrown down any more forever.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"32","sid":"JER 32"},{"type":"para","marker":"nb","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 32:1"},"The word that came to Jeremiah from the LORD in the tenth year of Zedekiah king of Judah, which was the eighteenth year of\nNebuchadnezzar. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 32:2"},"Now at that time the king of Babylon’s army was besieging Jerusalem. Jeremiah the prophet was shut up in the court of the\nguard, which was in the king of Judah’s house. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 32:3"},"For Zedekiah king of Judah had shut him up, saying, “Why do you prophesy, and say, ‘The LORD says, “Behold, I will give\nthis city into the hand of the king of Babylon, and he will take it;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 32:4"},"and Zedekiah king of Judah won’t escape out of the hand of the Chaldeans, but will surely be delivered into the hand of\nthe king of Babylon, and will speak with him mouth to mouth, and his eyes will see his eyes;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 32:5"},"and he will bring Zedekiah to Babylon, and he will be there until I visit him,” says the LORD: “though you fight with the\nChaldeans, you will not prosper?”’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 32:6"},"Jeremiah said, “The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 32:7"},"‘Behold, Hanamel the son of Shallum your uncle will come to you, saying, “Buy my field that is in Anathoth; for the right\nof redemption is yours to buy it.”’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 32:8"},"“So Hanamel my uncle’s son came to me in the court of the guard according to the LORD’s word, and said to me, ‘Please buy\nmy field that is in Anathoth, which is in the land of Benjamin; for the right of inheritance is yours, and the redemption is\nyours. Buy it for yourself.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Then I knew that this was the LORD’s word. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 32:9"},"I bought the field that was in Anathoth of Hanamel my uncle’s son, and weighed him the money, even seventeen\nshekels",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["32:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35\nounces."]}],"caller":"+"}," of silver. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 32:10"},"I signed the deed, sealed it, called witnesses, and weighed the money in the balances to him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 32:11"},"So I took the deed of the purchase, both that which was sealed, containing the terms and conditions, and that which was\nopen; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 32:12"},"and I delivered the deed of the purchase to Baruch the son of Neriah, the son of Mahseiah, in the presence of Hanamel my\nuncle’s son, and in the presence of the witnesses who signed the deed of the purchase, before all the Jews who sat in the court\nof the guard. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 32:13"},"“I commanded Baruch before them, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 32:14"},"the LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel says: ‘Take these deeds, this deed of the purchase which is sealed, and this deed\nwhich is open, and put them in an earthen vessel, that they may last many days.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 32:15"},"For the LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel says: ‘Houses and fields and vineyards will yet again be bought in this land.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 32:16"},"Now after I had delivered the deed of the purchase to Baruch the son of Neriah, I prayed to the LORD, saying,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"mi","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 32:17"},"“Ah Lord ALLAH! Behold, you have made the heavens and the earth by your great power and by your outstretched arm. There\nis nothing too hard for you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 32:18"},"You show loving kindness to thousands, and repay the iniquity of the fathers into the bosom of their children after them.\nThe great, the mighty Allah, the LORD of Armies is your name: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 32:19"},"great in counsel, and mighty in work; whose eyes are open to all the ways of the children of men, to give everyone\naccording to his ways, and according to the fruit of his doings;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 32:20"},"who performed signs and wonders in the land of Egypt, even to this day, both in Israel and amongst other men; and made\nyourself a name, as it is today; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 32:21"},"and brought your people Israel out of the land of Egypt with signs, with wonders, with a strong hand, with an\noutstretched arm, and with great terror; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 32:22"},"and gave them this land, which you swore to their fathers to give them, a land flowing with milk and honey.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 32:23"},"They came in and possessed it, but they didn’t obey your voice and didn’t walk in your law. They have done nothing of all\nthat you commanded them to do. Therefore you have caused all this evil to come upon them.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"pi1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 32:24"},"“Behold, siege ramps have come to the city to take it. The city is given into the hand of the Chaldeans who fight against\nit, because of the sword, of the famine, and of the pestilence. What you have spoken has happened. Behold, you see it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 32:25"},"You have said to me, Lord ALLAH, ‘Buy the field for money, and call witnesses;’ whereas the city is given into the hand\nof the Chaldeans.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 32:26"},"Then the LORD’s word came to Jeremiah, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 32:27"},"“Behold, I am the LORD, Allah of all flesh. Is there anything too hard for me?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 32:28"},"Therefore the LORD says: Behold, I will give this city into the hand of the Chaldeans, and into the hand of\nNebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, and he will take it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JER 32:29"},"The Chaldeans, who fight against this city, will come and set this city on fire, and burn it with the houses on whose\nroofs they have offered incense to Baal, and poured out drink offerings to other gods, to provoke me to anger.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JER 32:30"},"“For the children of Israel and the children of Judah have done only that which was evil in my sight from their youth;\nfor the children of Israel have only provoked me to anger with the work of their hands, says the LORD.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JER 32:31"},"For this city has been to me a provocation of my anger and of my wrath from the day that they built it even to this day,\nso that I should remove it from before my face, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JER 32:32"},"because of all the evil of the children of Israel and of the children of Judah, which they have done to provoke me to\nanger: they, their kings, their princes, their priests, their prophets, the men of Judah, and the inhabitants of Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JER 32:33"},"They have turned their backs to me, and not their faces. Although I taught them, rising up early and teaching them, yet\nthey have not listened to receive instruction. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JER 32:34"},"But they set their abominations in the house which is called by my name, to defile it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JER 32:35"},"They built the high places of Baal, which are in the valley of the son of Hinnom, to cause their sons and their daughters\nto pass through fire to Molech, which I didn’t command them. It didn’t even come into my mind, that they should do this\nabomination, to cause Judah to sin.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JER 32:36"},"Now therefore the LORD, Allah of Israel, says concerning this city, about which you say, “It is given into the hand of\nthe king of Babylon by the sword, by the famine, and by the pestilence:”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JER 32:37"},"“Behold, I will gather them out of all the countries where I have driven them in my anger, and in my wrath, and in great\nindignation; and I will bring them again to this place. I will cause them to dwell safely.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JER 32:38"},"Then they will be my people, and I will be their Allah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JER 32:39"},"I will give them one heart and one way, that they may fear me forever, for their good, and the good of their children\nafter them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"JER 32:40"},"I will make an everlasting covenant with them, that I will not turn away from following them, to do them good. I will put\nmy fear in their hearts, that they may not depart from me. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"JER 32:41"},"Yes, I will rejoice over them to do them good, and I will plant them in this land assuredly with my whole heart and with\nmy whole soul.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"JER 32:42"},"For the LORD says: “Just as I have brought all this great evil on this people, so I will bring on them all the good that\nI have promised them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"JER 32:43"},"Fields will be bought in this land, about which you say, ‘It is desolate, without man or animal. It is given into the\nhand of the Chaldeans.’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"JER 32:44"},"Men will buy fields for money, sign the deeds, seal them, and call witnesses, in the land of Benjamin, and in the places\naround Jerusalem, in the cities of Judah, in the cities of the hill country, in the cities of the lowland, and in the cities of\nthe South; for I will cause their captivity to be reversed,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"33","sid":"JER 33"},{"type":"para","marker":"nb","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 33:1"},"Moreover the LORD’s word came to Jeremiah the second time, while he was still locked up in the court of the guard, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 33:2"},"“The LORD who does it, the LORD who forms it to establish it—the LORD is his name, says:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 33:3"},"‘Call to me, and I will answer you, and will show you great and difficult things, which you don’t know.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 33:4"},"For the LORD, Allah of Israel, says concerning the houses of this city and concerning the houses of the kings of Judah,\nwhich are broken down to make a defence against the mounds and against the sword;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 33:5"},"while men come to fight with the Chaldeans, and to fill them with the dead bodies of men, whom I have killed in my anger\nand in my wrath, and for all whose wickedness I have hidden my face from this city:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 33:6"},"‘Behold, I will bring it health and cure, and I will cure them; and I will reveal to them abundance of peace and truth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 33:7"},"I will cause the captivity of Judah and the captivity of Israel to return, and will build them, as at the first.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 33:8"},"I will cleanse them from all their iniquity by which they have sinned against me. I will pardon all their iniquities by\nwhich they have sinned against me and by which they have transgressed against me.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 33:9"},"This city will be to me for a name of joy, for praise, and for glory, before all the nations of the earth, which will hear\nall the good that I do to them, and will fear and tremble for all the good and for all the peace that I provide to it.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 33:10"},"The LORD says: “Yet again there will be heard in this place, about which you say, ‘It is waste, without man and without\nanimal, even in the cities of Judah, and in the streets of Jerusalem, that are desolate, without man and without inhabitant and\nwithout animal,’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 33:11"},"the voice of joy and the voice of gladness, the voice of the bridegroom and the voice of the bride, the voice of those\nwho say, ‘Give thanks to the LORD of Armies, for the LORD is good, for his loving kindness endures forever;’ who bring\nthanksgiving into the LORD’s house. For I will cause the captivity of the land to be reversed as at the first,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 33:12"},"The LORD of Armies says: “Yet again there will be in this place, which is waste, without man and without animal, and in\nall its cities, a habitation of shepherds causing their flocks to lie down.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 33:13"},"In the cities of the hill country, in the cities of the lowland, in the cities of the South, in the land of Benjamin, in\nthe places around Jerusalem, and in the cities of Judah, the flocks will again pass under the hands of him who counts them,”\nsays the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 33:14"},"“Behold, the days come,” says the LORD, “that I will perform that good word which I have spoken concerning the house of\nIsrael and concerning the house of Judah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 33:15"},"“In those days and at that time, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will cause a Branch of righteousness to grow up to Dawood.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He will execute justice and righteousness in the land. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 33:16"},"In those days Judah will be saved, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and Jerusalem will dwell safely. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["This is the name by which she will be called: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The LORD our righteousness.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 33:17"},"For the LORD says: “Dawood will never lack a man to sit on the throne of the house of Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 33:18"},"The Levitical priests won’t lack a man before me to offer burnt offerings, to burn meal offerings, and to do sacrifice\ncontinually.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 33:19"},"The LORD’s word came to Jeremiah, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 33:20"},"“The LORD says: ‘If you can break my covenant of the day and my covenant of the night, so that there will not be day and\nnight in their time; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 33:21"},"then may my covenant also be broken with Dawood my servant, that he won’t have a son to reign on his throne; and with the\nLevites the priests, my ministers. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 33:22"},"As the army of the sky can’t be counted, and the sand of the sea can’t be measured; so I will multiply the offspring of\nDawood my servant and the Levites who minister to me.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 33:23"},"The LORD’s word came to Jeremiah, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 33:24"},"“Don’t consider what this people has spoken, saying, ‘Has the LORD cast off the two families which he chose?’ Thus they\ndespise my people, that they should be no more a nation before them.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 33:25"},"The LORD says: “If my covenant of day and night fails, if I have not appointed the ordinances of heaven and earth;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 33:26"},"then I will also cast away the offspring of Yaqub, and of Dawood my servant, so that I will not take of his offspring to\nbe rulers over the offspring of Ibrahim, Isḥāq, and Yaqub: for I will cause their captivity to be reversed and will have mercy\non them.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"34","sid":"JER 34"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 34:1"},"The word which came to Jeremiah from the LORD, when Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, with all his army, all the kingdoms of\nthe earth that were under his dominion, and all the peoples, were fighting against Jerusalem and against all its cities,\nsaying: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 34:2"},"“The LORD, Allah of Israel, says, ‘Go, and speak to Zedekiah king of Judah, and tell him, the LORD says, “Behold, I will\ngive this city into the hand of the king of Babylon and he will burn it with fire.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 34:3"},"You won’t escape out of his hand, but will surely be taken and delivered into his hand. Your eyes will see the eyes of the\nking of Babylon, and he will speak with you mouth to mouth. You will go to Babylon.”’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 34:4"},"“Yet hear the LORD’s word, O Zedekiah king of Judah: The LORD says concerning you, ‘You won’t die by the sword.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 34:5"},"You will die in peace; and with the burnings of your fathers, the former kings who were before you, so they will make a\nburning for you. They will lament you, saying, “Ah Lord!” for I have spoken the word,’ says the LORD.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 34:6"},"Then Jeremiah the prophet spoke all these words to Zedekiah king of Judah in Jerusalem,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 34:7"},"when the king of Babylon’s army was fighting against Jerusalem, and against all the cities of Judah that were left,\nagainst Lachish and against Azekah; for these alone remained of the cities of Judah as fortified cities.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 34:8"},"The word came to Jeremiah from the LORD, after king Zedekiah had made a covenant with all the people who were at\nJerusalem, to proclaim liberty to them; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 34:9"},"that every man should let his male servant, and every man his female servant, who is a Hebrew or a Hebrewess, go free;\nthat no one should make bondservants of them, of a Jew his brother.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 34:10"},"All the princes and all the people obeyed who had entered into the covenant, that everyone should let his male servant,\nand everyone his female servant go free, that no one should make bondservants of them any more. They obeyed and let them go;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 34:11"},"but afterwards they turned, and caused the servants and the handmaids, whom they had let go free, to return, and brought\nthem into subjection for servants and for handmaids. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 34:12"},"Therefore the LORD’s word came to Jeremiah from the LORD, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 34:13"},"“The LORD, Allah of Israel, says: ‘I made a covenant with your fathers in the day that I brought them out of the land of\nEgypt, out of the house of bondage, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 34:14"},"At the end of seven years, every man of you shall release his brother who is a Hebrew, who has been sold to you, and has\nserved you six years. You shall let him go free from you; but your fathers didn’t listen to me, and didn’t incline their ear.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 34:15"},"You had now turned, and had done that which is right in my eyes, in every man proclaiming liberty to his neighbour. You\nhad made a covenant before me in the house which is called by my name;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 34:16"},"but you turned and profaned my name, and every man caused his servant, and every man his handmaid, whom you had let go\nfree at their pleasure, to return. You brought them into subjection, to be to you for servants and for handmaids.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 34:17"},"Therefore the LORD says: “You have not listened to me, to proclaim liberty, every man to his brother, and every man to\nhis neighbour. Behold, I proclaim to you a liberty,” says the LORD, “to the sword, to the pestilence, and to the famine. I will\nmake you be tossed back and forth amongst all the kingdoms of the earth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 34:18"},"I will give the men who have transgressed my covenant, who have not performed the words of the covenant which they made\nbefore me, when they cut the calf in two and passed between its parts:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 34:19"},"the princes of Judah, the princes of Jerusalem, the eunuchs, the priests, and all the people of the land, who passed\nbetween the parts of the calf; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 34:20"},"I will even give them into the hand of their enemies, and into the hand of those who seek their life. Their dead bodies\nwill be food for the birds of the sky and for the animals of the earth.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 34:21"},"“I will give Zedekiah king of Judah and his princes into the hands of their enemies, into the hands of those who seek\ntheir life and into the hands of the king of Babylon’s army, who has gone away from you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 34:22"},"Behold, I will command,” says the LORD, “and cause them to return to this city. They will fight against it, take it, and\nburn it with fire. I will make the cities of Judah a desolation, without inhabitant.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"35","sid":"JER 35"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 35:1"},"The word which came to Jeremiah from the LORD in the days of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 35:2"},"“Go to the house of the Rechabites, and speak to them, and bring them into the LORD’s house, into one of the rooms, and\ngive them wine to drink.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 35:3"},"Then I took Jaazaniah the son of Jeremiah, the son of Habazziniah, with his brothers, all his sons, and the whole house of\nthe Rechabites; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 35:4"},"and I brought them into the LORD’s house, into the room of the sons of Hanan the son of Igdaliah, the man of Allah, which\nwas by the room of the princes, which was above the room of Maaseiah the son of Shallum, the keeper of the threshold.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 35:5"},"I set before the sons of the house of the Rechabites bowls full of wine, and cups; and I said to them, “Drink wine!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 35:6"},"But they said, “We will drink no wine; for Jonadab the son of Rechab, our father, commanded us, saying, ‘You shall drink\nno wine, neither you, nor your sons, forever. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 35:7"},"You shall not build a house, sow seed, plant a vineyard, or have any; but all your days you shall dwell in tents, that you\nmay live many days in the land in which you live as nomads.’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 35:8"},"We have obeyed the voice of Jonadab the son of Rechab, our father, in all that he commanded us, to drink no wine all our\ndays, we, our wives, our sons, or our daughters; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 35:9"},"and not to build houses for ourselves to dwell in. We have no vineyard, field, or seed;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 35:10"},"but we have lived in tents, and have obeyed, and done according to all that Jonadab our father commanded us.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 35:11"},"But when Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up into the land, we said, ‘Come! Let’s go to Jerusalem for fear of the army\nof the Chaldeans, and for fear of the army of the Syrians; so we will dwell at Jerusalem.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 35:12"},"Then the LORD’s word came to Jeremiah, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 35:13"},"“The LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says: ‘Go and tell the men of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem, “Will you not\nreceive instruction to listen to my words?” says the LORD. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 35:14"},"“The words of Jonadab the son of Rechab that he commanded his sons, not to drink wine, are performed; and to this day\nthey drink none, for they obey their father’s commandment; but I have spoken to you, rising up early and speaking, and you have\nnot listened to me. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 35:15"},"I have sent also to you all my servants the prophets, rising up early and sending them, saying, ‘Every one of you must\nreturn now from his evil way, amend your doings, and don’t go after other gods to serve them, then you will dwell in the land\nwhich I have given to you and to your fathers:’ but you have not inclined your ear, nor listened to me.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 35:16"},"The sons of Jonadab the son of Rechab have performed the commandment of their father which he commanded them, but this\npeople has not listened to me.”’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 35:17"},"“Therefore the LORD, Allah of Armies, Allah of Israel, says: ‘Behold, I will bring on Judah and on all the inhabitants of\nJerusalem all the evil that I have pronounced against them; because I have spoken to them, but they have not heard; and I have\ncalled to them, but they have not answered.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 35:18"},"Jeremiah said to the house of the Rechabites, “The LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says: ‘Because you have obeyed the\ncommandment of Jonadab your father, and kept all his precepts, and done according to all that he commanded you;’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 35:19"},"therefore the LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says: ‘Jonadab the son of Rechab will not lack a man to stand before me\nforever.’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"36","sid":"JER 36"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 36:1"},"In the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah, this word came to Jeremiah from the LORD, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 36:2"},"“Take a scroll of a book, and write in it all the words that I have spoken to you against Israel, and against Judah, and\nagainst all the nations, from the day I spoke to you, from the days of Josiah, even to this day.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 36:3"},"It may be that the house of Judah will hear all the evil which I intend to do to them; that they may each return from his\nevil way; that I may forgive their iniquity and their sin.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 36:4"},"Then Jeremiah called Baruch the son of Neriah; and Baruch wrote from the mouth of Jeremiah all the LORD’s words, which he\nhad spoken to him, on a scroll of a book. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 36:5"},"Jeremiah commanded Baruch, saying, “I am restricted. I can’t go into the LORD’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 36:6"},"Therefore you go, and read from the scroll which you have written from my mouth, the LORD’s words, in the ears of the\npeople in the LORD’s house on the fast day. Also you shall read them in the ears of all Judah who come out of their cities.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 36:7"},"It may be they will present their supplication before the LORD, and will each return from his evil way; for the LORD has\npronounced great anger and wrath against this people.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 36:8"},"Baruch the son of Neriah did according to all that Jeremiah the prophet commanded him, reading in the book the LORD’s\nwords in the LORD’s house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 36:9"},"Now in the fifth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah, in the ninth month, all the people in Jerusalem, and\nall the people who came from the cities of Judah to Jerusalem, proclaimed a fast before the LORD.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 36:10"},"Then Baruch read the words of Jeremiah from the book in the LORD’s house, in the room of Gemariah the son of Shaphan, the\nscribe, in the upper court, at the entry of the new gate of the LORD’s house, in the ears of all the people.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 36:11"},"When Micaiah the son of Gemariah, the son of Shaphan, had heard out of the book all the LORD’s words,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 36:12"},"he went down into the king’s house, into the scribe’s room: and behold, all the princes were sitting there, Elishama the\nscribe, Delaiah the son of Shemaiah, Elnathan the son of Achbor, Gemariah the son of Shaphan, Zedekiah the son of Hananiah, and\nall the princes. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 36:13"},"Then Micaiah declared to them all the words that he had heard, when Baruch read the book in the ears of the people.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 36:14"},"Therefore all the princes sent Jehudi the son of Nethaniah, the son of Shelemiah, the son of Cushi, to Baruch, saying,\n“Take in your hand the scroll in which you have read in the ears of the people, and come.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So Baruch the son of Neriah took the scroll in his hand, and came to them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 36:15"},"They said to him, “Sit down now, and read it in our hearing.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So Baruch read it in their hearing. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 36:16"},"Now when they had heard all the words, they turned in fear one towards another, and said to Baruch, “We will surely tell\nthe king of all these words.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 36:17"},"They asked Baruch, saying, “Tell us now, how did you write all these words at his mouth?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 36:18"},"Then Baruch answered them, “He dictated all these words to me with his mouth, and I wrote them with ink in the book.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 36:19"},"Then the princes said to Baruch, “You and Jeremiah go hide. Don’t let anyone know where you are.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 36:20"},"They went in to the king into the court; but they had laid up the scroll in the room of Elishama the scribe. Then they\ntold all the words in the hearing of the king. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 36:21"},"So the king sent Jehudi to get the scroll; and he took it out of the room of Elishama the scribe. Jehudi read it in the\nhearing of the king, and in the hearing of all the princes who stood beside the king.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 36:22"},"Now the king was sitting in the winter house in the ninth month; and there was a fire in the brazier burning before him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 36:23"},"When Jehudi had read three or four leaves, the king cut it with the penknife, and cast it into the fire that was in the\nbrazier, until all the scroll was consumed in the fire that was in the brazier.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 36:24"},"The king and his servants who heard all these words were not afraid, and didn’t tear their garments.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 36:25"},"Moreover Elnathan and Delaiah and Gemariah had made intercession to the king that he would not burn the scroll; but he\nwould not listen to them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 36:26"},"The king commanded Jerahmeel the king’s son, and Seraiah the son of Azriel, and Shelemiah the son of Abdeel, to arrest\nBaruch the scribe and Jeremiah the prophet; but the LORD hid them.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 36:27"},"Then the LORD’s word came to Jeremiah, after the king had burnt the scroll, and the words which Baruch wrote at the mouth\nof Jeremiah, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 36:28"},"“Take again another scroll, and write in it all the former words that were in the first scroll, which Jehoiakim the king\nof Judah has burnt. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JER 36:29"},"Concerning Jehoiakim king of Judah you shall say, ‘The LORD says: “You have burnt this scroll, saying, “Why have you\nwritten therein, saying, ‘The king of Babylon will certainly come and destroy this land, and will cause to cease from there man\nand animal?’”’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JER 36:30"},"Therefore the LORD says concerning Jehoiakim king of Judah: “He will have no one to sit on Dawood’s throne. His dead body\nwill be cast out in the day to the heat, and in the night to the frost.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JER 36:31"},"I will punish him, his offspring, and his servants for their iniquity. I will bring on them, on the inhabitants of\nJerusalem, and on the men of Judah, all the evil that I have pronounced against them, but they didn’t listen.”’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JER 36:32"},"Then took Jeremiah another scroll, and gave it to Baruch the scribe, the son of Neriah, who wrote therein from the mouth\nof Jeremiah all the words of the book which Jehoiakim king of Judah had burnt in the fire; and many similar words were added to\nthem. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"37","sid":"JER 37"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 37:1"},"Zedekiah the son of Josiah reigned as king, instead of Coniah the son of Jehoiakim, whom Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon\nmade king in the land of Judah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 37:2"},"But neither he, nor his servants, nor the people of the land, listened to the LORD’s words, which he spoke by the prophet\nJeremiah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 37:3"},"Zedekiah the king sent Jehucal the son of Shelemiah, and Zephaniah the son of Maaseiah, the priest, to the prophet\nJeremiah, saying, “Pray now to the LORD our Allah for us.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 37:4"},"Now Jeremiah came in and went out amongst the people; for they had not put him into prison.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 37:5"},"Pharaoh’s army had come out of Egypt; and when the Chaldeans who were besieging Jerusalem heard news of them, they broke\nup from Jerusalem. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 37:6"},"Then the LORD’s word came to the prophet Jeremiah, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 37:7"},"“The LORD, Allah of Israel, says, ‘You shall tell the king of Judah, who sent you to me to enquire of me: “Behold,\nPharaoh’s army, which has come out to help you, will return to Egypt into their own land.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 37:8"},"The Chaldeans will come again, and fight against this city. They will take it and burn it with fire.”’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 37:9"},"“The LORD says, ‘Don’t deceive yourselves, saying, “The Chaldeans will surely depart from us;” for they will not depart.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 37:10"},"For though you had struck the whole army of the Chaldeans who fight against you, and only wounded men remained amongst\nthem, they would each rise up in his tent and burn this city with fire.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 37:11"},"When the army of the Chaldeans had broken up from Jerusalem for fear of Pharaoh’s army,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 37:12"},"then Jeremiah went out of Jerusalem to go into the land of Benjamin, to receive his portion there, in the middle of the\npeople. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 37:13"},"When he was in Benjamin’s gate, a captain of the guard was there, whose name was Irijah, the son of Shelemiah, the son of\nHananiah; and he seized Jeremiah the prophet, saying, “You are defecting to the Chaldeans!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 37:14"},"Then Jeremiah said, “That is false! I am not defecting to the Chaldeans.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But he didn’t listen to him; so Irijah seized Jeremiah, and brought him to the princes.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 37:15"},"The princes were angry with Jeremiah, and struck him, and put him in prison in the house of Jonathan the scribe; for they\nhad made that the prison. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 37:16"},"When Jeremiah had come into the dungeon house, and into the cells, and Jeremiah had remained there many days,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 37:17"},"then Zedekiah the king sent, and had him brought out. The king asked him secretly in his house, “Is there any word from\nthe LORD?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Jeremiah said, “There is.” He also said, “You will be delivered into the hand of the king of Babylon.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 37:18"},"Moreover Jeremiah said to king Zedekiah, “How have I sinned against you, against your servants, or against this people,\nthat you have put me in prison? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 37:19"},"Now where are your prophets who prophesied to you, saying, ‘The king of Babylon will not come against you, nor against\nthis land?’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 37:20"},"Now please hear, my lord the king: please let my supplication be presented before you, that you not cause me to return to\nthe house of Jonathan the scribe, lest I die there.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 37:21"},"Then Zedekiah the king commanded, and they committed Jeremiah into the court of the guard. They gave him daily a loaf of\nbread out of the bakers’ street, until all the bread in the city was gone. Thus Jeremiah remained in the court of the guard.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"38","sid":"JER 38"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 38:1"},"Shephatiah the son of Mattan, and Gedaliah the son of Pashhur, and Jucal the son of Shelemiah, and Pashhur the son of\nMalchijah, heard the words that Jeremiah spoke to all the people, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 38:2"},"“The LORD says, ‘He who remains in this city will die by the sword, by the famine, and by the pestilence; but he who goes\nout to the Chaldeans will live, and he will escape with his life, and he will live.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 38:3"},"The LORD says, ‘This city will surely be given into the hand of the army of the king of Babylon, and he will take it.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 38:4"},"Then the princes said to the king, “Please let this man be put to death; because he weakens the hands of the men of war\nwho remain in this city, and the hands of all the people, in speaking such words to them: for this man doesn’t seek the welfare\nof this people, but harm.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 38:5"},"Zedekiah the king said, “Behold, he is in your hand; for the king can’t do anything to oppose you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 38:6"},"Then they took Jeremiah and threw him into the dungeon of Malchijah the king’s son, that was in the court of the guard.\nThey let down Jeremiah with cords. In the dungeon there was no water, but mire; and Jeremiah sank in the mire.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 38:7"},"Now when Ebedmelech the Ethiopian, a eunuch, who was in the king’s house, heard that they had put Jeremiah in the dungeon\n(the king was then sitting in Benjamin’s gate), \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 38:8"},"Ebedmelech went out of the king’s house, and spoke to the king, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 38:9"},"“My lord the king, these men have done evil in all that they have done to Jeremiah the prophet, whom they have cast into\nthe dungeon. He is likely to die in the place where he is, because of the famine; for there is no more bread in the city.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 38:10"},"Then the king commanded Ebedmelech the Ethiopian, saying, “Take from here thirty men with you, and take up Jeremiah the\nprophet out of the dungeon, before he dies.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 38:11"},"So Ebedmelech took the men with him, and went into the house of the king under the treasury, and took from there rags and\nworn-out garments, and let them down by cords into the dungeon to Jeremiah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 38:12"},"Ebedmelech the Ethiopian said to Jeremiah, “Now put these rags and worn-out garments under your armpits under the cords.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Jeremiah did so. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 38:13"},"So they drew up Jeremiah with the cords, and took him up out of the dungeon; and Jeremiah remained in the court of the\nguard. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 38:14"},"Then Zedekiah the king sent and took Jeremiah the prophet to himself into the third entry that is in the LORD’s house.\nThen the king said to Jeremiah, “I will ask you something. Hide nothing from me.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 38:15"},"Then Jeremiah said to Zedekiah, “If I declare it to you, will you not surely put me to death? If I give you counsel, you\nwill not listen to me.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 38:16"},"So Zedekiah the king swore secretly to Jeremiah, saying, “As the LORD lives, who made us this soul, I will not put you to\ndeath, neither will I give you into the hand of these men who seek your life.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 38:17"},"Then Jeremiah said to Zedekiah, “The LORD, Allah of Armies, Allah of Israel, says: ‘If you will go out to the king of\nBabylon’s princes, then your soul will live, and this city will not be burnt with fire. You will live, along with your house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 38:18"},"But if you will not go out to the king of Babylon’s princes, then this city will be given into the hand of the Chaldeans,\nand they will burn it with fire, and you won’t escape out of their hand.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 38:19"},"Zedekiah the king said to Jeremiah, “I am afraid of the Jews who have defected to the Chaldeans, lest they deliver me\ninto their hand, and they mock me.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 38:20"},"But Jeremiah said, “They won’t deliver you. Obey, I beg you, the LORD’s voice, in that which I speak to you; so it will\nbe well with you, and your soul will live. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 38:21"},"But if you refuse to go out, this is the word that the LORD has shown me:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 38:22"},"‘Behold, all the women who are left in the king of Judah’s house will be brought out to the king of Babylon’s princes,\nand those women will say, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Your familiar friends have turned on you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and have prevailed over you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Your feet are sunk in the mire, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they have turned away from you.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 38:23"},"They will bring out all your wives and your children to the Chaldeans. You won’t escape out of their hand, but will be\ntaken by the hand of the king of Babylon. You will cause this city to be burnt with fire.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 38:24"},"Then Zedekiah said to Jeremiah, “Let no man know of these words, and you won’t die.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 38:25"},"But if the princes hear that I have talked with you, and they come to you, and tell you, ‘Declare to us now what you have\nsaid to the king; don’t hide it from us, and we will not put you to death; also tell us what the king said to you;’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 38:26"},"then you shall tell them, ‘I presented my supplication before the king, that he would not cause me to return to\nJonathan’s house, to die there.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 38:27"},"Then all the princes came to Jeremiah, and asked him; and he told them according to all these words that the king had\ncommanded. So they stopped speaking with him; for the matter was not perceived.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 38:28"},"So Jeremiah stayed in the court of the guard until the day that Jerusalem was taken.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"39","sid":"JER 39"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 39:1"},"In the ninth year of Zedekiah king of Judah, in the tenth month, Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon and all his army came\nagainst Jerusalem, and besieged it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 39:2"},"In the eleventh year of Zedekiah, in the fourth month, the ninth day of the month, a breach was made in the city.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 39:3"},"All the princes of the king of Babylon came in, and sat in the middle gate, Nergal Sharezer, Samgarnebo, Sarsechim,\nRabsaris, Nergal Sharezer, Rabmag, with all the rest of the princes of the king of Babylon.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 39:4"},"When Zedekiah the king of Judah and all the men of war saw them, then they fled, and went out of the city by night, by the\nway of the king’s garden, through the gate between the two walls; and he went out towards the Arabah.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 39:5"},"But the army of the Chaldeans pursued them, and overtook Zedekiah in the plains of Jericho. When they had taken him, they\nbrought him up to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon to Riblah in the land of Hamath; and he pronounced judgement on him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 39:6"},"Then the king of Babylon killed Zedekiah’s sons in Riblah before his eyes. The king of Babylon also killed all the nobles\nof Judah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 39:7"},"Moreover he put out Zedekiah’s eyes and bound him in fetters, to carry him to Babylon.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 39:8"},"The Chaldeans burnt the king’s house, and the houses of the people, with fire, and broke down the walls of Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 39:9"},"Then Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard carried away captive into Babylon the residue of the people who remained in the\ncity, the deserters also who fell away to him, and the residue of the people who remained.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 39:10"},"But Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard left of the poor of the people, who had nothing, in the land of Judah, and gave\nthem vineyards and fields at the same time. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 39:11"},"Now Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon commanded Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard concerning Jeremiah, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 39:12"},"“Take him, and take care of him. Do him no harm; but do to him even as he tells you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 39:13"},"So Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard sent, with Nebushazban, Rabsaris, and Nergal Sharezer, Rabmag, and all the chief\nofficers of the king of Babylon; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 39:14"},"they sent, and took Jeremiah out of the court of the guard, and committed him to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of\nShaphan, that he should carry him home. So he lived amongst the people.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 39:15"},"Now the LORD’s word came to Jeremiah, while he was shut up in the court of the guard, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 39:16"},"“Go, and speak to Ebedmelech the Ethiopian, saying, ‘The LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says: “Behold, I will bring my\nwords on this city for evil, and not for good; and they will be accomplished before you in that day.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 39:17"},"But I will deliver you in that day,” says the LORD; “and you will not be given into the hand of the men of whom you are\nafraid. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 39:18"},"For I will surely save you, and you won’t fall by the sword, but you will escape with your life; because you have put\nyour trust in me,” says the LORD.’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"40","sid":"JER 40"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 40:1"},"The word which came to Jeremiah from the LORD, after Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard had let him go from Ramah, when\nhe had taken him being bound in chains amongst all the captives of Jerusalem and Judah, who were carried away captive to\nBabylon. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 40:2"},"The captain of the guard took Jeremiah, and said to him, “The LORD your Allah pronounced this evil on this place;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 40:3"},"and the LORD has brought it, and done according as he spoke. Because you have sinned against the LORD, and have not obeyed\nhis voice, therefore this thing has come on you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 40:4"},"Now, behold, I release you today from the chains which are on your hand. If it seems good to you to come with me into\nBabylon, come, and I will take care of you; but if it seems bad to you to come with me into Babylon, don’t. Behold, all the\nland is before you. Where it seems good and right to you to go, there go.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 40:5"},"Now while he had not yet gone back, “Go back then,” he said, “to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, whom the\nking of Babylon has made governor over the cities of Judah, and dwell with him amongst the people; or go wherever it seems\nright to you to go.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So the captain of the guard gave him food and a present, and let him go.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 40:6"},"Then Jeremiah went to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam to Mizpah, and lived with him amongst the people who were left in the\nland. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 40:7"},"Now when all the captains of the forces who were in the fields, even they and their men, heard that the king of Babylon\nhad made Gedaliah the son of Ahikam governor in the land, and had committed to him men, women, children, and of the poorest of\nthe land, of those who were not carried away captive to Babylon;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 40:8"},"then Ismail the son of Nethaniah, and Johanan and Jonathan the sons of Kareah, and Seraiah the son of Tanhumeth, and the\nsons of Ephai the Netophathite, and Jezaniah the son of the Maacathite, they and their men came to Gedaliah to Mizpah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 40:9"},"Gedaliah the son of Ahikam the son of Shaphan swore to them and to their men, saying, “Don’t be afraid to serve the\nChaldeans. Dwell in the land, and serve the king of Babylon, and it will be well with you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 40:10"},"As for me, behold, I will dwell at Mizpah, to stand before the Chaldeans who will come to us; but you, gather wine and\nsummer fruits and oil, and put them in your vessels, and dwell in your cities that you have taken.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 40:11"},"Likewise when all the Jews who were in Moab, and amongst the children of Ammon, and in Edom, and who were in all the\ncountries, heard that the king of Babylon had left a remnant of Judah, and that he had set over them Gedaliah the son of\nAhikam, the son of Shaphan; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 40:12"},"then all the Jews returned out of all places where they were driven, and came to the land of Judah, to Gedaliah, to\nMizpah, and gathered very much wine and summer fruits. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 40:13"},"Moreover Johanan the son of Kareah, and all the captains of the forces who were in the fields, came to Gedaliah to\nMizpah, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 40:14"},"and said to him, “Do you know that Baalis the king of the children of Ammon has sent Ismail the son of Nethaniah to take\nyour life?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But Gedaliah the son of Ahikam didn’t believe them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 40:15"},"Then Johanan the son of Kareah spoke to Gedaliah in Mizpah secretly, saying, “Please let me go, and I will kill Ismail\nthe son of Nethaniah, and no man will know it. Why should he take your life, that all the Jews who are gathered to you should\nbe scattered, and the remnant of Judah perish?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 40:16"},"But Gedaliah the son of Ahikam said to Johanan the son of Kareah, “You shall not do this thing; for you speak falsely of\nIsmail.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"41","sid":"JER 41"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 41:1"},"Now in the seventh month, Ismail the son of Nethaniah, the son of Elishama, of the royal offspring and one of the chief\nofficers of the king, and ten men with him, came to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam to Mizpah; and there they ate bread together in\nMizpah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 41:2"},"Then Ismail the son of Nethaniah arose, and the ten men who were with him, and struck Gedaliah the son of Ahikam the son\nof Shaphan with the sword and killed him, whom the king of Babylon had made governor over the land.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 41:3"},"Ismail also killed all the Jews who were with him, with Gedaliah, at Mizpah, and the Chaldeans who were found there, the\nmen of war. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 41:4"},"The second day after he had killed Gedaliah, and no man knew it,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 41:5"},"men came from Shechem, from Shiloh, and from Samaria, even eighty men, having their beards shaved and their clothes torn,\nand having cut themselves, with meal offerings and frankincense in their hand, to bring them to the LORD’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 41:6"},"Ismail the son of Nethaniah went out from Mizpah to meet them, weeping all along as he went: and as he met them, he said\nto them, “Come to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 41:7"},"It was so, when they came into the middle of the city, that Ismail the son of Nethaniah killed them, and cast them into\nthe middle of the pit, he, and the men who were with him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 41:8"},"But ten men were found amongst those who said to Ismail, “Don’t kill us; for we have stores hidden in the field, of wheat,\nand of barley, and of oil, and of honey.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So he stopped, and didn’t kill them amongst their brothers. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 41:9"},"Now the pit in which Ismail cast all the dead bodies of the men whom he had killed, by the side of Gedaliah (this was that\nwhich Asa the king had made for fear of Baasha king of Israel), Ismail the son of Nethaniah filled it with those who were\nkilled. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 41:10"},"Then Ismail carried away captive all of the people who were left in Mizpah, even the king’s daughters, and all the people\nwho remained in Mizpah, whom Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard had committed to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam. Ismail the son\nof Nethaniah carried them away captive, and departed to go over to the children of Ammon.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 41:11"},"But when Johanan the son of Kareah, and all the captains of the forces who were with him, heard of all the evil that\nIsmail the son of Nethaniah had done, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 41:12"},"then they took all the men, and went to fight with Ismail the son of Nethaniah, and found him by the great waters that\nare in Gibeon. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 41:13"},"Now when all the people who were with Ismail saw Johanan the son of Kareah, and all the captains of the forces who were\nwith him, then they were glad. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 41:14"},"So all the people who Ismail had carried away captive from Mizpah turned about and came back, and went to Johanan the son\nof Kareah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 41:15"},"But Ismail the son of Nethaniah escaped from Johanan with eight men, and went to the children of Ammon.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 41:16"},"Then Johanan the son of Kareah and all the captains of the forces who were with him took all the remnant of the people\nwhom he had recovered from Ismail the son of Nethaniah, from Mizpah, after he had killed Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the men of\nwar, with the women, the children, and the eunuchs, whom he had brought back from Gibeon.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 41:17"},"They departed and lived in Geruth Chimham, which is by Bethlehem, to go to enter into Egypt\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 41:18"},"because of the Chaldeans; for they were afraid of them, because Ismail the son of Nethaniah had killed Gedaliah the son\nof Ahikam, whom the king of Babylon made governor over the land.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"42","sid":"JER 42"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 42:1"},"Then all the captains of the forces, and Johanan the son of Kareah, and Jezaniah the son of Hoshaiah, and all the people\nfrom the least even to the greatest, came near, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 42:2"},"and said to Jeremiah the prophet, “Please let our supplication be presented before you, and pray for us to Allah your\nLORD, even for all this remnant; for we are left but a few of many, as your eyes see us;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 42:3"},"that Allah your LORD may show us the way in which we should walk, and the things that we should do.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 42:4"},"Then Jeremiah the prophet said to them, “I have heard you. Behold, I will pray to Allah your LORD according to your words;\nand it will happen that whatever thing the LORD answers you, I will declare it to you. I will keep nothing back from you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 42:5"},"Then they said to Jeremiah, “May the LORD be a true and faithful witness amongst us, if we don’t do according to all the\nword with which Allah your LORD sends you to tell us. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 42:6"},"Whether it is good, or whether it is bad, we will obey the voice of the LORD our Allah, to whom we send you; that it may\nbe well with us, when we obey the voice of the LORD our Allah.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 42:7"},"After ten days, the LORD’s word came to Jeremiah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 42:8"},"Then he called Johanan the son of Kareah, and all the captains of the forces who were with him, and all the people from\nthe least even to the greatest, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 42:9"},"and said to them, “The LORD, Allah of Israel, to whom you sent me to present your supplication before him, says:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 42:10"},"‘If you will still live in this land, then I will build you, and not pull you down, and I will plant you, and not pluck\nyou up; for I grieve over the distress that I have brought on you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 42:11"},"Don’t be afraid of the king of Babylon, of whom you are afraid. Don’t be afraid of him,’ says the LORD: ‘for I am with\nyou to save you, and to deliver you from his hand. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 42:12"},"I will grant you mercy, that he may have mercy on you, and cause you to return to your own land.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 42:13"},"“‘But if you say, “We will not dwell in this land;” so that you don’t obey Allah your LORD’s voice,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 42:14"},"saying, “No; but we will go into the land of Egypt, where we will see no war, nor hear the sound of the trumpet, nor have\nhunger of bread; and there will we dwell:”’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 42:15"},"now therefore hear the LORD’s word, O remnant of Judah: The LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says, ‘If you indeed set\nyour faces to enter into Egypt, and go to live there; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 42:16"},"then it will happen that the sword, which you fear, will overtake you there in the land of Egypt; and the famine, about\nwhich you are afraid, will follow close behind you there in Egypt; and you will die there.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 42:17"},"So will it be with all the men who set their faces to go into Egypt to live there. They will die by the sword, by the\nfamine, and by the pestilence. None of them will remain or escape from the evil that I will bring on them.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 42:18"},"For the LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says: ‘As my anger and my wrath has been poured out on the inhabitants of\nJerusalem, so my wrath will be poured out on you, when you enter into Egypt; and you will be an object of horror, an\nastonishment, a curse, and a reproach; and you will see this place no more.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 42:19"},"“The LORD has spoken concerning you, remnant of Judah, ‘Don’t go into Egypt!’ Know certainly that I have testified to you\ntoday. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 42:20"},"For you have dealt deceitfully against your own souls; for you sent me to Allah your LORD, saying, ‘Pray for us to the\nLORD our Allah; and according to all that the LORD our Allah says, so declare to us, and we will do it.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 42:21"},"I have declared it to you today; but you have not obeyed Allah your LORD’s voice in anything for which he has sent me to\nyou. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 42:22"},"Now therefore know certainly that you will die by the sword, by the famine, and by the pestilence in the place where you\ndesire to go to live there.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"43","sid":"JER 43"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 43:1"},"When Jeremiah had finished speaking to all the people all the words of the LORD their Allah, with which the LORD their\nAllah had sent him to them, even all these words, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 43:2"},"then Azariah the son of Hoshaiah, Johanan the son of Kareah, and all the proud men spoke, saying to Jeremiah, “You speak\nfalsely. The LORD our Allah has not sent you to say, ‘You shall not go into Egypt to live there;’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 43:3"},"but Baruch the son of Neriah has turned you against us, to deliver us into the hand of the Chaldeans, that they may put us\nto death, and carry us away captive to Babylon.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 43:4"},"So Johanan the son of Kareah, and all the captains of the forces, and all the people, didn’t obey the LORD’s voice, to\ndwell in the land of Judah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 43:5"},"But Johanan the son of Kareah, and all the captains of the forces, took all the remnant of Judah, who had returned from\nall the nations where they had been driven, to live in the land of Judah;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 43:6"},"the men, and the women, and the children, and the king’s daughters, and every person who Nebuzaradan the captain of the\nguard had left with Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan; and Jeremiah the prophet, and Baruch the son of Neriah;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 43:7"},"and they came into the land of Egypt; for they didn’t obey the LORD’s voice: and they came to Tahpanhes.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 43:8"},"Then the LORD’s word came to Jeremiah in Tahpanhes, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 43:9"},"“Take great stones in your hand, and hide them in mortar in the brick work, which is at the entry of Pharaoh’s house in\nTahpanhes, in the sight of the men of Judah; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 43:10"},"and tell them, the LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says: ‘Behold, I will send and take Nebuchadnezzar the king of\nBabylon, my servant, and will set his throne on these stones that I have hidden; and he will spread his royal pavilion over\nthem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 43:11"},"He will come, and will strike the land of Egypt; such as are for death will be put to death, and such as are for\ncaptivity to captivity, and such as are for the sword to the sword.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 43:12"},"I will kindle a fire in the houses of the gods of Egypt. He will burn them, and carry them away captive. He will array\nhimself with the land of Egypt, as a shepherd puts on his garment; and he will go out from there in peace.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 43:13"},"He will also break the pillars of Beth Shemesh, that is in the land of Egypt; and he will burn the houses of the gods of\nEgypt with fire.’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"44","sid":"JER 44"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 44:1"},"The word that came to Jeremiah concerning all the Jews who lived in the land of Egypt, who lived at Migdol, and at\nTahpanhes, and at Memphis, and in the country of Pathros, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 44:2"},"“The LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says: ‘You have seen all the evil that I have brought on Jerusalem, and on all the\ncities of Judah. Behold, today they are a desolation, and no man dwells in them,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 44:3"},"because of their wickedness which they have committed to provoke me to anger, in that they went to burn incense, to serve\nother gods that they didn’t know, neither they, nor you, nor your fathers.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 44:4"},"However I sent to you all my servants the prophets, rising up early and sending them, saying, “Oh, don’t do this\nabominable thing that I hate.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 44:5"},"But they didn’t listen and didn’t incline their ear. They didn’t turn from their wickedness, to stop burning incense to\nother gods. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 44:6"},"Therefore my wrath and my anger was poured out, and was kindled in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem;\nand they are wasted and desolate, as it is today.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 44:7"},"“Therefore now the LORD, Allah of Armies, Allah of Israel, says: ‘Why do you commit great evil against your own souls, to\ncut off from yourselves man and woman, infant and nursing child out of the middle of Judah, to leave yourselves no one\nremaining; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 44:8"},"in that you provoke me to anger with the works of your hands, burning incense to other gods in the land of Egypt, where\nyou have gone to live; that you may be cut off, and that you may be a curse and a reproach amongst all the nations of the\nearth? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 44:9"},"Have you forgotten the wickedness of your fathers, and the wickedness of the kings of Judah, and the wickedness of their\nwives, and your own wickedness, and the wickedness of your wives, which they committed in the land of Judah and in the streets\nof Jerusalem? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 44:10"},"They are not humbled even to this day, neither have they feared, nor walked in my law, nor in my statutes, that I set\nbefore you and before your fathers.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 44:11"},"“Therefore the LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says: ‘Behold, I will set my face against you for evil, even to cut off\nall Judah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 44:12"},"I will take the remnant of Judah, that have set their faces to go into the land of Egypt to live there, and they will all\nbe consumed. They will fall in the land of Egypt. They will be consumed by the sword and by the famine. They will die, from the\nleast even to the greatest, by the sword and by the famine. They will be an object of horror, an astonishment, and a curse, and\na reproach. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 44:13"},"For I will punish those who dwell in the land of Egypt, as I have punished Jerusalem, by the sword, by the famine, and by\nthe pestilence; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 44:14"},"so that none of the remnant of Judah, who have gone into the land of Egypt to live there, will escape or be left to\nreturn into the land of Judah, to which they have a desire to return to dwell there; for no one will return except those who\nwill escape.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 44:15"},"Then all the men who knew that their wives burnt incense to other gods, and all the women who stood by, a great assembly,\neven all the people who lived in the land of Egypt, in Pathros, answered Jeremiah, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 44:16"},"“As for the word that you have spoken to us in the LORD’s name, we will not listen to you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 44:17"},"But we will certainly perform every word that has gone out of our mouth, to burn incense to the queen of the sky, and to\npour out drink offerings to her, as we have done, we and our fathers, our kings and our princes, in the cities of Judah, and in\nthe streets of Jerusalem; for then had we plenty of food, and were well, and saw no evil.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 44:18"},"But since we stopped burning incense to the queen of the sky, and pouring out drink offerings to her, we have lacked all\nthings, and have been consumed by the sword and by the famine. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 44:19"},"“When we burnt incense to the queen of the sky, and poured out drink offerings to her, did we make her cakes to worship\nher, and pour out drink offerings to her, without our husbands?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 44:20"},"Then Jeremiah said to all the people, to the men, and to the women, even to all the people who had given him an answer,\nsaying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 44:21"},"“The incense that you burnt in the cities of Judah, and in the streets of Jerusalem, you and your fathers, your kings and\nyour princes, and the people of the land, didn’t the LORD remember them, and didn’t it come into his mind?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 44:22"},"Thus the LORD could no longer bear it, because of the evil of your doings, and because of the abominations which you have\ncommitted. Therefore your land has become a desolation, and an astonishment, and a curse, without inhabitant, as it is today.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 44:23"},"Because you have burnt incense, and because you have sinned against the LORD, and have not obeyed the LORD’s voice, nor\nwalked in his law, nor in his statutes, nor in his testimonies; therefore this evil has happened to you, as it is today.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 44:24"},"Moreover Jeremiah said to all the people, including all the women, “Hear the LORD’s word, all Judah who are in the land\nof Egypt! \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 44:25"},"The LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says, ‘You and your wives have both spoken with your mouths, and with your hands\nhave fulfilled it, saying, “We will surely perform our vows that we have vowed, to burn incense to the queen of the sky, and to\npour out drink offerings to her.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“‘Establish then your vows, and perform your vows.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 44:26"},"“Therefore hear the LORD’s word, all Judah who dwell in the land of Egypt: ‘Behold, I have sworn by my great name,’ says\nthe LORD, ‘that my name will no more be named in the mouth of any man of Judah in all the land of Egypt, saying, “As the Lord\nALLAH lives.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 44:27"},"Behold, I watch over them for evil, and not for good; and all the men of Judah who are in the land of Egypt will be\nconsumed by the sword and by the famine, until they are all gone.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 44:28"},"Those who escape the sword will return out of the land of Egypt into the land of Judah few in number. All the remnant of\nJudah, who have gone into the land of Egypt to live there, will know whose word will stand, mine or theirs.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JER 44:29"},"“‘This will be the sign to you,’ says the LORD, ‘that I will punish you in this place, that you may know that my words\nwill surely stand against you for evil.’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JER 44:30"},"The LORD says, ‘Behold, I will give Pharaoh Hophra king of Egypt into the hand of his enemies, and into the hand of those\nwho seek his life; as I gave Zedekiah king of Judah into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, who was his enemy, and\nsought his life.’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"45","sid":"JER 45"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 45:1"},"The message that Jeremiah the prophet spoke to Baruch the son of Neriah, when he wrote these words in a book at the mouth\nof Jeremiah, in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 45:2"},"“The LORD, Allah of Israel, says to you, Baruch: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 45:3"},"‘You said, “Woe is me now! For the LORD has added sorrow to my pain! I am weary with my groaning, and I find no rest.”’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 45:4"},"“You shall tell him, the LORD says: ‘Behold, that which I have built, I will break down, and that which I have planted I\nwill pluck up; and this in the whole land. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 45:5"},"Do you seek great things for yourself? Don’t seek them; for, behold, I will bring evil on all flesh,’ says the LORD; ‘but\nI will let you escape with your life wherever you go.’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"46","sid":"JER 46"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 46:1"},"The LORD’s word which came to Jeremiah the prophet concerning the nations.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 46:2"},"Of Egypt: concerning the army of Pharaoh Necoh king of Egypt, which was by the river Euphrates in Carchemish, which\nNebuchadnezzar king of Babylon struck in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 46:3"},"“Prepare the buckler and shield, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and draw near to battle! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 46:4"},"Harness the horses, and get up, you horsemen, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and stand up with your helmets. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Polish the spears, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["put on the coats of mail. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 46:5"},"Why have I seen it? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They are dismayed and are turned backward. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Their mighty ones are beaten down, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["have fled in haste, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and don’t look back. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Terror is on every side,” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 46:6"},"“Don’t let the swift flee away, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["nor the mighty man escape. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["In the north by the river Euphrates \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they have stumbled and fallen. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 46:7"},"“Who is this who rises up like the Nile, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["whose waters toss themselves like the rivers? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 46:8"},"Egypt rises up like the Nile, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and his waters toss themselves like the rivers. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He says, ‘I will rise up. I will cover the earth. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will destroy cities and its inhabitants.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 46:9"},"Go up, you horses! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Rage, you chariots! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Let the mighty men go out: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Cush and Put, who handle the shield; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the Ludim, who handle and bend the bow. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 46:10"},"For that day is of the Lord, the LORD of Armies, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a day of vengeance, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that he may avenge himself of his adversaries. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The sword will devour and be satiated, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will drink its fill of their blood; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the Lord, the LORD of Armies, has a sacrifice in the north country by the river Euphrates.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 46:11"},"Go up into Gilead, and take balm, virgin daughter of Egypt.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You use many medicines in vain. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["There is no healing for you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 46:12"},"The nations have heard of your shame, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the earth is full of your cry; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the mighty man has stumbled against the mighty, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they both fall together.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 46:13"},"The word that the LORD spoke to Jeremiah the prophet, how that Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon should come and strike the\nland of Egypt. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 46:14"},"“Declare in Egypt, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["publish in Migdol, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and publish in Memphis and in Tahpanhes: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["say, ‘Stand up, and prepare; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the sword has devoured around you.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 46:15"},"Why are your strong ones swept away? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They didn’t stand, because the LORD pushed them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 46:16"},"He made many to stumble. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Yes, they fell on one another. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They said, ‘Arise! Let’s go again to our own people, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and to the land of our birth, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the oppressing sword.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 46:17"},"They cried there, ‘Pharaoh king of Egypt is but a noise; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["he has let the appointed time pass by.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 46:18"},"“As I live,” says the King, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["whose name is the LORD of Armies, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“surely like Tabor amongst the mountains, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and like Carmel by the sea, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so he will come. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 46:19"},"You daughter who dwells in Egypt, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["furnish yourself to go into captivity; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for Memphis will become a desolation, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will be burnt up, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["without inhabitant. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 46:20"},"“Egypt is a very beautiful heifer; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but destruction out of the north has come. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It has come. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 46:21"},"Also her hired men in the middle of her are like calves of the stall;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for they also are turned back. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They have fled away together. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They didn’t stand, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the day of their calamity has come on them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the time of their visitation. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 46:22"},"Its sound will go like the serpent; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for they will march with an army, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and come against her with axes, as wood cutters. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 46:23"},"They will cut down her forest,” says the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“though it can’t be searched; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["because they are more than the locusts, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and are innumerable. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 46:24"},"The daughter of Egypt will be disappointed; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["she will be delivered into the hand of the people of the north.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 46:25"},"The LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says: “Behold, I will punish Amon of No, and Pharaoh, and Egypt, with her gods, and\nher kings; even Pharaoh, and those who trust in him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 46:26"},"I will deliver them into the hand of those who seek their lives, and into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, and\ninto the hand of his servants. Afterwards it will be inhabited, as in the days of old,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 46:27"},"“But don’t you be afraid, Yaqub my servant. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Don’t be dismayed, Israel; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for, behold, I will save you from afar, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your offspring from the land of their captivity. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Yaqub will return, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will be quiet and at ease. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["No one will make him afraid. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 46:28"},"Don’t be afraid, O Yaqub my servant,” says the LORD; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“for I am with you; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for I will make a full end of all the nations where I have driven you;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["but I will not make a full end of you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but I will correct you in measure, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will in no way leave you unpunished.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"47","sid":"JER 47"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 47:1"},"The LORD’s word that came to Jeremiah the prophet concerning the Philistines, before Pharaoh struck Gaza.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 47:2"},"The LORD says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, waters rise up out of the north, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will become an overflowing stream, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and will overflow the land and all that is therein, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the city and those who dwell therein. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The men will cry, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all the inhabitants of the land will wail. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 47:3"},"At the noise of the stamping of the hoofs of his strong ones,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["at the rushing of his chariots, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["at the rumbling of his wheels, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["the fathers don’t look back to their children \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for feebleness of hands; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 47:4"},"because of the day that comes to destroy all the Philistines,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to cut off from Tyre and Sidon every helper who remains; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for the LORD will destroy the Philistines, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the remnant of the isle of Caphtor. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 47:5"},"Baldness has come on Gaza; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Ashkelon is brought to nothing, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["the remnant of their valley: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["how long will you cut yourself? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 47:6"},"“‘You sword of the LORD, how long will it be before you are quiet?\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Put yourself back into your scabbard; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["rest, and be still.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 47:7"},"“How can you be quiet, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["since the LORD has given you a command? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Against Ashkelon, and against the seashore, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["there has he appointed it.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"48","sid":"JER 48"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 48:1"},"Of Moab. The LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Woe to Nebo! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["For it is laid waste. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Kiriathaim is disappointed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It is taken. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Misgab",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["48:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, The stronghold"]}],"caller":"+"}," is put to shame\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and broken down. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 48:2"},"The praise of Moab is no more. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["In Heshbon they have devised evil against her: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘Come! Let’s cut her off from being a nation.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You also, Madmen, will be brought to silence. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The sword will pursue you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 48:3"},"The sound of a cry from Horonaim, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["desolation and great destruction! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 48:4"},"Moab is destroyed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Her little ones have caused a cry to be heard. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 48:5"},"For they will go up by the ascent of Luhith with continual weeping.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["For at the descent of Horonaim they have heard the distress of the cry of destruction.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 48:6"},"Flee! Save your lives! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Be like the juniper bush in the wilderness. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 48:7"},"For, because you have trusted in your works and in your treasures,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you also will be taken. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Chemosh will go out into captivity, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["his priests and his princes together. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 48:8"},"The destroyer will come on every city, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and no city will escape; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["the valley also will perish, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the plain will be destroyed; as the LORD has spoken. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 48:9"},"Give wings to Moab, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that she may fly and get herself away: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and her cities will become a desolation, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["without anyone to dwell in them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 48:10"},"“Cursed is he who does the work of the LORD negligently; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and cursed is he who keeps back his sword from blood. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 48:11"},"“Moab has been at ease from his youth, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and he has settled on his lees, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and has not been emptied from vessel to vessel, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["neither has he gone into captivity: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["therefore his taste remains in him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and his scent is not changed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 48:12"},"Therefore behold, the days come,” says the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“that I will send to him those who pour off, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and they will pour him off; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will empty his vessels, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and break their containers in pieces. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 48:13"},"Moab will be ashamed of Chemosh, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as the house of Israel was ashamed of Bethel, their confidence.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 48:14"},"“How do you say, ‘We are mighty men, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and valiant men for the war?’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 48:15"},"Moab is laid waste, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they have gone up into his cities, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and his chosen young men have gone down to the slaughter,” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["says the King, whose name is the LORD of Armies. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 48:16"},"“The calamity of Moab is near to come, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and his affliction hurries fast. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 48:17"},"All you who are around him, bemoan him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all you who know his name; say, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘How the strong staff is broken, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the beautiful rod!’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 48:18"},"“You daughter who dwells in Dibon, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["come down from your glory, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and sit in thirst; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for the destroyer of Moab has come up against you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He has destroyed your strongholds. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 48:19"},"Inhabitant of Aroer, stand by the way and watch. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Ask him who flees, and her who escapes; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["say, ‘What has been done?’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 48:20"},"Moab is disappointed; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for it is broken down. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Wail and cry! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Tell it by the Arnon, that Moab is laid waste. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 48:21"},"Judgement has come on the plain country, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["on Holon, on Jahzah, on Mephaath, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 48:22"},"on Dibon, on Nebo, on Beth Diblathaim, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 48:23"},"on Kiriathaim, on Beth Gamul, on Beth Meon, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 48:24"},"on Kerioth, on Bozrah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and on all the cities of the land of Moab, far or near. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 48:25"},"The horn of Moab is cut off, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and his arm is broken,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 48:26"},"“Make him drunken; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for he magnified himself against the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Moab will wallow in his vomit, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and he also will be in derision. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 48:27"},"For wasn’t Israel a derision to you? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Was he found amongst thieves? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For as often as you speak of him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you shake your head. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 48:28"},"You inhabitants of Moab, leave the cities, and dwell in the rock.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Be like the dove that makes her nest over the mouth of the abyss.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JER 48:29"},"“We have heard of the pride of Moab. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He is very proud in his loftiness, his pride, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["his arrogance, and the arrogance of his heart. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JER 48:30"},"I know his wrath,” says the LORD, “that it is nothing; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["his boastings have done nothing. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JER 48:31"},"Therefore I will wail for Moab. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Yes, I will cry out for all Moab. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They will mourn for the men of Kir Heres. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JER 48:32"},"With more than the weeping of Jazer \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will weep for you, vine of Sibmah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Your branches passed over the sea. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They reached even to the sea of Jazer. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The destroyer has fallen on your summer fruits \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and on your vintage. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JER 48:33"},"Gladness and joy is taken away from the fruitful field \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and from the land of Moab. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I have caused wine to cease from the wine presses. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["No one will tread with shouting. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The shouting will be no shouting. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JER 48:34"},"From the cry of Heshbon even to Elealeh, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even to Jahaz they have uttered their voice, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from Zoar even to Horonaim, to Eglath Shelishiyah; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the waters of Nimrim will also become desolate. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JER 48:35"},"Moreover I will cause to cease in Moab,” says the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“him who offers in the high place, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and him who burns incense to his gods. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JER 48:36"},"Therefore my heart sounds for Moab like pipes, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and my heart sounds like pipes for the men of Kir Heres. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Therefore the abundance that he has gotten has perished. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JER 48:37"},"For every head is bald, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and every beard clipped. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["There are cuttings on all the hands, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and sackcloth on the waist. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JER 48:38"},"On all the housetops of Moab, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and in its streets, there is lamentation everywhere; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for I have broken Moab like a vessel in which no one delights,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JER 48:39"},"“How it is broken down! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["How they wail! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["How Moab has turned the back with shame! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["So will Moab become a derision \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and a terror to all who are around him.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"JER 48:40"},"For the LORD says: “Behold, he will fly as an eagle, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will spread out his wings against Moab. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"JER 48:41"},"Kerioth is taken, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the strongholds are seized. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The heart of the mighty men of Moab at that day \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["will be as the heart of a woman in her pangs. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"JER 48:42"},"Moab will be destroyed from being a people, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because he has magnified himself against the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"JER 48:43"},"Terror, the pit, and the snare are on you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["inhabitant of Moab,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"JER 48:44"},"“He who flees from the terror will fall into the pit; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and he who gets up out of the pit will be taken in the snare:\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for I will bring on him, even on Moab, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the year of their visitation,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"JER 48:45"},"“Those who fled stand without strength under the shadow of Heshbon;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for a fire has gone out of Heshbon, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and a flame from the middle of Sihon, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and has devoured the corner of Moab, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the crown of the head of the tumultuous ones. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"JER 48:46"},"Woe to you, O Moab! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The people of Chemosh are undone; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for your sons are taken away captive, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your daughters into captivity. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"JER 48:47"},"“Yet I will reverse the captivity of Moab in the latter days,”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Thus far is the judgement of Moab. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"49","sid":"JER 49"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 49:1"},"Of the children of Ammon. The LORD says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Has Israel no sons? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Has he no heir? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Why then does Malcam possess Gad, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and his people dwell in its cities? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 49:2"},"Therefore behold, the days come,” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["says the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“that I will cause an alarm of war to be heard against Rabbah of the children of Ammon;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and it will become a desolate heap, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and her daughters will be burnt with fire: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["then Israel will possess those who possessed him,” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 49:3"},"“Wail, Heshbon, for Ai is laid waste! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Cry, you daughters of Rabbah! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Clothe yourself in sackcloth. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Lament, and run back and forth amongst the fences; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for Malcam will go into captivity, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["his priests and his princes together. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 49:4"},"Why do you boast in the valleys, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your flowing valley, backsliding daughter? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You trusted in her treasures, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["saying, ‘Who will come to me?’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 49:5"},"Behold, I will bring a terror on you,” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["says the Lord, the LORD of Armies, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“from all who are around you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["All of you will be driven completely out, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and there will be no one to gather together the fugitives. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 49:6"},"“But afterward I will reverse the captivity of the children of Ammon,”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 49:7"},"Of Edom, the LORD of Armies says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Is wisdom no more in Teman? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Has counsel perished from the prudent? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Has their wisdom vanished? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 49:8"},"Flee! Turn back! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Dwell in the depths, inhabitants of Dedan; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for I will bring the calamity of Esau on him when I visit him.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 49:9"},"If grape gatherers came to you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["would they not leave some gleaning grapes? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["If thieves came by night, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["wouldn’t they steal until they had enough? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 49:10"},"But I have made Esau bare, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have uncovered his secret places, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and he will not be able to hide himself. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["His offspring is destroyed, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with his brothers and his neighbours; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and he is no more. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 49:11"},"Leave your fatherless children. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will preserve them alive. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Let your widows trust in me.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 49:12"},"For the LORD says: “Behold, they to whom it didn’t pertain to drink of the cup will certainly drink; and are you he who\nwill altogether go unpunished? You won’t go unpunished, but you will surely drink.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 49:13"},"For I have sworn by myself,” says the LORD, “that Bozrah will become an astonishment, a reproach, a waste, and a curse.\nAll its cities will be perpetual wastes.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 49:14"},"I have heard news from the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and an ambassador is sent amongst the nations, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["saying, “Gather yourselves together! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Come against her! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Rise up to the battle!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 49:15"},"“For, behold, I have made you small amongst the nations, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and despised amongst men. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 49:16"},"As for your terror, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the pride of your heart has deceived you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["O you who dwell in the clefts of the rock, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who hold the height of the hill, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["though you should make your nest as high as the eagle, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will bring you down from there,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 49:17"},"“Edom will become an astonishment. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Everyone who passes by it will be astonished, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will hiss at all its plagues. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 49:18"},"As in the overthrow of Sodom and Gomorrah and its neighbour cities,” says the LORD,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“no man will dwell there, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["neither will any son of man live therein. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 49:19"},"“Behold, he will come up like a lion from the pride of the Jordan against the strong habitation:\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for I will suddenly make them run away from it; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and whoever is chosen, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will appoint him over it. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For who is like me? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Who will appoint me a time? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Who is the shepherd who will stand before me?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 49:20"},"Therefore hear the counsel of the LORD, that he has taken against Edom;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and his purposes, that he has purposed against the inhabitants of Teman:\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Surely they will drag them away, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the little ones of the flock. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Surely he will make their habitation desolate over them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 49:21"},"The earth trembles at the noise of their fall; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["there is a cry, the noise which is heard in the Red Sea. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 49:22"},"Behold, he will come up and fly as the eagle, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and spread out his wings against Bozrah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The heart of the mighty men of Edom at that day will be as the heart of a woman in her pangs.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 49:23"},"Of Damascus: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Hamath is confounded, and Arpad; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for they have heard evil news. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They have melted away. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["There is sorrow on the sea. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It can’t be quiet. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 49:24"},"Damascus has grown feeble, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["she turns herself to flee, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and trembling has seized her. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Anguish and sorrows have taken hold of her, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as of a woman in travail. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 49:25"},"How is the city of praise not forsaken, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the city of my joy? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 49:26"},"Therefore her young men will fall in her streets, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all the men of war will be brought to silence in that day,”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["says the LORD of Armies. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 49:27"},"“I will kindle a fire in the wall of Damascus, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and it will devour the palaces of Ben Hadad.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 49:28"},"Of Kedar, and of the kingdoms of Hazor, which Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon struck. The LORD says:\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Arise, go up to Kedar, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and destroy the children of the east. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JER 49:29"},"They will take their tents and their flocks. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they will carry away for themselves their curtains, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["all their vessels, and their camels; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will cry to them, ‘Terror on every side!’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JER 49:30"},"Flee! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Wander far off! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Dwell in the depths, you inhabitants of Hazor,” says the LORD;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“for Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon has taken counsel against you,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and has conceived a purpose against you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JER 49:31"},"Arise! Go up to a nation that is at ease, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that dwells without care,” says the LORD; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“that has neither gates nor bars, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that dwells alone. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JER 49:32"},"Their camels will be a booty, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the multitude of their livestock a plunder. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will scatter to all winds those who have the corners of their beards cut off;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will bring their calamity from every side of them,” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JER 49:33"},"Hazor will be a dwelling place of jackals, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a desolation forever. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["No man will dwell there, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["neither will any son of man live therein.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JER 49:34"},"The LORD’s word that came to Jeremiah the prophet concerning Elam, in the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah king of\nJudah, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JER 49:35"},"“The LORD of Armies says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘Behold, I will break the bow of Elam, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the chief of their might. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JER 49:36"},"I will bring on Elam the four winds from the four quarters of the sky,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will scatter them towards all those winds. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["There will be no nation where the outcasts of Elam will not come.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JER 49:37"},"I will cause Elam to be dismayed before their enemies, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and before those who seek their life. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will bring evil on them, even my fierce anger,’ says the LORD;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘and I will send the sword after them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["until I have consumed them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JER 49:38"},"I will set my throne in Elam, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will destroy from there king and princes,’ says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JER 49:39"},"‘But it will happen in the latter days \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that I will reverse the captivity of Elam,’ says the LORD.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"50","sid":"JER 50"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 50:1"},"The word that the LORD spoke concerning Babylon, concerning the land of the Chaldeans, by Jeremiah the prophet.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 50:2"},"“Declare amongst the nations and publish, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and set up a standard; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["publish, and don’t conceal: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["say, ‘Babylon has been taken, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Bel is disappointed, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Merodach is dismayed! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Her images are disappointed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Her idols are dismayed.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 50:3"},"For a nation comes up out of the north against her, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["which will make her land desolate, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and no one will dwell in it. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They have fled. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They are gone, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["both man and animal. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 50:4"},"“In those days, and in that time,” says the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“the children of Israel will come, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they and the children of Judah together; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["they will go on their way weeping, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will seek the LORD their Allah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 50:5"},"They will enquire concerning Zion with their faces turned towards it,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["saying, ‘Come, and join yourselves to the LORD in an everlasting covenant\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that will not be forgotten.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 50:6"},"My people have been lost sheep. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Their shepherds have caused them to go astray. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They have turned them away on the mountains. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They have gone from mountain to hill. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They have forgotten their resting place. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 50:7"},"All who found them have devoured them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Their adversaries said, ‘We are not guilty, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["because they have sinned against the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the habitation of righteousness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even the LORD, the hope of their fathers.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 50:8"},"“Flee out of the middle of Babylon! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Go out of the land of the Chaldeans, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and be as the male goats before the flocks. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 50:9"},"For, behold, I will stir up \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and cause to come up against Babylon a company of great nations from the north country;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will set themselves in array against her. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["She will be taken from there. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Their arrows will be as of an expert mighty man. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["None of them will return in vain. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 50:10"},"Chaldea will be a prey. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["All who prey on her will be satisfied,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 50:11"},"“Because you are glad, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because you rejoice, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["O you who plunder my heritage, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because you are wanton as a heifer that treads out the grain,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and neigh as strong horses; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 50:12"},"your mother will be utterly disappointed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["She who bore you will be confounded. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Behold, she will be the least of the nations, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a wilderness, a dry land, and a desert. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 50:13"},"Because of the LORD’s wrath she won’t be inhabited, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but she will be wholly desolate. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Everyone who goes by Babylon will be astonished, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and hiss at all her plagues. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 50:14"},"Set yourselves in array against Babylon all around, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["all you who bend the bow; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["shoot at her. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Spare no arrows; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for she has sinned against the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 50:15"},"Shout against her all around. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["She has submitted herself. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Her bulwarks have fallen. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Her walls have been thrown down, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for it is the vengeance of the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Take vengeance on her. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["As she has done, do to her. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 50:16"},"Cut off the sower from Babylon, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and him who handles the sickle in the time of harvest. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For fear of the oppressing sword, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they will each return to their own people, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will each flee to their own land. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 50:17"},"“Israel is a hunted sheep. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The lions have driven him away. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["First, the king of Assyria devoured him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and now at last Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon has broken his bones.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 50:18"},"Therefore the LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, I will punish the king of Babylon and his land, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as I have punished the king of Assyria. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 50:19"},"I will bring Israel again to his pasture, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and he will feed on Carmel and Bashan. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["His soul will be satisfied on the hills of Ephraim and in Gilead.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 50:20"},"In those days, and in that time,” says the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“the iniquity of Israel will be sought for, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and there will be none; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["also the sins of Judah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they won’t be found; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for I will pardon them whom I leave as a remnant. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 50:21"},"“Go up against the land of Merathaim, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even against it, and against the inhabitants of Pekod. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Kill and utterly destroy after them,” says the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“and do according to all that I have commanded you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 50:22"},"A sound of battle is in the land, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and of great destruction. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 50:23"},"How the hammer of the whole earth is cut apart and broken!\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["How Babylon has become a desolation amongst the nations! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 50:24"},"I have laid a snare for you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and you are also taken, Babylon, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and you weren’t aware. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You are found, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and also caught, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because you have fought against the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 50:25"},"The LORD has opened his armoury, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and has brought out the weapons of his indignation; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the Lord, the LORD of Armies, has a work to do in the land of the Chaldeans.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 50:26"},"Come against her from the farthest border. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Open her storehouses. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Cast her up as heaps. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Destroy her utterly. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Let nothing of her be left. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 50:27"},"Kill all her bulls. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Let them go down to the slaughter. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Woe to them! For their day has come, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the time of their visitation. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 50:28"},"Listen to those who flee and escape out of the land of Babylon,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to declare in Zion the vengeance of the LORD our Allah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the vengeance of his temple. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JER 50:29"},"“Call together the archers against Babylon, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["all those who bend the bow. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Encamp against her all around. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Let none of it escape. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Pay her back according to her work. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["According to all that she has done, do to her; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for she has been proud against the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["against the Holy One of Israel. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JER 50:30"},"Therefore her young men will fall in her streets. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["All her men of war will be brought to silence in that day,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JER 50:31"},"“Behold, I am against you, you proud one,” says the Lord, the LORD of Armies;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“for your day has come, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the time that I will visit you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JER 50:32"},"The proud one will stumble and fall, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and no one will raise him up. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will kindle a fire in his cities, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and it will devour all who are around him.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JER 50:33"},"The LORD of Armies says: “The children of Israel and the children of Judah are oppressed together.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["All who took them captive hold them fast. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They refuse to let them go. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JER 50:34"},"Their Redeemer is strong: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The LORD of Armies is his name. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He will thoroughly plead their cause, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that he may give rest to the earth, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and disquiet the inhabitants of Babylon. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JER 50:35"},"“A sword is on the Chaldeans,” says the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“and on the inhabitants of Babylon, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["on her princes, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and on her wise men. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JER 50:36"},"A sword is on the boasters, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will become fools. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["A sword is on her mighty men, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will be dismayed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JER 50:37"},"A sword is on their horses, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["on their chariots, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and on all the mixed people who are in the middle of her; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will become as women. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["A sword is on her treasures, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will be robbed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JER 50:38"},"A drought is on her waters, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will be dried up; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for it is a land of engraved images, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they are mad over idols. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JER 50:39"},"Therefore the wild animals of the desert \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with the wolves will dwell there. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The ostriches will dwell therein; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and it will be inhabited no more forever; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["neither will it be lived in from generation to generation. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"JER 50:40"},"As when Allah overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah and its neighbour cities,” says the LORD,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“so no man will dwell there, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["neither will any son of man live therein. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"JER 50:41"},"“Behold, a people comes from the north; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and a great nation and many kings will be stirred up from the uttermost parts of the earth.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"JER 50:42"},"They take up bow and spear. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They are cruel, and have no mercy. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Their voice roars like the sea. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They ride on horses, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["everyone set in array, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as a man to the battle, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["against you, daughter of Babylon. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"JER 50:43"},"The king of Babylon has heard the news of them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and his hands become feeble: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["anguish has taken hold of him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["pains as of a woman in labour. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"JER 50:44"},"Behold, the enemy will come up like a lion \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the pride of the Jordan against the strong habitation; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for I will suddenly make them run away from it. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Whoever is chosen, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will appoint him over it; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for who is like me? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Who will appoint me a time? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Who is the shepherd who can stand before me?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"JER 50:45"},"Therefore hear the counsel of the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that he has taken against Babylon; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and his purposes, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that he has purposed against the land of the Chaldeans: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Surely they will drag them away, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even the little ones of the flock. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Surely he will make their habitation desolate over them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"JER 50:46"},"At the noise of the taking of Babylon the earth trembles; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the cry is heard amongst the nations. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"51","sid":"JER 51"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 51:1"},"The LORD says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, I will raise up against Babylon, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and against those who dwell in Lebkamai, a destroying wind. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 51:2"},"I will send to Babylon strangers, who will winnow her. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They will empty her land; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for in the day of trouble they will be against her all around.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 51:3"},"Against him who bends, let the archer bend his bow, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["also against him who lifts himself up in his coat of mail. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Don’t spare her young men! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Utterly destroy all her army! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 51:4"},"They will fall down slain in the land of the Chaldeans, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and thrust through in her streets. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 51:5"},"For Israel is not forsaken, nor Judah, by his Allah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["by the LORD of Armies; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["though their land is full of guilt against the Holy One of Israel.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 51:6"},"“Flee out of the middle of Babylon! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Everyone save his own life! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Don’t be cut off in her iniquity; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for it is the time of the LORD’s vengeance. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He will render to her a recompense. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 51:7"},"Babylon has been a golden cup in the LORD’s hand, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who made all the earth drunk. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The nations have drunk of her wine; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["therefore the nations have gone mad. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 51:8"},"Babylon has suddenly fallen and been destroyed! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Wail for her! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Take balm for her pain. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Perhaps she may be healed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 51:9"},"“We would have healed Babylon, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but she is not healed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Forsake her, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and let’s each go into his own country; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for her judgement reaches to heaven, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and is lifted up even to the skies. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 51:10"},"‘The LORD has produced our righteousness: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["come, and let’s declare in Zion the work of the LORD our Allah.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 51:11"},"“Make the arrows sharp! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Hold the shields firmly! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The LORD has stirred up the spirit of the kings of the Medes,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because his purpose is against Babylon, to destroy it; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for it is the vengeance of the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the vengeance of his temple. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 51:12"},"Set up a standard against the walls of Babylon! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Make the watch strong! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Set the watchmen, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and prepare the ambushes; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for the LORD has both purposed and done \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that which he spoke concerning the inhabitants of Babylon. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 51:13"},"You who dwell on many waters, abundant in treasures, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your end has come, the measure of your covetousness. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 51:14"},"The LORD of Armies has sworn by himself, saying, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘Surely I will fill you with men, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as with the canker worm; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will lift up a shout against you.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 51:15"},"“He has made the earth by his power. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He has established the world by his wisdom. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["By his understanding he has stretched out the heavens. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 51:16"},"When he utters his voice, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["there is a roar of waters in the heavens, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and he causes the vapours to ascend from the ends of the earth.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He makes lightning for the rain, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and brings the wind out of his treasuries. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 51:17"},"“Every man has become brutish without knowledge. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Every goldsmith is disappointed by his image; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for his molten image is falsehood, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and there is no breath in them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 51:18"},"They are vanity, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a work of delusion. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["In the time of their visitation, they will perish. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 51:19"},"The portion of Yaqub is not like these, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for he is the former of all things; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["including the tribe of his inheritance: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The LORD of Armies is his name. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 51:20"},"“You are my battle axe and weapons of war. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["With you I will break the nations into pieces. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["With you I will destroy kingdoms. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 51:21"},"With you I will break in pieces \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the horse and his rider. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 51:22"},"With you I will break in pieces \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the chariot and him who rides therein. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["With you I will break in pieces \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["man and woman. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["With you I will break in pieces \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the old man and the youth. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["With you I will break in pieces \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the young man and the virgin. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 51:23"},"With you I will break in pieces \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the shepherd and his flock. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["With you I will break in pieces \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the farmer and his yoke. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["With you I will break in pieces \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["governors and deputies. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 51:24"},"“I will render to Babylon and to all the inhabitants of Chaldea all their evil that they have done in Zion in your\nsight,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 51:25"},"“Behold, I am against you, destroying mountain,” says the LORD,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“which destroys all the earth. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will stretch out my hand on you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["roll you down from the rocks, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will make you a burnt mountain. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 51:26"},"They won’t take a cornerstone from you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["nor a stone for foundations; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but you will be desolate forever,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 51:27"},"“Set up a standard in the land! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Blow the trumpet amongst the nations! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Prepare the nations against her! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Call together against her the kingdoms of Ararat, Minni, and Ashkenaz!\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Appoint a marshal against her! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Cause the horses to come up as the rough canker worm! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 51:28"},"Prepare against her the nations, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the kings of the Medes, its governors, and all its deputies, and all the land of their dominion!\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JER 51:29"},"The land trembles and is in pain; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the purposes of the LORD against Babylon stand, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to make the land of Babylon a desolation, without inhabitant.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JER 51:30"},"The mighty men of Babylon have stopped fighting, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they remain in their strongholds. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Their might has failed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They have become as women. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Her dwelling places are set on fire. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Her bars are broken. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JER 51:31"},"One runner will run to meet another, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and one messenger to meet another, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to show the king of Babylon that his city is taken on every quarter.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JER 51:32"},"So the passages are seized. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They have burnt the reeds with fire. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The men of war are frightened.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JER 51:33"},"For the LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“The daughter of Babylon is like a threshing floor at the time when it is trodden.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Yet a little while, and the time of harvest comes for her.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JER 51:34"},"“Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon has devoured me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He has crushed me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He has made me an empty vessel. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He has, like a monster, swallowed me up. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He has filled his mouth with my delicacies. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He has cast me out. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JER 51:35"},"May the violence done to me and to my flesh be on Babylon!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the inhabitant of Zion will say; and, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“May my blood be on the inhabitants of Chaldea!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["will Jerusalem say. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JER 51:36"},"Therefore the LORD says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, I will plead your cause, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and take vengeance for you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will dry up her sea, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and make her fountain dry. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JER 51:37"},"Babylon will become heaps, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a dwelling place for jackals, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["an astonishment, and a hissing, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["without inhabitant. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JER 51:38"},"They will roar together like young lions. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They will growl as lions’ cubs. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JER 51:39"},"When they are heated, I will make their feast, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will make them drunk, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["that they may rejoice, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and sleep a perpetual sleep, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and not wake up,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"JER 51:40"},"“I will bring them down like lambs to the slaughter, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like rams with male goats. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"JER 51:41"},"“How Sheshach is taken! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["How the praise of the whole earth seized! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["How Babylon has become a desolation amongst the nations! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"JER 51:42"},"The sea has come up on Babylon. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["She is covered with the multitude of its waves. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"JER 51:43"},"Her cities have become a desolation, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a dry land, and a desert, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a land in which no man dwells. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["No son of man passes by it. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"JER 51:44"},"I will execute judgement on Bel in Babylon, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will bring out of his mouth that which he has swallowed up.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The nations will not flow any more to him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Yes, the wall of Babylon will fall. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"JER 51:45"},"“My people, go away from the middle of her, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and each of you save yourselves from the LORD’s fierce anger.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"JER 51:46"},"Don’t let your heart faint. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Don’t fear for the news that will be heard in the land. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For news will come one year, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and after that in another year news will come, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and violence in the land, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["ruler against ruler. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"JER 51:47"},"Therefore behold, the days come that I will execute judgement on the engraved images of Babylon;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and her whole land will be confounded. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["All her slain will fall in the middle of her. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"JER 51:48"},"Then the heavens and the earth, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all that is therein, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["will sing for joy over Babylon; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the destroyers will come to her from the north,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"JER 51:49"},"“As Babylon has caused the slain of Israel to fall, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so the slain of all the land will fall at Babylon. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"JER 51:50"},"You who have escaped the sword, go! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Don’t stand still! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Remember the LORD from afar, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and let Jerusalem come into your mind.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"JER 51:51"},"“We are confounded, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because we have heard reproach. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Confusion has covered our faces, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for strangers have come into the sanctuaries of the LORD’s house.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"JER 51:52"},"“Therefore behold, the days come,” says the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“that I will execute judgement on her engraved images; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and through all her land the wounded will groan. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53","sid":"JER 51:53"},"Though Babylon should mount up to the sky, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and though she should fortify the height of her strength, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["yet destroyers will come to her from me,” says the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54","sid":"JER 51:54"},"“The sound of a cry comes from Babylon, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and of great destruction from the land of the Chaldeans! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55","sid":"JER 51:55"},"For the LORD lays Babylon waste, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and destroys out of her the great voice! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Their waves roar like many waters. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The noise of their voice is uttered. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56","sid":"JER 51:56"},"For the destroyer has come on her, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even on Babylon. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Her mighty men are taken. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Their bows are broken in pieces, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for the LORD is Allah of retribution. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He will surely repay. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57","sid":"JER 51:57"},"I will make her princes, her wise men, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["her governors, her deputies, and her mighty men drunk. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They will sleep a perpetual sleep, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and not wake up,” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["says the King, whose name is the LORD of Armies. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"58","sid":"JER 51:58"},"The LORD of Armies says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“The wide walls of Babylon will be utterly overthrown. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Her high gates will be burnt with fire. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The peoples will labour for vanity, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the nations for the fire; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will be weary.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"59","sid":"JER 51:59"},"The word which Jeremiah the prophet commanded Seraiah the son of Neriah, the son of Mahseiah, when he went with Zedekiah\nthe king of Judah to Babylon in the fourth year of his reign. Now Seraiah was chief quartermaster.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"60","sid":"JER 51:60"},"Jeremiah wrote in a book all the evil that should come on Babylon, even all these words that are written concerning\nBabylon. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"61","sid":"JER 51:61"},"Jeremiah said to Seraiah, “When you come to Babylon, then see that you read all these words,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"62","sid":"JER 51:62"},"and say, ‘LORD, you have spoken concerning this place, to cut it off, that no one will dwell in it, neither man nor\nanimal, but that it will be desolate forever.’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"63","sid":"JER 51:63"},"It will be, when you have finished reading this book, that you shall bind a stone to it, and cast it into the middle of\nthe Euphrates. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"64","sid":"JER 51:64"},"Then you shall say, ‘Thus will Babylon sink, and will not rise again because of the evil that I will bring on her; and\nthey will be weary.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Thus far are the words of Jeremiah. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"52","sid":"JER 52"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JER 52:1"},"Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he began to reign. He reigned eleven years in Jerusalem: and his mother’s name was\nHamutal the daughter of Jeremiah of Libnah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JER 52:2"},"He did that which was evil in the LORD’s sight, according to all that Jehoiakim had done.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JER 52:3"},"For through the LORD’s anger this happened in Jerusalem and Judah, until he had cast them out from his presence.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Zedekiah rebelled against the king of Babylon. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JER 52:4"},"In the ninth year of his reign, in the tenth month, in the tenth day of the month, Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came, he\nand all his army, against Jerusalem, and encamped against it; and they built forts against it round about.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JER 52:5"},"So the city was besieged to the eleventh year of king Zedekiah.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JER 52:6"},"In the fourth month, in the ninth day of the month, the famine was severe in the city, so that there was no bread for the\npeople of the land. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JER 52:7"},"Then a breach was made in the city, and all the men of war fled, and went out of the city by night by the way of the gate\nbetween the two walls, which was by the king’s garden. Now the Chaldeans were against the city all around. The men of war went\ntowards the Arabah, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JER 52:8"},"but the army of the Chaldeans pursued the king, and overtook Zedekiah in the plains of Jericho; and all his army was\nscattered from him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JER 52:9"},"Then they took the king, and carried him up to the king of Babylon to Riblah in the land of Hamath; and he pronounced\njudgement on him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JER 52:10"},"The king of Babylon killed the sons of Zedekiah before his eyes. He also killed all the princes of Judah in Riblah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JER 52:11"},"He put out the eyes of Zedekiah; and the king of Babylon bound him in fetters, and carried him to Babylon, and put him in\nprison until the day of his death. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JER 52:12"},"Now in the fifth month, in the tenth day of the month, which was the nineteenth year of king Nebuchadnezzar, king of\nBabylon, Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard, who stood before the king of Babylon, came into Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JER 52:13"},"He burnt the LORD’s house, and the king’s house; and all the houses of Jerusalem, even every great house, he burnt with\nfire. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JER 52:14"},"All the army of the Chaldeans, who were with the captain of the guard, broke down all the walls of Jerusalem all around.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JER 52:15"},"Then Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard carried away captive of the poorest of the people, and the residue of the\npeople who were left in the city, and those who fell away, who fell to the king of Babylon, and the residue of the multitude.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JER 52:16"},"But Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard left of the poorest of the land to be vineyard keepers and farmers.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JER 52:17"},"The Chaldeans broke the pillars of bronze that were in the LORD’s house, and the bases and the bronze sea that were in\nthe LORD’s house in pieces, and carried all of their bronze to Babylon.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JER 52:18"},"They also took away the pots, the shovels, the snuffers, the basins, the spoons, and all the vessels of bronze with which\nthey ministered. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JER 52:19"},"The captain of the guard took away the cups, the fire pans, the basins, the pots, the lamp stands, the spoons, and the\nbowls; that which was of gold, in gold, and that which was of silver, in silver.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JER 52:20"},"They took the two pillars, the one sea, and the twelve bronze bulls that were under the bases, which king Sulaiman had\nmade for the LORD’s house. The bronze of all these vessels was without weight.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JER 52:21"},"As for the pillars, the height of the one pillar was eighteen\ncubits;",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["52:21 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man’s arm, or about 18\ninches or 46 centimetres."]}],"caller":"+"}," and a line of twelve cubits encircled it; and its thickness was four fingers. It was hollow.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JER 52:22"},"A capital of bronze was on it; and the height of the one capital was five\ncubits,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["52:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man’s arm, or about 18\ninches or 46 centimetres."]}],"caller":"+"}," with network and pomegranates on the capital all around, all of bronze: and the second pillar also\nhad like these, and pomegranates. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JER 52:23"},"There were ninety-six pomegranates on the sides; all the pomegranates were one hundred on the network all around.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JER 52:24"},"The captain of the guard took Seraiah the chief priest, and Zephaniah the second priest, and the three keepers of the\nthreshold: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JER 52:25"},"and out of the city he took an officer who was set over the men of war; and seven men of those who saw the king’s face,\nwho were found in the city; and the scribe of the captain of the army, who mustered the people of the land; and sixty men of\nthe people of the land, who were found in the middle of the city.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JER 52:26"},"Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard took them, and brought them to the king of Babylon to Riblah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JER 52:27"},"The king of Babylon struck them, and put them to death at Riblah in the land of Hamath.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So Judah was carried away captive out of his land. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JER 52:28"},"This is the number of the people whom Nebuchadnezzar carried away captive:\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":["in the seventh year, three thousand and twenty-three Jews; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JER 52:29"},"in the eighteenth year of Nebuchadnezzar, he carried away captive from Jerusalem eight hundred and thirty-two persons;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JER 52:30"},"in the twenty-third year of Nebuchadnezzar Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard carried away captive of the Jews seven\nhundred and forty-five people: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":["all the people were four thousand and six hundred. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JER 52:31"},"In the thirty-seventh year of the captivity of Jehoiachin king of Judah, in the twelfth month, in the twenty-fifth day of\nthe month, Evilmerodach king of Babylon, in the first year of his reign, lifted up the head of Jehoiachin king of Judah, and\nreleased him from prison. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JER 52:32"},"He spoke kindly to him, and set his throne above the throne of the kings who were with him in Babylon,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JER 52:33"},"and changed his prison garments. Jehoiachin ate bread before him continually all the days of his life.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JER 52:34"},"For his allowance, there was a continual allowance given him by the king of Babylon, every day a portion until the day of\nhis death, all the days of his life. "]}]}